title: layered pudding cake
directions: Bake cake mix as directed.
Fix pudding as directed.
When cake has cooled, slice in pieces.
Layer in big container cake, pudding, pie filling until you stop with pie filling.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: turkey cookout
directions: Wash turkey under cool running water.
Remove hair and pin feathers.
Pat dry with paper towels.
Lightly salt and pepper.

title: western hash
directions: Brown ground beef; drain and add all other ingredients. Simmer for 30 minutes.
Put in casserole dish.
Top with desired amount of sliced Velveeta cheese.
Put in oven for 15 minutes or until cheese is melted at 350°.

title: richard's ragging cajun turkey breast
directions: Take turkey and swizzel a little vinegar on.
Rub on Cajun seasoning into meat and then in seasoned bread crumbs.
Heat pan; add oil, then butter and garlic.
Quickly fry fillets 1 minute on each side or until brown but still tender.
Remove to plate; add more vinegar to frying pan.
Deglaze the pan and return in juices to pan from fillets.
Boil and reduce by 1/2.
Pour onto platter; arrange turkey on top.

title: peggy's banana pudding
directions: Mix all of the above together and layer alternating with bananas, vanilla wafers and pudding, winding up with pudding on the top.
Crumble a handful of vanilla wafers and spread over top for garnish.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.

Remove bacon from grease and add all ingredients except mushrooms, cream cheese, and bread crumbs. Cook until tender and then add cream cheese. Remove stems from mushrooms and stuff mounds with cream cheese mixture.
Place in a baking dish and add 1/4 cup hot water.
Spread bread crumbs on top and bake at 375 degrees for 20 minutes.
Insert a toothpick into each to serve.

title: english trifle
directions: Make pudding according to box directions.
Coat glass bowl with raspberry preserves.
Layer with slices of cake (sprinkled with brandy, sherry or rum), pudding, whipped cream and fruit with juice.
Continue layering to top of bowl.

title: orange pork tenderloin
directions: Mix butter, thyme and cayenne.
Spread on pork.
Place pork on rack in roasting pan.
Pour orange juice over it.
Roast at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes per pound or until temperature on meat thermometer reaches 185°.
Remove meat to platter and keep warm.

title: homemade brownies
directions: Melt butter and let it cool.
Add beaten eggs, sugar, cocoa, flour, vanilla and baking powder.
Mix well with a wooden spoon; do not use an electric mixer.
Bake at 350° in 9 x 13-inch greased and lightly floured pan for 25 minutes or until tops are firm. Top with chocolate frosting and 1 cup finely chopped walnuts.

title: buttermilk almond scones cafe latte
directions: In a bowl, whisk together 3 of the eggs, the buttermilk and almond extract.

title: homemade bubble solution
directions: Mix well.
Do not shake.
Store in closed container.
Make circle from wire coat hanger or other wire.
Dip into solution and wave in air to make giant bubbles (outside only).

title: sauteed broccoli
directions: In large skillet over medium heat, cook garlic in butter 1 minute; add broccoli, walnuts and salt.
Cover and cook 4 to 6 minutes until broccoli is crisp-tender, stirring frequently. Serve immediately.
Serves 6, each serving containing 135 calories.
Preparation time:
5 minutes; cook time:
7 minutes. Ready to serve in 15 minutes.

title: our best chicken salad
directions: Combine chicken or turkey, onion, celery and green pepper. Mix cream with mayonnaise, then add salt, pepper and lemon juice. Toss with chicken.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: key lime pie
directions: Peel and chop apples and set aside. Combine sugar, flour and salt. Add egg, vanilla and sour cream. Beat until smooth. Add apples; mix well and pour into pastry lined pie pan. Bake at 375° for 15 minutes. Reduce heat to 325° and bake 30 minutes longer. Remove from oven and sprinkle with topping.

title: potted pork
directions: In a heavy saucepan, combine all ingredients and simmer, covered over low heat for 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Pour into an earthenware crock or rustic serving dish. Chill.
Makes a delicious spread on melba toast for appetizer or on a slice of crusty bread for lunch.

title: stove top shoulder ham
directions: Place ham in pot after adding ingredients on top.
Place on high fire until it comes to a boil.
Cut to low fire.
Boil for 2 hours or until tender.

title: earthquake cake
directions: In 13x9 in. pan, spread butter, then spread chopped nuts, then spread shredded coconut.

title: cream cheese cake
directions: Beat cream cheese and sugar with mixer. Add sour cream, Cool Whip and vanilla. Pour in pie shell. Top with strawberry or pineapple topping.

title: yum yum cake
directions: Mix together cake mix, margarine and 1 egg.
Press in bottom of long pan.
Mix together cream cheese, 2 eggs and powdered sugar.
Spread over top of cake mixture.
Bake at 300° for about 45 minutes.

title: mayonnaise
directions: Beat eggs.
Stir in sour cream, vinegar, sugar, butter and mustard which has been rubbed smooth with a little vinegar.
Put on the stove in double boiler and cook until it thickens.
This will keep for several weeks in a cool place.

title: chicken in crock-pot
directions: Start high, then low for all day.
Serve with rice or noodles.

title: veggie bars
directions: Pat rolls into wide cookie sheet with edges.
Cook at 350° for 7 to 8 minutes or until light brown but not gummy.
Mix cream cheese, mayonnaise and dry Ranch dressing.
Spread on top crescent rolls.
Mix together peppers, mushrooms, broccoli and cheese. Cover and chill for 8 hours.

title: zucchini stuffing
directions: Saute diced zucchini and onion in 1/2 cup margarine until tender.
Melt 1/3 cup margarine in casserole dish.
Add cooked zucchini and onion, then stuffing, soup and sour cream.
Drizzle 1/4 cup margarine on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: sour cream corn bread
directions: Mix together.
Pour into 9-inch greased square pan.
Bake in preheated 400° oven for 30 minutes.

title: cheesey vegetable soup
directions: Saute onion in butter, do not brown.
Add vegetables and water. Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer covered for 10 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Stir in milk and cheese.
Heat through until cheeses are melted.
(Green Giant canned corn, vacum packed and added after other veggies are cooked.)

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Mix.
Refrigerate 12 hours (overnight).
Bake in greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: apple raisin bread(no sugar)
directions: Beat oil and egg; mix flour, baking powder, spice, soda and salt.
Soak raisins in hot water 5 minutes; drain.
Add a small amount of flour with oil mixture and mix to blend.
Add juice and remaining flour; mix to moisten.
Add apple and raisins.
Bake in loaf pan at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.
This bread toasts great and is excellent with butter and cinnamon.

title: shrimp salad
directions: In small mixing bowl, beat the cream cheese, sour cream and mayonnaise until smooth.
Spread on a 12-inch round serving platter.
Cover with seafood sauce.
Sprinkle with cheese, shrimp, onions and tomatoes.
Cover and chill.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: "francisco's gumbo"
directions: Throw it all in a pot; cook slowly for 1/2 to 2 hours.
Serve with rice.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Mix sugar, corn syrup, peanuts and salt.
Microwave on High for 7 1/2 to 9 1/2 minutes.
Add butter and vanilla.
Microwave on High until mixture reaches hard crack stage (300°).
Stir in soda. Pour onto buttered cookie sheet.
Cool and break into pieces.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown ground chuck with onion.
Drain off fat.
Mix all other ingredients.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer 45 minutes. Serve with bite-size Tostitos or crackers.

title: corn flake christmas wreaths
directions: Be careful in your selection, do not choose too young, and take only such as have been reared in a good moral atmosphere. Some insist on keeping them in a pickle, while others keep them in hot water.

This only makes them sour and sometimes bitter. Even poor varieties may be sweet, tender and good by garnishing them with smiles and flavored with kisses to taste, then wrap them in a mantle of charity, keep warm with a steady fire of domestic devotions and serve with peaches and cream.
When thus prepared, they will keep for years.

title: salmon stew
directions: Dice potatoes in small pieces. Cook until tender.
Add the salmon and its juices and the rest of the ingredients.
Cook for about 30 to 40 minutes, stirring to keep from sticking, on medium heat.

title: gingerbread cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Blend butter, sugar, spices and salt. Beat until fluffy.
Add molasses, milk and vanilla.
Beat thoroughly.
Continue beating and add flour gradually.
(Dough will pull from sides of bowl.)
Form flattened ball, wrap in waxed paper and chill for 2 hours or more.
Roll out on floured board and cut or mold shapes.
Bake for 12 minutes.
Cool cookies on rack.
Roll over and over and still have chewy cookies!
Yield: 5 dozen.

title: oven crusted chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In medium bowl, combine marjoram, flour, thyme and rosemary.
Dredge chicken in this mixture, then roll in margarine.
Roll in cereal to coat.
Place on rack in shallow baking pan.
Bake 55 to 60 minutes or until golden brown.

title: impossible pie(makes its own crust)
directions: Mix in a blender.
Pour into buttered 9-inch Pyrex pie plate. Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: anita's hot chicken salad
directions: Cook chicken, rice and eggs.
Dice chicken and combine in a bowl with all other ingredients, except for crackers.
Mix well and add salt and pepper to taste.
Spread mixture into an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Crush Ritz crackers and cover mixture.
Pour 1/2 stick butter or margarine over crackers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cut into squares and serve on lettuce leaves.

title: double chocolate nugget cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Blend cake mix, oil, eggs and vanilla. Beat by hand about 2 minutes. Add chocolate chips and pecans. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet. Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°. Makes about 4 dozen cookies.

title: toby's frozen fruit slush
directions: Mix together first 2 ingredients. Bring to a boil. Cook about 1 minute; sugar should be dissolved. Cool.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding and 1/2 container Cool Whip.
In a large casserole dish, layer the bananas.
Spoon on part of pudding mix.
Sprinkle on wafers and drizzle Eagle Brand.
Repeat layers until all ingredients are used.
Top with remaining Cool Whip and refrigerate overnight.

title: chocolate chip oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix margarine, sugar, lemon extract and Ricotta cheese in large bowl.
Blend well, then add eggs.
Blend well.
Mix dry ingredients in separate bowl, then gradually add to other mixture, blending well each time it is combined.
A soft dough will form. Roll into 1-inch balls.
Bake 15 minutes at 350° on greased cookie sheets.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Mix together shortening, sugar and eggs.
Add flour, soda, cream of tartar and salt.
Chill dough.
Roll into balls and roll them into a mixture of cinnamon and sugar.
Flatten on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: stuffed dates
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients well; fill hot dogs with cheese mixture.
Place on baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Serve hot.
Makes 5 servings.

title: stuffed ham roll
directions: Cut French bread in half (lengthwise).
Hollow out center. Mix cheese well and add mayonnaise, celery and onion.
Use softened butter on bread halves; roll pickles with ham slices and place on bread.
Put bread halves together; wrap in plastic wrap to chill overnight before serving.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Fry cabbage and onion in water and oil until cabbage is tender.
Brown hamburger; add hamburger and tomato paste to cabbage and onion mixture.
(Don't forget to drain grease off hamburger.)
Simmer approximately 10 minutes.

title: broiled shrimp
directions: Arrange shrimp in shallow baking pan, one tucked alongside the next. Melt butter and add lemon juice, garlic powder and parsley.
Pour 3/4 of this over the shrimp. Broil about 5 inches from heat for 4 minutes. (Extra large shrimp will have to be turned and broiled a few extra minutes.)
Baste with remaining sauce and serve.

title: red cake
directions: Mix together cocoa, soda and vinegar.
Mix cake mix as directed (whole egg).
Add cocoa mix and red food coloring.
Bake as directed on box.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Mix in order; bake in bread pan at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: apple dip
directions: Melt cream cheese and spread in a small pan.
Top with a layer of butterscotch, caramel, fudge topping; sprinkle top with nuts. Serve with sliced apples for dipping.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw spinach completely.
Squeeze remaining water out.
In a large bowl, mix all ingredients together until well blended. Chill overnight.

title: prune jam
directions: Place prunes and orange juice in blender.
Mix until thick.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream together	butter	and
sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Sift together dry ingredients and add into
batter
along
with
applesauce.
Roll nuts and fruits in 1/2 cup flour and then mix them into the batter.

title: moss ball
directions: Place cheese in bowl until soft.
Add onion and Worcestershire sauce; beat.
Chill.
Put on plate and roll in parsley.
Chill 2 hours.

title: grandmother endsley's cheese biscuits
directions: Sift flour, salt, pepper and paprika.
Mix margarine, cheese and flour mixture.
Work in with hands until it will hold together.
Roll 1/4-inch thin.
Cut with small cutter.
Prick top with fork.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Watch carefully, they will scorch easily.

title: banana split cake
directions: Melt 1 stick of
butter and mix with graham crackers. Press into bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Beat for 15 minutes with electric mixer the 2 sticks butter, eggs and confectioners sugar.
Pour over graham crackers.
Slice bananas and layer on cake mix.
Drain pineapple and layer over bananas.
Layer Cool Whip over pineapple.
Sprinkle on nuts.
Drizzle on chocolate syrup.
Put cherries on top.

title: meringue shells
directions: Beat eggs until foamy; beat in salt and cream of tartar.
Add sugar a tablespoon at a time, beating gradually, then add powdered sugar.
Beat until it will not drop from beaters.
Put on greased wax paper.
Bake at 275° for 20 minutes.
Turn off oven and leave in oven for 5 minutes.
Cool and remove from pan.

title: swedish gingerbreads
directions: Mix molasses, sugar, and butter in a pan.
Melt it.
Add cream and spices, mix.
Mix the baking powder with a little of the flour.
Mix everything in a large bowl.
Put the dough in aluminum pan in the refrigerator.
Leave to harden a few days.
Take a little of the dough out, hit it a little, mix a little more flour in it if needed.
Sprinkle flour on a table, roll the dough as thin as possible.
Press shapes in it.
Put the cookies on a greased baking sheet.
Cook 5 - 10 minutes until brown.

title: baked fish
directions: Melt margarine in skillet.
Add onion and green pepper.
Cook until almost done.
Add tomatoes and basil to skillet.
Let cook about 5 more minutes.
Arrange fish in foil covered pan.
Sprinkle with Mrs. Dash.
Cut slits in top of fish.
Insert bacon.
Pour mixture from skillet over fish.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour at 350°.
Serve with favorite vegetables.

title: squash patties
directions: Mash squash.
Add other ingredients.
Drop by spoonfuls into deep fat.
Brown on one side.
Turn over and brown on the other side.
Remove from fat and drain on paper towels.

title: 5 layer casserole
directions: Layer in casserole in order given.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Wash, skin broccoli down to tenderest parts.
Chop in very small pieces.
Chop onion in small pieces.
Mix in bowl.
Cover tightly and leave overnight in refrigerate.
Before serving mix mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar.
Put cheese and dressing in bowl. Stir all together.
Serve.

title: microwave cheesecake
directions: Melt butter in an 8 x 12-inch baking dish; add cinnamon and crumbs.
Mix together, reserving 3 tablespoons for topping.
Press crumb mixture into bottom and sides of pan to form crust.

title: mom's squash casserole
directions: Cook and drain squash/onion very well.
Add all other ingredients, except stuffing.
Top casserole with stuffing.
Cook at 250° until bubbly.

title: eggplant or zucchini souffle
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9-inch casserole dish.
Cut eggplant or zucchini into pieces and cook in boiling water until tender.
Drain well and mash slightly.
Make white sauce with butter, flour and milk.
When thick and smooth, add eggplant or zucchini, onion, catsup, cheese, crumbs and seasonings.
Beat egg yolks and stir into mixture.
Beat egg whites until stiff; fold into vegetable mixture.
Pour into casserole and bake for 45 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: caramel corn with peanuts
directions: Pop popcorn.
Remove all unpopped kernels.
Set aside.
In saucepan, combine brown sugar, corn syrup, margarine and peanuts. Bring mixture to boil and boil 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add soda and vanilla.
Stir well.
Pour hot mixture over popcorn. Spread covered corn onto shallow baking pans.
Bake 1 hour at 250°, stirring every 15 minutes.
Cool.
Break apart and store in Ziploc bags.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix together all ingredients except crackers/corn flakes and margarine.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes, covered.
Add crumbled topping; dot with margarine.
Bake, uncovered, 10 minutes or until topping browns.

title: chicken salad
directions: Put all together and mix.
Serve on chef salad or sandwiches.

title: pinto bean soup
directions: Wash beans; cover with water and bring to a boil.
Cut heat to low and allow to simmer about 2 hours.
Saute onion, garlic and ground beef.
When browned, add chili powder.
Add meat mixture, parsley, celery and tomatoes to beans.
Return to a boil; cut heat again to low.
Simmer for 2 hours.
Add sliced carrots during last hour of cooking time.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: broccoli quiche
directions: Toss cheese with flour.
Add broccoli, milk, eggs, mushrooms and seasonings.
Mix well.
Pour into pastry shell.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes to 1 hour or until set.
Makes 6 servings.

title: four layer dessert
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix flour, butter and almonds and press into pan.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes.
Mix cream cheese and powdered sugar; fold in Cool Whip.
Spread over crust.
Mix pudding and milk until thick.
Spread over second layer.
Spread Cool Whip on top.
Refrigerate.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Mix milk with pudding.
Then add Cool Whip.
Stir until smooth.
Use a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer the bottom of pan with graham crackers.
Pour half of pudding on graham crackers and then put another layer of graham crackers.
Pour the rest of mixture on these.
Put last layer of graham crackers on.
Heat chocolate icing for 30 seconds in microwave, then ice the top of graham crackers.
Refrigerate.

title: reuben casserole
directions: Place sauerkraut in a 1 1/2-quart glass casserole.
Top with corned beef, then shredded cabbage.
Combine mayonnaise and Thousand Island dressing; spread over cheese.
Top with tomato slices.
Melt margarine and stir bread crumbs into it.
Sprinkle buttered crumbs over tomato slices.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: hot water cornmeal(quick and easy)
directions: Combine cornmeal, salt and sugar or sugar substitute in bowl. Mix well.
Add hot water slowly, stirring and mixing constantly. Batter should be thick so you can make cakes.
Wet hands and pat mixture into cakes.
Fry in hot grease until golden brown.
Do not cook too slow, but cooking too fast will make it appear raw.
Keep in mind it's okay because the hot water has already cooked the meal.
You're just making it crispy.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook and drain broccoli.
Mix together all but crackers.
Put in 9 x 13-inch glass casserole.
Saute cracker crumbs and 3/4 cube of butter in skillet.
Spread over broccoli mixture and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: monkey bread
directions: Mix sugar and cinnamon in bowl.
Break apart biscuits and roll into one inch balls.
Toss balls in sugar mixture.
Place in greased Bundt pan.
Melt butter and pour over.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Flip onto a large plate when done.

title: strawberry banana salad
directions: Strain fruit.
Cream together cream cheese and sugar.
Add pineapple, strawberries, nuts and bananas.
Fold in Cool Whip. Freeze in a 9 x 13-inch pan or plastic container.
Keep frozen. Cut into squares.

title: reuben sandwich
directions: Place half of corn beef and half of cheese on bread and repeat another layer.
Steam until corn beef is hot and cheese is melted.
Layer beef, cheese, sauerkraut, Russian dressing and repeat.
Top with bread.

title: veal and tarragon tomato cream
directions: In a large skillet, melt butter over moderate heat.
Add the shallots and saute until tender, 2 to 3 minutes.
Add veal and saute, breaking veal up into small pieces with a wooden spoon, until veal is no longer pink, about 5 minutes.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Simmer until thick, about 10 minutes.
Serve immediately over angel hair pasta or spaghetti.

title: cheese souffle
directions: Butter both sides of bread and break into pieces.
Make 3 layers of bread and cheese.
Start with bread layer and top with cheese. Combine the eggs, salt, dry mustard, pepper and milk. Pour over cheese and bread.
Refrigerate overnight (covered). Take from refrigerator 1 hour before cooking.
Place dish in pan of water and bake at 350° for 1 hour, uncovered.

title: cranberry sauce
directions: Drain pineapple.
Save juice and use with water. Boil 1 1/2 cups water, add jello and bring to a boil.
Take off immediately and add 1 cup water and the 1/2 cup juice and the rest of the ingredients.
Stir around until cranberries are spread around and jelly is dissolved.
Put in refrigerator and let set.

title: dill sauced meat loaf
directions: Mix ground beef, onion, bread crumbs, dill juice, egg, salt and pepper until well blended.
Shape into loaf in shallow pan. Combine dill pickle, catsup, water, sugar and Worcestershire sauce.
Pour over loaf and bake 40 to 50 minutes at 350°, basting two or three times.
Serves 6.

title: aunt nell's brown sugar candy
directions: Mix all ingredients but marshmallow cream together in a large pot.
Cook until it reaches a soft ball stage.
Remove from heat and add the marshmallow cream.
Beat until it sets up.
Pour into greased pans.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix all ingredients, adding broccoli last. Bake for 30 minutes or until golden brown at 350°.

title: mulled cider
directions: Mix ingredients and simmer 20 minutes. Serve hot on a cold winter day.

title: potato salad
directions: Boil peeled potatoes with salt.
Drain and set aside until cooled.
Dice potatoes into a large mixing bowl.
Add the green peppers, onions, celery seed and diced eggs to the bowl.
Add mayonnaise and mustard (you should add just enough mustard to color the salad).
Combine the sugar and vinegar; pour over the salad.
Gently mix.
Garnish with sliced eggs and paprika.

title: beef tortilla casserole
directions: Brown beef and season slightly with garlic salt and pepper. Mix into beef; soups, sauces and green chilies.
Heat, stirring occasionally.
Add salt to taste and place in casserole alternating tortillas and sauce.
Sprinkle cheese and onion between each layer. Bake at 350° until bubbly, about 1/2 hour.
Place cheese on top to melt through dish.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients; add pineapple.
Place in refrigerator for 15 minutes.
Remove and add lemon juice.
Mix well and pour into graham cracker crusts.
Chill in refrigerator.
Serve cold. Makes 2 pies.

title: impossible lasagna pie
directions: Grease a 10 x 1-1/2 inch pie plate.
Layer Cottage & Parmesan Cheese in plate.
Mix Beef, Herbs, Paste & 1/2 c. Mozzarella Cheese; spoon on top.
Beat Milk, Bisquick, Eggs, Salt and Pepper 15 seconds in blender on high or 1 minute with hand beater.
Pour into plate.
Bake at 400 for 30 - 35 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Sprinkle with remaining Mozzarella Cheese.
Can trim it with strips of Green Peppers and Tomatoes.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Dump all of pineapple, juice, sugar, flour and grated cheese into a greased casserole dish.
Melt stick of butter; crumble Ritz crackers.
Mix butter and crackers together; put on top of pineapple mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter squares
directions: Melt 2 sticks of butter; mix in graham cracker crumbs, sugar and peanut butter. Press mixture into ungreased 9 x 13 pan. In microwave, melt 1 stick of butter with chocolate chips; do not overcook! Pour chocolate over top of peanut butter mixture. Chill until hardens and enjoy!

title: eggplant parmesan
directions: Peel eggplant and slice.
Dip slices in egg and milk mixture, then into bread crumbs.
Cover bottom of frying pan with cooking oil and fry eggplant.
Sprinkle each slice with small amount of garlic powder while frying.
Add more oil as necessary.

title: deviled eggs
directions: In large pot, add water and gently add eggs.
Bring water to hard rapid boil.
Reduce to simmer for 10 minutes.
Put pot into sink and fill with cold water.
Let sit for 20 minutes. Meanwhile, cut bacon into 1/2-inch pieces and fry until crisp. Drain and set aside.
In a small bowl, mix mayonnaise, mustard, salt and pepper; set aside.
Peel eggs; cut in half lengthwise, separating the whites and yolks.
Rinse out whites.
Mash yolks into fine substance.
Add bacon and mix well.
Add to mayonnaise mixture and mix well.
Add more mayonnaise if desired.
Fill egg whites with mixture.
Sprinkle with paprika and serve.
Best served cold.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Lightly grease muffin or corn stick pan.
Combine all ingredients; blend well.
Fill pans almost full and bake for 18 or 20 minutes.

title: cream puff cake
directions: Bring to a boil the water and oleo.
Remove from heat.
Add flour.
Mix in eggs 1 at a time, mixing well.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan, greased, and up sides.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes. Cool.
Mix milk and cream cheese, then add pudding.
Mix well and spread on crust.
Top with Cool Whip, nuts and syrup if desired. Good even with diet or sugar-free pudding.

title: baked sour cream chicken
directions: In a medium bowl, combine first 8 ingredients. Dip chicken in batter, then roll in crumbs.
Place meaty side down in a large greased baking pan. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes, turning over after 1/2 hour.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: winter salad
directions: Combine first 9 ingredients in a small bowl. Combine salad greens, grapefruit, onion and walnuts in a large bowl. Drizzle with vinegar mixture, tossing to coat. Yields 6 servings of 1 1/2 cups each.

title: yum yum casserole
directions: Brown meat and onions in shortening.
Add water to barely cover with celery and cook slow for 20 minutes or until tender. Add other ingredients and place in casserole.
Top with crushed potato chips.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: macaroon pie
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together.
Add egg whites and almond extract.
Pour into well buttered pie pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Serve with whipped cream.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: broccoli-cheese casserole
directions: Cool broccoli.
Drain and chop.
Mix soup, eggs, mayonnaise and cheese.
Pour over broccoli.
Melt butter.
Mix with crushed crackers.
Sprinkle over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: many layer salad
directions: Layer in order given, spreading ingredients evenly.
Cover closely with Saran Wrap and refrigerate for 12 to 24 hours.
Mix before serving.

title: triple chocolate brownie pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 8-inch pie plate.
In a small bowl, beat eggs.
Add sugar and butter.
In a separate bowl, stir together flour, cocoa and salt.
Add to egg mixture.
Beat well. stir in chips, nuts, vanilla.
Spread into prepared pan and bake 35 minutes or until set - it will not test done in the center. Cool completely.
Cut into wedges.
Drizzle with chocolate topping.

title: baked fish fillets
directions: Mix potato flakes, oil, salt and paprika.
Roll fish in mixture.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.

title: crock-pot dressing
directions: Note:
If using seasoned stuffing mix, omit herbs and salt.

title: glazed walnuts
directions: Bring to a boil. Cook to soft ball stage. Add walnuts.
Beat until fluffy. Spread on wax paper until dry.

title: special brownies
directions: Sift flour; add melted Crisco.
Combine sugar, cocoa and well beaten eggs.
Add to flour mixture.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Bake in well-greased pan at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: low-fat sweet potato crunch
directions: Cook cubed sweet potatoes in boiling water for 15 minutes or until tender.
Drain.
Let cool.
Position knife blade in food processor bowl.
Add potatoes and applesauce; process until smooth.
Add egg yolk, vanilla extract and cinnamon.
Process until smooth; set aside in a bowl.
Beat egg whites (room temperature) until stiff peaks form.
Gently stir 1/3 of egg whites into sweet potato mixture, then gently fold in remaining egg whites.
Spoon into 1 1/2-quart souffle dish coated with cooking spray.
Combine sugar, flour and margarine and sprinkle over potato mixture.
Bake at 350°
for 35 minutes.

title: the best homemade ice cream(no cholesterol)
directions: Separate eggs.	Beat egg whites stiff. Beat egg yolks (Egg Beaters) until lemon colored.

title: cheesy corn pudding
directions: Dissolve cornstarch in liquid.
Blend all ingredients well with a mixer at medium speed.
Pour into an oiled casserole dish. Bake, uncovered, in 375° oven until mixture is set and top is lightly browned.
This keeps well, refrigerated, for 3 or 4 days.

title: crushed pecan pie
directions: Mix together ingredients in the order listed.
Then add melted butter.
Put in an unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: bouncing ball punch
directions: Prepare approximately 40 minutes before needed.
Let frozen melon balls stand at room temperature for 20 minutes.
Mix the fruit punch drink, lemonade concentrate and water in punch bowl. Add frozen melon balls.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Stir.
Serve.

title: company ham
directions: Roast at 325° for 5 to 7 pounds, 2 to 2 1/2 hours; 7 to 10 pounds, 2 1/2 to 3 hours; 10 to 12 pounds, 3 to 3 1/2 hours; 12 to 14 pounds, 3 1/2 to 4 hours.

title: broccoli-onion deluxe
directions: Cut up fresh broccoli and cook or cook frozen broccoli according to package directions.
Drain.
Cook frozen or fresh onions in boiling salted water until tender.
Drain.

title: amish dressing
directions: Prepare bread by
cutting
in small pieces and toasting in oven. Melt butter in skillet
and
put crumbs in to toast a little, this adds good flavor.
In
a
larger
bowl,
put
chicken pieces, broth, cooked vegetables (potatoes, celery
and
carrots, cut
the size of peas, and cooked in salt
water),
salt, pepper, onions and beaten eggs.
(If not enough broth to soak up bread, add some milk.) Pour over toasted bread. Grease roaster.
Put dressing in and bake covered at 350° approximately 1 hour.
Serves 12 to 15.
If stuffing bird, omit broth, eggs and milk.

title: lula campbell's ham sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Cook in top of double boiler until thickened.
Serve warm.

title: quickie chicken pie
directions: Place meat in bottom of shallow baking dish. Melt margarine and pour over chicken. Slice eggs over top of chicken & margarine mixture. Mix flour, baking powder and milk. Pour over eggs. Mix soup and chicken broth in sauce pot. Bring to a boil. Pour over top. Bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes.

title: homemade shake 'n bake
directions: Grind 1 pound of saltine crackers in a food processor.
Mix all ingredients together and store indefinitely in the refrigerator in a covered container.

title: mama's shrimp creole
directions: In a large saucepan, combine tomatoes and seasonings.
Add vegetables and stir until thoroughly moistened. Cook over medium-high heat until vegetables are tender, stirring occasionally. Combine cornstarch and water.
Add shrimp.
Heat and stir just until boiling.
Remove bay leaf. Serve over rice.
Makes 6 servings.

title: yorkshire pudding mary ann
directions: Mix flour and salt together; gradually add milk, beating until smooth after each addition.
Add eggs one at a time, beating until smooth.
Cover and chill for 2 hours.
Pour into hot shallow (8 x 10-inch) pan, containing oil.
Bake at 425° for 25 to 30 minutes. Cut into squares and serve immediately with gravy.
Yields 6 portions.

title: sunday brunch casserole
directions: In a skillet, cook bacon until crisp. Cool and crumble. Set aside. In the drippings, saut onion and green pepper until tender; remove with a slotted spoon. Stir in hash browns, cheese, salt, pepper, dill, onion, green pepper and bacon. Transfer to a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Bake, uncovered, at 350°
for 35 to 45 minutes or until a knife inserted near the center comes out clean. Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: cheese wafers
directions: Cut butter into flour until texture resembles coarse meal. Mix in cheese, cayenne pepper and salt.
Fold in Rice Krispies. Pinch off small pieces; place on cookie sheet and pat flat.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Double the recipe serves 150 people.

title: champagne salad
directions: Cream together sugar and cream cheese.
Add drained pineapple. Then add strawberries, bananas, nuts and Cool Whip.
Mix well and refrigerate several hours before serving.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Chop garlic, onions and peppers very finely.
Add all ingredients, except cheese.
Use bacon drippings in skillet.
Pour 1/2 of mixture into pan.
Add cheese and add remaining batter. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: freezer cucumbers
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and let stand at least 1 hour. Squeeze out water.
Add the next 3 ingredients and stir together. Keep in refrigerator covered.
Stir everyday for 5 days, then put in containers and freeze.
Makes crisp and delicious pickles.

title: jan hagels
directions: Cream butter with sugar and egg yolk.
Sift flour and cinnamon.
Pat down thin in a cookie sheet.
Brush top with egg white.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Bake in preheated 300° oven for 1/2 hour.
When cool, cut into squares.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Drop a tablespoonful into hot grease.

title: rhubarb cherry crunch
directions: Place rhubarb in an 11 x 7-inch baking pan.
Combine sugar and cornstarch in a small saucepan.
Gradually stir in water.
Cook, stirring constantly over medium heat, until thick.
Stir in pie filling and almond extract.
Pour over rhubarb.
Combine oatmeal, flour, sugar, salt and butter until crumbly.
Add walnuts and sprinkle over fruit.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: cranberry muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease muffin pans.
Sift about half of sugar with other dry ingredients.
Mix other half of sugar with cranberries; add to flour mixture.
Combine liquids and add to dry ingredients.
Mix until lumpy.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.
Brush tops with butter and sprinkle with sugar.
Makes 12 to 14 muffins.

title: pineapple and american cheese salad
directions: Beat egg; add sugar, flour, pineapple juice and water.
Cook until thick.
Cool and pour over pineapple, cheese, marshmallows and nuts mixture.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix together and roll into small balls.
Refrigerate.
Melt 1 pound chocolate coating; dip balls and place in freezer for 3 to 4 minutes.

title: annie's "pig out" cake
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl and stir well.
Bake in 2 nine-inch cake pans.
Let cool.
Split to make 4 layers.

title: sweet potato muffins
directions: Grease
muffin
cups
or prepare with paper liners. Preheat oven
to
Beat sugar, sweet potatoes and margarine until
smooth.
Add
eggs
and blend well.
Sift together flour, baking
powder, spices and salt.
Add alternately with milk to sweet
potato mixture, stirring just to blend; do not over mix. Fold
in raisins and nuts.
Spoon into muffin cups. May be frozen and re-heated.

title: sugarless millionaire pie
directions: Mix pudding with milk.
Add to pudding mix the pineapple and pecans and fold in 1/2 of Cool Whip.
Pour into baked pie shell. Top with remaining Cool Whip.

title: cheese potato soup
directions: Cook vegetables in 2 cups of water with the 2 chicken bouillon cubes.
Bring to a boil.
Turn down to a simmer for about 30 minutes or until vegetables are soft.
Mix 1/4 cup milk and 1/4 cup flour to make a paste.
Pour paste in with the vegetables. Add 2 3/4 cups milk of milk and Velveeta cheese (ham cubes are optional).

title: marinated fish
directions: Coat the fish pieces all over with flour.
Heat oil in skillet and when hot, fry the fish pieces.
Remove fish and set aside. Then fry the sliced onions and peppers in the same skillet.

title: toffee cookie squares
directions: Sift flour.
Add salt and sugar.
Cut in margarine until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Add beaten egg yolk and vanilla. Pack into a 9 x 9-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
While warm, spread with melted chocolate.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Cool and cut into small squares.

title: graham cracker delight
directions: Boil margarine, butter and sugar at full boil for 3 minutes. Line cookie sheet with foil.
Place graham crackers which have been broken on the foil.
Pour boiled mixture over crackers.
Bake 10 minutes at 325°.
While hot, sprinkle mini-chocolate chips over the top.
Spread as melts, sprinkle with chopped walnuts.

title: no-cook refrigerator pickles
directions: *Or, use 1 cup white vinegar.

title: smoke sausage in sweet and sour sauce
directions: Cut sausage into bite-size pieces and brown in skillet. Mix jelly, chili sauce
and lemon juice in boiler.
Add enough water to rinse chili
sauce
jar.
Simmer
on
low heat.
Pour over sausage.

title: cucumber-sour cream salad
directions: Pare cucumbers and slice thinly into large bowl. Stir together other ingredients, except dill weed.
Pour over cucumbers and toss lightly.
Sprinkle with dill weed.
Cover and chill.
Just before serving, toss carefully.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: puppy chow(for people)
directions: In a small bowl, combine chocolate morsels and oil.
Microwave on High 1 1/2 minutes or until chocolate melts.
Stir in peanut butter.
Pour mixture over Crispix cereal.
Stir.
Place confectioners sugar into a gallon size storage bag.
Add coated cereal and close bag tightly.
Shake bag gently until cereal is thoroughly coated.
Refrigerate to store.

title: mountain top krispies
directions: *May substitute pecan pieces.
tags: huge scoop Jif crunchy peanut butter

title: monster cookies
directions: In a very large bowl, mix eggs, brown sugar, margarine, peanut butter, white sugar and vanilla.
Add baking soda and oats.
Stir in M&M's, chocolate chips and pecans.
Drop by rounded teaspoonful onto an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 15 dozen large cookies.
They freeze great!

title: butter pound cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and eggs; add eggs one at a time until fluffy.
Add vanilla and flour.
Bake in a greased and floured loaf pan at 350° for 20 minutes, then 375° for 30 minutes.

title: edna's no mistake yellow squash casserole
directions: In saucepan, cook squash, onion and green and red sweet peppers in melted margarine over medium heat for 7 to 9 minutes or until vegetables are slightly softened.
Thoroughly mix mayonnaise, cheese, egg, sugar and seasonings into vegetables. Spoon into a 2 1/2 quart baking dish that has been sprayed with nonstick coating.
Sprinkle with cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until bubbly and browned.
Makes 8 servings.

title: cherry pudding
directions: Melt margarine in 2-quart baking dish. Mix sugar, flour, baking powder, salt and milk in a bowl.
Pour batter into melted margarine and mix well. Sweeten fruit to taste and pour into batter. Do not stir.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: azalea's spanish baked beans
directions: Mix vinegar, sugar, salt, mustard and Worcestershire sauce. Slice or chop onion and pepper and stir in.
Add flour.
Stir in beans and bake at 400° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: nacho dip
directions: Mix together the sour cream and cream cheese.
Layer all ingredients, except onion and tomato.
Heat until cheese is melted.
Add onion and tomato on top.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Melt margarine; stir in remaining ingredients, except chocolate chips and paraffin.
Form into small balls.
Melt paraffin and chocolate chips in double boiler.
Dip balls in chocolate and paraffin mixture and place on waxed paper to set.

title: cherry salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Keep in refrigerator overnight.

title: zucchini brownies
directions: Beat all ingredients in a large mixing bowl for one minute. Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
If desired, frost with a chocolate glaze.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Measure corn flake crumbs, sugar and margarine into 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan; mix thoroughly.
With back of tablespoon, press mixture evenly and firmly in bottom of pan to form crust.

title: sauce piquante
directions: Season meat and brown in olive oil.
Add onions and bell peppers.
Simmer for 3 to 4 minutes.
Add tomato sauce, celery soup, mushroom soup, relish, olives, Kitchen Bouquet, parsley and water.
Cook until meat is tender.
Add bay leaves.
Cook for 10 minutes and remove.
Season to taste with red and black peppers, garlic powder, Season-All salt, lemon pepper, Tony Chachere Creole seasoning.

title: oatmeal chocolate chip
directions: Cream together sugars, eggs and shortening.
Add rest of ingredients.
Mix well.
Spoon on cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: sunday rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Mix well,
then	add hot water, oil, beaten eggs, honey, salt and ginger.
Add unsifted wheat flour
and	white flour.
Mix
well;
chill
overnight. Shape into rolls.
Bake in 425° oven for 12 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Bring reserved pineapple juice to boil in saucepan.
Remove from heat.
Dissolve jello in hot juice.
Add cranberry sauce and vinegar.
Stir to melt.
Add pineapple and nuts.
Carefully fold in oranges.
Pour into a serving dish.
Refrigerate 4 hours.

title: new ranger cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix, sugar, shortening, eggs and vanilla.
Stir in remaining ingredients, mixing thoroughly. Dough will be stiff.
Drop by teaspoonful about 2-inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 9 to 11 minutes.
Cool before removing from cookie sheet.
Yields 5 dozen.

title: salmon souffle
directions: Mix ingredients together except egg whites.
In separate bowl beat the 2 egg whites until stiff.
Fold in the beaten egg whites. Spoon into a 1 1/2-quart buttered casserole.
Top with 1 cup cracker crumbs that have been tossed with 3 tablespoons melted butter.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: potatoes, french alps style
directions: Heat oven to 375°. Place potatoes in 4 layers in buttered 2-quart shallow baking pan, sprinkling each layer with 1/4 of the salt, pepper, nutmeg and cheese. Dot with butter. Pour broth over potatoes. Place pan over direct heat until broth bubbles. Transfer to oven and bake until potatoes are tender, top is brown and broth is absorbed, 1 hour. Makes 6 servings.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion in 4 tablespoons butter until soft.
Stir in flour.
Add water.
Cook over low heat, stirring until mixture thickens and comes to a boil.
Blend in Cheez Whiz and combine sauce with broccoli.
Add eggs and mix gently until blended.
Turn into 1 1/2-quart greased casserole.
Cover with crumbs and dot with remaining butter.
Bake covered at 325° for 1 hour.
Makes 8 servings.

title: italian casserole
directions: In a large skillet saute onions and green peppers in butter until onions are clear and peppers are soft. Remove from skillet and discard leftover butter. Add ground beef and saute until gray. Put beef, onions and peppers into a large soup pot. Add tomato soup, water, noodles and tomato paste and boil until noodles are soft. Add corn and olives and place in large casserole dish. Cover with cheese and dot the top with butter. Bake at 375 degrees for approximately 45 minutes.

title: poor man steak
directions: Mix all ingredients except mushroom soup.
Slice into squares. Place in refrigerator overnight.
Take out of refrigerator next day and pour soup over meat.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: slaw
directions: Mix all ingredients and sprinkle with 1/2 cup sugar.
Mix 1 cup sugar, 1/2 cup oil, 1/2 cup vinegar, 1 tablespoon mustard and 1 tablespoon salt.
Bring to a boil.
Add black pepper to taste.

title: cheddar crown onion bread
directions: Generously grease a 12 cup Bundt pan.
In a large bowl, combine flour mixture, yeast and cheese.
Mix well.
Stir in hot water, oil, egg and chives.
Knead dough for 5 minutes.
Cover and let rest 5 minutes.

title: butterscotch chews
directions: Melt butter, when cool put in mixer with milk, sugar and eggs; blend well.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Stir into egg mixture and blend well.
Add vanilla, raisins and chocolate chips.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush in blender the Oreo cookies.
Mix together the butter, soft cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Mix and add the pudding and milk.
Add Cool Whip.
Put in flowerpot in layers of cookie crumbs and pudding mix.

title: pepper steak
directions: Cut steak in slices and brown in oil 10 to 15 minutes.
Add onion, garlic salt and pepper.
Dissolve bouillon cube in boiling water, then add to meat.
Cover and simmer 25 minutes.
Add tomatoes and bell pepper and simmer 15 minutes more.
Mix flour, cold water and add soy sauce.
Add to meat and stir slowly until thickened and cook 30 minutes more.

title: butter pecan ice cream
directions: Saute pecans in butter for 5 minutes, until toasted.
Cool. Combine remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour mixture into freezer can.
Freeze until ice cream is thick.
Remove dasher and add pecans.
Return dasher and freeze until firm.
Let ripen one hour.

title: pineapple walnut cake
directions: Beat together.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: shrimp spread
directions: Combine all ingredients (except shrimp).
Blend until creamy. Add shrimp (fold lightly).
When ready to serve, add cocktail sauce on top.

title: chili and beans
directions: Cook ground beef in a frying pan until lightly brown; drain excess oil off of beef.
Add onions and celery.
Cook about 3 minutes in frying pan, then add ground meat and all other ingredients.
Mix well.
Simmer about 30 minutes.

title: creamy dijon dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients; stir until smooth.
Cover; chill.

title: quail in casserole
directions: Rub the birds lightly with salt, then brown in oil.
Remove to heated casserole.
In same oil, saute carrot, onion, green pepper and mushrooms.
Blend in flour; stir in heated broth.
Season to taste with salt.
Pour this sauce and wine over quail.
Cover and bake at 350° about 1 hour.
Serve over rice.

title: creamy cinnamon dip
directions: Blend cream cheese, brown sugar, cinnamon and orange juice in small bowl.
Chill.
Serve with fresh fruit, cookies or small pieces of cake.
May be prepared up to 4 days in advance.
Makes approximately 1 1/4 cups.

title: kolache
directions: Mix flour, salt and milk in large bowl.
Add cooled, melted margarine and beaten eggs.
Dissolve yeast in 1/4 cup lukewarm water.
Add 1 teaspoon sugar to water and add to mixture.
Mix with hands but do not knead.
Add more flour if mixture seems too rich.
Chill overnight and roll out in powdered sugar.
Cut into rounds and make an indentation with your thumb for filling.
Fill with prune or walnut filling and bake at 350° for 1/2 to 3/4 hour.

title: 7 layer dinner
directions: Layer each item as listed in casserole dish.
Cover with foil; bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: summer salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and keep in refrigerator.
When ready to serve, combine 1/2 cup sugar and 1 cup Miracle Whip. Pour over salad and stir well.

title: italian sausage and peppers
directions: Cook the sausage in 4 to 6 tablespoons water until water evaporates.
Continue to cook until sausage is browned all over, turning once.
Remove and set aside.
When the sausage is cool enough to handle, cut it into 1/2-inch slices.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Blend
peanut
butter
and
cream
cheese into powdered sugar until
crumbly.
Place 1/2 of this mixture in the bottom of a baked pie shell.
Mix instant pudding with 1 cup milk and fold in 1/2 of the whipped topping.
Pour into pie shell over peanut butter
crumbs.
Sprinkle
on top the remaining peanut butter crumbs.
Cover
top
of
pie with remainder of whipped topping. Chill and serve. Serves 6.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in 9 x 13 inch pan at 350 degrees until done.

title: fresh apple nut cake
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar and oil.
Sift dry ingredients and add eggs.
Mix.
Add apples, nuts and vanilla.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan 45 minutes at 350°.
Add icing.

title: grandma mcqueen's frito delight
directions: Spread a bed of Fritos.
Pour ground beef sauce over Fritos. Garnish with cheese, lettuce, olives, avocado, tomatoes and onions.

title: creamy pumpkin soup
directions: Cook bacon until crisp; crumble and set aside.
In a saucepan, saute onion and garlic in 1 tablespoon bacon drippings until tender.
In blender or food processor, puree pumpkin, flour, 1/3 cup milk and onion mixture; add to pan.
Add broth, spices, and remaining milk. Bring to boil over medium heat.
Boil for 2 minutes.
Top servings with dollop of sour cream and sprinkle with bacon.
Serve with rolls, fruit, and cheese.
Serves 6-8.

title: rolled lasagna
directions: Mix the cheeses, eggs, seasonings and parsley together.
Cut the partially cooked lasagna in half.
Fill each half with 1 heaping tablespoonful of mixture and roll up.
Put spaghetti sauce on the bottom of a large oiled lasagna dish, then put the filled lasagna with the seam side down in the sauce.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cereal surprise
directions: When you come to the bottom of cereal boxes, put all kinds of different ones together into one of the boxes.
Keep doing this for awhile.
Shake gently or mix with your hands.
Serve in a bowl with milk and sugar as you usually do.

title: easy dessert
directions: In a 9 x 9-inch pan, layer pie filling and sprinkle with cake mix.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, until golden. Serve with whipping cream or ice cream.

title: pet's traditional pumpkin pie
directions: Preheat oven and cookie sheet to 375°.
Remove one pie crust shell from freezer.
Meanwhile, combine filling ingredients in order given.
Place pie shell on preheated cookie sheet near center of oven.
Working quickly, pour filling into pie shell. Bake for 70 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool on wire rack.
Garnish with whipped cream if desired. Makes 1 (9-inch) pie.

title: chocolate kiss cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill one hour.
Take dough and wrap it around a chocolate Kiss.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 375°.

title: hot spiced cider
directions: Bring all ingredients to a boil; simmer for 1/2 hour and be sure to refrigerate leftover cider.

title: banana split cake
directions: Combine cracker crumbs and melted margarine; press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix confectioners sugar, softened margarine, eggs and vanilla together until fluffy; spread over crust.
Spread pineapple over sugar mixture.
Arrange banana slices over pineapple.
Spread whipped topping over bananas.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Garnish with cherries, if desired.

title: peas supreme
directions: Thaw frozen peas.
(Do not cook.)
Add diced ham and cheese. Toss to coat with creamy bacon dressing.
Chill well.
Serve on lettuce.

title: cheese and onion bread
directions: Scald milk.
Add honey, butter and salt.
Allow this to cool to skin temperature.
Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup water (warm).
Add yeast to milk mixture when cool.
Beat egg well.
Then add egg, cheese and onion to milk and beat until relatively smooth.
Add whole wheat flour and beat well.
Gradually add white flour, stirring until dough leaves sides of bowl.
Knead dough about 10 minutes.
Allow to rise once in the bowl and then again in the pans until doubled in size.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for about 40 minutes.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: fiesta beans
directions: Pick over and rinse beans.
Place in large pot and cover with water so that water is about 2 inches over top of beans.
Mince garlic; cut salt pork into 1/4 x 1/4 x 1-inch pieces and add both to beans.
Bring to boil and simmer until tender (2 to 4 hours).

title: baked oatmeal
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Grease an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve with milk.

title: veggie bites
directions: Heat the oven to 450°.
Brush bottom of rectangular pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inches with about 1 tablespoon of the melted margarine.
Beat egg and water with a fork in a shallow dish.
Mix flour and salt in another shallow dish.
Dip about 1/4 of the vegetables into egg mixture.
Remove 1 vegetable piece at a time with a slotted spoon, fork or hands; roll in flour mixture to coat.
Place in pan. Repeat with remaining vegetables.
Pour remaining margarine carefully over each vegetable piece.
Bake, uncovered, turning once, until crisp-tender and golden brown, 10 to 12 minutes. Sprinkle Parmesan cheese.

title: barbecued deer meat
directions: Put whole deer roast into crock-pot.
Sprinkle with salt, sugar and pepper. Add vinegar and cover. Start at 7 or 8 p.m. in the evening; cook all night on low (or auto shift).

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Mix altogether and bake in a 9-inch pie pan at 350° until nice, brown and knife inserted in the middle comes out clean.

title: west indies salad
directions: Mix and let stand in refrigerator 3 to 4 hours.
Serve with crackers.

title: plum pudding
directions: Sift flour; mix in bread crumbs and all dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Add eggs and melted butter.
Mix well.
Add whiskey and Guinness and mix well.
Turn into fire-proof bowl and cover carefully with greased paper.
Place in a pot of boiling water. Water should not come more than half-way up the side of the bowl. Steam for 4 hours.
Check water occasionally and add more boiling water as needed.
Remove damp cover and cover with fresh greased paper and store in dry place.
The pudding improves with age. When ready to eat, heat in microwave or fry with butter in hot pan.
Serve with brandy butter.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream softened butter and sugar until light in a mixer bowl (beat on medium speed of electric mixer until well creamed, about 5 minutes).
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each. Sift flour and baking powder together twice.
Add to cream mixture alternately with milk, beating after each addition.
Add flavoring and continue to beat 5 minutes to make batter light and fluffy.

title: my experiment - cheesecake
directions: Mix and press into pan (use tube or spring-form).

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Blend all ingredients together and beat until cocktail is soft. Bake in a greased and floured pan (13 x 9-inch) in a 300° oven for 45 minutes or until cake pulls away from pan.

title: pita bread
directions: Combine
in
bowl
warm
water,
yeast and sugar.
Stir until yeast
is
thoroughly dissolved.
Let stand until yeast begins to "work".
Sift
into a large bowl the flour, oil and salt.
Beat in 2 cups of warm water using wooden spoon.
When blended, beat in yeast mixture until completely blended.
Turn onto floured board. Knead about 10 to 12 minutes until smooth and not
sticky.
Grease large
bowl.
Put in dough.
Turn to coat.
Cover with damp cloth.
Let rise until double, 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Punch
down. Knead
for
2 to 3 minutes.
Roll into thick sausage,
15 to 16-inches long.
Cut into 15 to 16 equal pieces.
Pat
each
into ball.
Roll
on
floured
board into circles 3/16-inch thick.
Be exact.
Let stand at room temperature for
hour.
Place on wire rack in a 500° oven about 5 minutes.
(Bread
will
start
to rise and brown.) Remove from oven.
Cool on wire rack.

title: king's arms tavern sweet potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish. Cook sweet potatoes in boiling, salted water until done; drain, peel and mash.
Stir in all ingredients except 2 tablespoons of sugar.
Turn the mixture into the greased casserole dish and sprinkle the remaining sugar on top.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: smoked salmon mousse
directions: Combine all ingredients except toast, chopped onion and capers in the container of a food processor or blender.
Blend to a fine puree.
Pour the mixture into a serving dish.
Smooth the top and chill.
Serve on toast or crackers with chopped onion and drained capers on the side.
Yield:
4 cups.

title: mallow fruit dip
directions: Beat all ingredients at medium speed with an electric mixer until well blended.
Serve as a dipping sauce with fresh fruit. Makes about 1 1/2 cups.
Can also substitute lime juice and lime peel for orange juice and orange peel.

title: cherry cheese pie
directions: In medium bowl, beat cheese until light and fluffy.
Add milk and blend thoroughly.
Stir in ReaLemon and vanilla.
Pour into crust.
Chill overnight.
Top with cherry pie filling before serving.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: royal cheese cake
directions: Grease 9-inch spring-form pan with flat bottom with butter and sprinkle graham cracker crumbs.

title: zucchini pineapple bread
directions: Beat eggs, oil, sugar and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients alternately with zucchini and pineapple.

title: corn bread
directions: Grease iron skillet with oil.
Stir mixture with spoon and put into skillet.
Bake at 350° until brown.
Cut like pie wedges.

title: night before casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into a greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch
baking dish.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Uncover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Boil carrots, onion and celery 10 minutes, then add potatoes and cook until almost done.
Drain vegetables and add to sauce. Heat margarine over low heat until melted.
Blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly until mixture is smooth and bubbly.
Remove from heat; stir in broth and milk. Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir 1 minute. Place sauce, vegetables and chicken in casserole (8 x 8-inch).

title: zucchini bars
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour in large greased and floured jelly roll pan and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: no bake peanut butter chip cookies
directions: Melt chips and shortening.
Stir until creamy.
Add cereal and raisins.
Stir until coated.
Drop by teaspoon on wax paper on cookie sheet.
Cover and chill for 1 hour.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Sift first 3 ingredients.
Add to rest of ingredients and mix at high speed for 6 minutes.
Divide into 4 pans that have been greased and floured or use Baker's Joy.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until toothpick inserted comes out clean.

title: casserole chili rellenos(good breakfast dish)
directions: Melt butter in 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Arrange chiles in layer over bottom dish.
Cover with cheese.
Blend eggs, salt, milk and biscuit mix.
Pour over cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until golden brown.

title: biscuit bread
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Melt Crisco in iron skillet.
Mix flour and buttermilk, then melted Crisco.
Pour in skillet.
Bake until brown.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Cook hen in water with salt until tender enough to pull off of the bone (about 2 hours).
Save broth for dressing and dumplings.

title: barbecued meatballs
directions: Mix together hamburger, crumbs and milk. Shape into balls.

title: creamy chicken and mushrooms
directions: In skillet in 1 tablespoon hot margarine, cook chicken 10 minutes or until browned on both sides. Remove.

In remaining 1 tablespoon hot margarine, cook mushrooms, onion and garlic powder until tender and liquid is absorbed. Add remaining ingredients. Heat to boiling. Return chicken to skillet. Cover and cook over low heat 5 minutes or until chicken is no longer pink.
Stir occasionally. Serves 4.
Very good with boiled red potatoes.

title: wargo special(or sloppy joes)
directions: Brown ground beef; pour off fat.
Mix catsup, onion, vinegar, sugar and dry mustard.
Pour over ground beef; simmer.
Cover for 20 minutes.
Stir and serve on hamburger buns.
Serves 4 to 6. Increase as needed for number of people being served.

title: easy yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Cut Crisco into flour.
Add sugar and egg.
Stir in yeast mixture and mix well.
Cover and refrigerate or bake in a greased muffin pan.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: john's famous bread
directions: Mix
all
ingredients well.
Pour mixed batter into pan of heated grease.
Bake at 400° for about 15 minutes or golden brown.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind berries; drain juice from pineapple and use in mixing gelatin.
Let cool.
Add berries, pineapple and nuts.
Place in refrigerator.
May use canned whole berries instead of fresh ground cranberries.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix ingredients together, peanut butter last.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake in 400° oven for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake 30 to 35 minutes longer.
Filling should appear slightly less set in center than around edges.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Spray 15 x 8 x 2-inch glass dish with Pam.
Sprinkle rice into bottom of pan.
Beat together the soups and pour over rice.
Then place chicken pieces into the soup.
Cover with foil and bake at 250° for about 2 hours.
Yield: 4 servings.

title: lo-cal white sauce
directions: Combine first three ingredients in heavy saucepan over medium heat until thick and bubbly.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Can add cheese for cheese sauce if desired.

title: barbecue shrimp
directions: Saute all ingredients except shrimp and let cool.
Pour over shrimp in large casserole and bake at 350° until done.

title: marshmallow creme divinity
directions: Mix Marshmallow Creme, water and vanilla.
Beat at high speed with an electric mixer until stiff peaks form.
This will take several minutes.
Fold in powdered sugar and nuts; drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper.
Let stand 24 hours.

title: steak pot pie
directions: Cook onion in margarine in 2 quart saucepan over medium-high heat until tender.
Blend in flour; cook 1 minute more.
Add broth and steak sauce; cook and stir until mixture thickens and begins to boil.
Stir in steak and vegetables.
Spoon mixture into 8-inch square glass baking dish.
Roll out and cut pastry crust to fit over dish.
Seal crust to edge of dish; brush with egg.
Slit top of crust to vent.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes or until crust is golden brown.
Serve immediately.

title: corn custard
directions: In a deep 1/2-quart casserole dish, heat milk, uncovered, on Full power for 2 1/2 minutes or until scalded in microwave.
Add butter and stir until butter is melted.
Stir in eggs, sugar, salt and pepper; blend well.
Stir in corn and heat, uncovered, on Roast for 16 or 17 minutes.
Set aside 5 minutes to finish cooking.

title: irish potato casserole
directions: Bake potatoes (don't overcook).
Refrigerate until cold.
Peel and grate coarsely.
Mix with other ingredients and turn into casserole dish and bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes.

title: scalloped pineapple
directions: Blend sugar, butter and eggs.
Soak bread cubes in mixture 5 minutes.
Add pineapple and juice; mix.
Pour into greased baking dish and bake, uncovered, 1 hour at 350°.
Serve warm.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Chop broccoli.
Slightly beat the eggs.
Mix all ingredients. Bake in shallow baking dish for 30 minutes at 350°.
Top with cracker crumbs and butter.

title: dip for veggies or crackers
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill overnight.
This is great with veggies or served with crackers.
Your guests will love it!

title: egg casserole
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Scramble eggs adding cheese.
In a 9 x 12 pan, spread out bread and cover with sausage.
Pour eggs over sausage and stir to ensure that everything is coated with egg.
You can store in the refrigerator for next day use or bake right away at 375 degrees for about 30 to 40 minutes or until the eggs are no longer liquid and top is slightly brown.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Dissolve salt, sugar and cold water.
Pour melted Crisco in cold water mixture.
Add yeast, water, eggs and flour together. Cover with wax paper; place in refrigerator overnight.
Roll out and cut.
Dip biscuits into melted butter.
Place in pan.
Let rise one hour.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: beef steak picado
directions: Heat oil; brown meat in a large pan or pot.
Add onions; stir for a few minutes and then add bell peppers, tomatoes, Worcestershire sauce, salt and garlic powder.
Add enough water to cover the meat, etc.
Bring to a boil; then lower flame and simmer for 30 to 40 minutes or until meat is tender.

title: barbecue hash
directions: Cook stew beef in water. Take meat out of pot and set aside 2 cups onions, mustard and lemon juice. Cook for 20 minutes.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In 13 x 9-inch baking pan, melt margarine in oven. Sprinkle crumbs over margarine. Pour sweetened condensed milk evenly over crumbs. Top with remaining ingredients. Press down. Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until lightly browned. Cool. Chill, if desired. Cut into bars. Store, loosely covered, at room temperature.

title: breakfast scramble
directions: Brown meat, cut crust off bread and line into a 9 x 13 pan. Cut meat into small pieces, spread on bread, mix all ingredients except cheese and pour over bread.
Keep in overnight- Bake 325 degrees for 35- 45 minutes - add grated cheese and bake 10 more minutes.

title: squash patties
directions: Beat egg in squash.
Add other ingredients.
Drop by tablespoon in hot oil.
Flatten to 1/4-inch thickness.
Cook to golden brown.
Turn to brown other side.
Makes about 14 patties. Drain on paper towel.

title: chocolate peanut spiders
directions: Melt chocolate chips and peanut butter chips in top of a double boiler.
When melted, add peanuts and noodles.
Stir until well coated.
Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper.
Let set until hardened.
Yields 2 1/2 dozen.

title: 5 cup casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
(Do not dilute soups.)
Bake in casserole dish for 25 minutes at 350°.

title: gingerbread cookies
directions: Stir together and chill at least 3 hours.
Roll out flat (1/4 inch) thick and cut into shapes.
Bake at 375° for 5 to 6 minutes.

title: cream cheese roll up
directions: Lay out slice of bologna.
Spread with cream cheese and roll. Garnish plate with greens and arrange bologna on it.

title: quick corn and zucchini sauté
directions: In a large skillet, saute peppers and zucchini in oil until crisp-tender, about 5 minutes.
Add corn, garlic salt and Italian seasoning.
Cook until thoroughly heated.

title: chinese hamburger casserole
directions: Brown beef until crumbly.
Add vegetables.
Add soups.
Stir in uncooked rice, soy sauce and pepper.
Turn into large, lightly greased casserole dish.
Cover and bake for 1 hour at 350°. Remove cover; spread noodles on top.
Bake 10 minutes longer.

title: apricot divine chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cover bottom of shallow baking pan with oil.

Shake chicken in bag with flour and salt until coated. Place chicken in single layer in baking pan and bake 25 minutes. Combine apricot preserves, mustard and yogurt (or sour cream). Spread apricot mixture on chicken and bake for 30 minutes more or until done.

title: lazy man's cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in dish.
Mix sugar, flour and milk in bowl (separately).
Then pour batter over butter; do not stir.
Spoon peach pie filling over batter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until brown.

title: orange chicken
directions: Season chicken pieces with salt, garlic powder, paprika, pepper, tarragon and thyme.
Place in a shallow baking pan, skin side down.

title: squash pie
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch together.
Add all ingredients in order given.
Bake 15 minutes at 425° and bake additional 35 to 40 minutes, or until knife inserted comes out clean.

title: mostaccioli broccoli bake
directions: Cook noodles, drain and rinse with cold water.
In medium saucepan, melt margarine.
Stir in flour until blended.
Add milk. Cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Stir in Parmesan cheese, salt, garlic powder, thyme and nutmeg.
Remove from heat. In a large bowl, combine broccoli, cheese sauce and noodles.
Spoon into a 12 x 9-inch baking dish; sprinkle Swiss cheese on top.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Yields 12 servings.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Mix cocoa and water in a saucepan.
Add margarine.
Bring mixture to a boil; cool slightly.
Sift together flour, baking soda and cinnamon.
Blend together (do not beat) sugar and eggs in a large mixing bowl.
Blend in cocoa mixture.
Add dry ingredients alternately with buttermilk, stirring after each addition, until well blended.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour in greased jelly roll pan. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Frost when cooled with Chocolate Icing.

title: broccoli lasagna rolls
directions: To make sauce:
Heat olive oil in medium-sized pan.
Add green peppers, parsley, spices and bay leaf.
Saute over very low heat, being careful not to burn spices.
Add tomato sauce and water. Simmer 2 to 3 hours.
Remove bay leaf.
About 1/2 hour before sauce will be finished, cook lasagna noodles according to package directions in unsalted water.
Set aside.

title: hot lips
directions: Put steaks in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with onions and green pepper.
Pour barbecue sauce on top.
Bake, covered, at 325° for 1 hour.

title: chili cheese and chips
directions: Brown beef and drain grease.
Stir in tomatoes, tomato paste, chili powder and onion.
Cover and simmer for 12 minutes.
Stir in cheese until melted.
Place chips on plate.
Pour beef mixture on top.
Serves 5.

title: dolly's meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together with hands and put in a baking dish.
Bake at 400° for about 1 hour or until desired doneness. After baking 45 minutes, pour extra ketchup on top and continue to bake.

title: pineapple torte
directions: Use 9 x 9-inch pan.
Mix together vanilla cookie crumbs, and melted butter; pat in bottom of pan.
Cream 1/4 cup butter and powdered sugar.
Add eggs and beat together until smooth.
Spread over cookie crust.
Drain pineapple well and spread over mixture in pan.
Whip whipping cream stiff and spread over.
Nut meats and extra crumbs can be spread over top.
Refrigerate 4 hours or more.

title: apple spice sundae
directions: Melt butter or margarine in saucepan.
Stir in brown sugar, cinnamon and pie filling.
Bring to a boil.
Remove from heat. Stir in nuts.
Serve warm over ice cream.

title: lime punch
directions: Prepare lemonade according to directions.
Dissolve jello in hot pineapple juice.
Cool before pouring into punch bowl.
Add soda and softened scoops of sherbet and lemonade.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Fry hamburger, green pepper, mushrooms and garlic in large pan. Add spaghetti mix, tomatoes and tomato sauce, oregano and basil. Add enough oregano and basil to cover the pan twice.
Simmer 30 minutes or more.

title: stuffed chicken breast
directions: Prepare stuffing by directions on box.
Cut chicken breasts in half, pound to desired thickness and lay a slice of Provolone cheese on top of breasts.
Place a large spoonful of stuffing on top of cheese.
Then roll the chicken breasts and secure with a toothpick.
Place in an 8 x 8-inch pan with chicken breasts in a row.
Add 1/2 cup milk to soup.
Then pour over chicken and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: e. g. cheese log
directions: Combine Cheddar cheese and softened cream cheese, mixing on medium speed on electric mixer until well blended.
Add chopped beef, green onion and Worcestershire sauce.
Mix well.
Chill several hours or overnight.
Shape mixture into 7-inch log.
Wrap 16 x 1-inch foil strips around log.
Roll in chopped parsley. Remove foil.
Serve with crackers or party rye bread.

title: yankee dish
directions: Cook macaroni until tender.
Drain in colander and rinse with cold water.
Mix all together in large bowl.
Chill and serve with crackers or rolls.

title: marinated vegetable-rice salad
directions: Drain all canned vegetables.
Combine all vegetables and rice in a large container.
In a saucepan, combine water, oil, vinegar, sugar and salt.
Heat almost to boiling.
Allow to cool slightly and pour over vegetables.
Cover and refrigerate several hours or overnight.

title: lemon squares
directions: Crust:
Blend butter, salt, 2 cups flour and confectioners sugar.
Pat into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: lemon chiffon bread
directions: Mix at low speed on mixer. Grease and flour 2 (8 x 4-inch) loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or until cake tester comes out clean.

title: oreo ice cream dessert
directions: Save 1 cup cookies for topping.
Mix together; place in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Freeze for 24 hours.
Cut in squares to serve.

title: easter bunny cake
directions: Cream together butter, cream cheese and sugar until fluffy. Add milk and one egg at a time; beat well.
Add flour, one cup at a time.
Add vanilla.
Put into well-greased form pan and bake 1 hour.

title: pickled beets
directions: Drain juice from 1 can sliced beets.
Add water to make 1 cup. Pour in saucepan.
Add 1/2 cup vinegar, 1 cup sugar and 1 stick cinnamon; bring to a boil.
Pour over beets.
Marinate several hours or overnight in refrigerator.

title: rice krispies cookies
directions: Bring sugar and syrup to a good boil.
Remove from heat and mix in peanut butter until smooth.
Pour Rice Krispies into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add sugar, syrup and peanut butter.
Mix and spread. Cool and cut into squares.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Saute onion in oleo in a large skillet.
Add frozen broccoli and cook until tender.
Add soup and Cheez Whiz and heat until bubbly.
Add rice and pour into a buttered casserole dish and bake at 375° until it bubbles, about 20 to 25 minutes.

title: pizza mac
directions: Spread cooked macaroni on pizza pan.
In saucepan, cook about 1 pound of ground beef, onion, water, tomato paste, garlic, green pepper, salt, pepper, Worcestershire sauce
and oregano; cook until done.
Pour over macaroni.
Sprinkle Mozzarella over top. Bake at 350° until cheese is hot and melted.
Serve with garlic bread and butter.

title: quick coffee cake
directions: Cut margarine into flour, baking powder, sugar and salt.
Add beaten egg with enough milk to make 2/3 cup.
Pour into greased pie tin.
Sprinkle with brown sugar and cinnamon.
Dot with butter and sprinkle on pecans.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: sweet potato pone
directions: Melt butter in shallow 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour into dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 8.
Good with turkey or ham!

title: hamburger-bean casserole
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Cook and stir beef and onion until brown. Stir in salt, pepper, beans and soup.
Heat to boiling.
Pour into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Keep hot in oven.
Stir flour and water to dough.
Knead 5 times.
Roll dough to fit casserole.
Bake 15 minutes.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: pecan puffs
directions: Cream together the butter, sugar and vanilla.
Stir in pecans and flour.
Form into 1-inch balls.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.
Remove from pan and roll in powdered sugar while hot.
Cool and roll again in powdered sugar.

title: strawberry twinkie delight
directions: Slice Twinkies and lay in casserole dish, cream side up.
Mix pudding by directions.
After mixing pudding, add Cool Whip and pour over Twinkies.
Mix berries and jello; pour over top.
Let chill.

title: salted pecan cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add egg and vanilla. Combine dry ingredients and add gradually to butter and sugar mixture; add oatmeal.
Mix well and add pecans.
Drop by teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Sprinkle lightly with salt.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: beet salad
directions: Layer beets at bottom of a clear bowl.
Layer sauce on top (mixed mayo and salad cream).
Sprinkle with walnuts.
Layer shredded carrots mixed with lemon.
Layer sauce on top (mayo and salad cream).
Sprinkle with walnuts again.
Chill in fridge at least 1 hour and then serve.

title: bears in the orchard
directions: In a large Dutch oven, bring applesauce to bubbling boil.
Mix gingerbread, using 1/2 recommended liquid.
Pour mix over hot applesauce.
Cover and cook 7 to 8 minutes until gingerbread is done.

title: mary's roasted peppers
directions: Place washed peppers on a baking sheet in oven on the top rung. Broil peppers at 500°.
As they char, keep turning until almost completely black.
Remove from oven and let cool.
Remove core and seeds under running water (the outer skin will come off easily). Slice each pepper into 6 pieces.
Add all other ingredients and let marinate at least 2 hours.

title: baby plum cake
directions: Sift dry
ingredients
together
in a mixing bowl.
Add oil, then eggs,	one
at
a
time,
and	beat
until batter is creamy. Then add plums, vanilla and nuts.
Pour in a tube pan or Bundt pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Ice with caramel frosting.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Mix all together and pour in pan.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes in oven at 400°.

title: 7-up salad
directions: Mix Jell-O and boiling water until Jell-O is dissolved.
Add 7-Up.
Let set until thickened.
Add crushed pineapple, cream cheese (whipped) and pecans.
Mix well.
Let stand until solid.

title: bacon-cheese soup
directions: Simmer all together several hours.

title: cutout christmas cookies
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Combine flour, cinnamon, baking powder, salt, cloves and nutmeg.
Gradually add to creamed mixture; mix well.
Chill for at least 1 hour.
On a lightly floured surface, roll dough, a portion at a time, to 1/8-inch thickness.
Cut into desired shapes.
Place on ungreased baking sheets.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 14 minutes, or until edges begin to brown.
Carefully brush with egg white; sprinkle with colored sugar.
Return to the oven for 3 to 5 minutes, or until lightly browned.
Yields about 6 dozen 2-inch cookies.

title: fried soft-shell crab
directions: Sprinkle soft-shell crabs with salt.
Roll in a mixture of fine saltine cracker crumbs, and flour.
Dip in a mixture of slightly beaten egg and milk; roll in crumbs and flour mixture again.
Heat salad oil in a skillet.
Fry crabs in hot fat 3 to 5 minutes on each side, depending on size of crabs.
Drain.
Serve with lemon wedges.

title: somebody's casserole potatoes
directions: Blend all ingredients together, put cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours in a baking dish, sprayed with Pam.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Cream together the first 5 ingredients.
Add flour and baking soda.
Add the chopped rhubarb.
