Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: pizza di ricotta(ricotta cake)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients together.
Bake for one hour in an 8 or 9-inch square pan.
"Italy!"

title: mom's baked beans
directions: Soak enough beans overnight to make 3 cups. Combine all the ingredients in a crock-pot, bean pot or suitable dish with cover for oven. (If too dry during cooking, add more tomatoes or tomato juice.) Bake in oven at 300° or slow cook for 12 1/2 to 13 hours.

title: fresh strawberry pie(club member: nicholas thompson)
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch, then add hot water. Cook until thick. Add jello; cool, then add strawberries. Pour into baked pie shell and top with Cool Whip.

title: sarah brown's squash pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour, eggs and margarine.
Add flavoring.
Add squash.
Mix well.
Pour in prepared pie shell.
Cook for 10 minutes at 400°, then 350° for 1 hour.
Tastes like coconut pie.

title: tortellini soup
directions: Combine all ingredients and simmer for 45 minutes.
If using regular pasta, add 10 minutes before soup is finished.

title: lemon chicken saute
directions: Roll chicken in flour to coat.
Spray skillet with nonstick cooking spray.
Add butter; melt.
Add chicken breasts.
Cook over medium heat until chicken is lightly browned (5 to 7 minutes). Turn chicken over; continue cooking until lightly browned.
Remove chicken; set aside.
Stir in teriyaki sauce, lemon juice, garlic and sugar.
Return chicken to pan.
Simmer 3 minutes.
Turn chicken over; continue cooking until fork-tender (2 to 3 minutes). Serve over rice.

title: vegetable stir-fry
directions: In blender, process garlic with vinegar until finely chopped. Add soy sauce, catsup, bouillon and spice.
Blend smooth.
Heat oil in wok or large skillet over high heat.
Stir-fry carrots 2 minutes.
Add onions and fry 1 minute.
Add asparagus, stir and add 1 tablespoon water.
Cover lightly and steam 5 minutes.
Add squash, celery and remaining water.
Cover and steam 5 minutes or until tender-crisp.
Stir in tomato and garlic sauce.
Cover and cook 1 minute.

title: fried chicken steak
directions: Saturate chicken cutlets in egg wash (eggs and milk).
Dip cutlets into seasoned flour; coat the chicken thoroughly in flour. Deep fry chicken in hot oil until golden brown.
Top with brown gravy and mashed potatoes.
Serve vegetables and corn bread.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients except vanilla and pecans in saucepan. Cook and stir over medium heat until well mixed and butter is melted.
Remove from heat and add nuts and vanilla.
Pour into an uncooked pie shell and bake for 10 minutes at 375° and 40 minutes at 350°.

title: cheese ortega omelet
directions: Toss cheese and pepper in buttered 9 x 13-inch Pyrex baking dish.
Pour over this mixture large can of evaporated milk, mixed with beaten eggs and flour.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes.

title: herb butter-spread bread
directions: With serrated edge knife, cut off top, side and end crusts of bread.
Do not cut away bottom crust.
Cut bread, leaving bottom attached, in half lengthwise and into 3/4-inch pieces crosswise. Cream butter.
Add salt and Worcestershire.
Place thyme and marjoram leaves in palm of hand; crush lightly to release flavoring oils.
Add herbs to butter; mix well.
Spread all cut surfaces of bread inside and out with butter.
Place bread on rimmed baking sheet.
(The butter will run as it heats.)
Bake, uncovered, in a 325° oven for about 30 minutes, or until crisp. Serve hot.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: double baked sweet potatoes
directions: Cut each potato in half lengthwise.
Scoop out center, leaving shell.
Mash potatoes.
Add margarine, apple juice, sugar and ginger and beat until fluffy.
Spoon into potato shells.
Top with Cocomallow Topping.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: elephant soup
directions: In a very large soup pot, simmer the elephant in water for two days.
Add the vegetables and simmer for one more day.
Add the salt and pepper.
The rabbit is optional because not everyone likes a hare in their soup.
Just for fun!

title: calico beans
directions: Cook
hamburger, bacon and onions; drain.
Mix together ketchup, brown
and
white
sugars, vinegar, salt and dry mustard. Drain
beans and add to mixture.
Bake 40 to 60 minutes at 350° or in crock-pot.
Best when sits in refrigerator for a few hours before cooking.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: easy apple crisp
directions: Layer sliced apples in baking dish.
Add water and spices. Mix flour, sugar and margarine until mixture is crumbly.
Top apples with mixture.
Bake at 325° until brown and apples are tender.

title: hamburger-zucchini casserole
directions: Brown the ground beef.
Cut zucchini into 3/4-inch slices, boil until tender and drain.
Layer in casserole dish the zucchini, ground beef, sauce, shredded Mozzarella cheese and Parmesan cheese (sprinkled on top).
May repeat layers.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour. Serves 4 to 6.

title: parmesan dressing
directions: Make Parmesan Dressing early in the day.
In a bowl or covered jar, combine all ingredients.
Stir with fork or shake until well blended.
Refrigerate until serving time.
Makes 1 cup.

title: pepperidge farm chicken casserole
directions: Put chicken in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place 1 slice of cheese on top of each piece of chicken.
Mix soup and water; pour over chicken.
Sprinkle dressing mix on top.
Drizzle melted margarine over top.
Bake at 325° for 2 hours.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cut up a medium size Irish potato. Cook until tender. Drain; mash while hot. Add confectioners sugar until stiff enough to roll (you will need 2 to 3 boxes) on sugared board. Spread with peanut butter and roll like a jelly roll. When cool, slice and serve.

title: rock-pop trail mix
directions: Microwave the popcorn using package directions. Combine the popped popcorn, dried fruit, raisins, and peanuts in a large bowl and mix well. Mix the confectioners' sugar and cinnamon in
a small bowl. Sprinkle over the popcorn mixture and stir to coat. Makes 12 cups.

title: spinach lasagna(heart healthy)
directions: Wash, dry and chop fresh spinach or squeeze thawed spinach dry. Saute onion and garlic in stock. Add tomato sauce and seasonings. Simmer 20 to 30 minutes. Mix cottage cheese and yogurt. Cook lasagna noodles according to package directions; drain well. Spread part of sauce in a shallow 9-inch baking pan. Add layers of noodles, spinach, cottage cheese mixture and Mozzarella. Repeat layers ending with Mozzarella. Bake in 350° oven 40 to 50 minutes. Makes about 6 servings.

title: pink salad
directions: Mix together and cool in refrigerator 10 to 15 minutes, then add Cool Whip.
Mix well.
Add marshmallows and mix.

title: welcome recipe
directions: Heat enthusiasm and tolerance, but do not boil.
Beat handshakes and friendliness, then smiles.
Stir all together until personality is formed.
This recipe is appropriate for any occasion.

title: lasagne
directions: Combine everything except the sauce and noodles.
Heat oil in Dutch oven and brown meat.
Add sauce and simmer 30 minutes.

title: frozen strawberry salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour in cupcake cups and freeze.
When ready to use, peel off paper and place on salad dish lined with lettuce or on each person's individual plate.

title: cheesecake
directions: Mix together the graham cracker crumbs, melted butter and 1/3 cup sugar.
Grease a spring-form pan.
Line the sides and the bottom with the graham cracker crust mixture, then refrigerate.

title: pizza bread
directions: Toast bread lightly.
Sprinkle with oregano, garlic and oil. Spread toast with tomato paste.
Top with cheese.
Place pizza under hot grill (broiler) until the cheese is bubbly and golden. Serve immediately with a little extra oregano sprinkled on top, if desired.

title: beef oriental
directions: Brown meat and onions. Mix all other ingredients in dish and bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: brownies
directions: Melt butter in a saucepan.
Remove from heat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well until blended and smooth.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: better than tom selleck cake
directions: Prepare box of German chocolate cake mix in 9 x 13-inch pan as directed.
While hot, poke holes in cake and pour mixture of Eagle Brand milk and butterscotch ice cream topping over cake.
Let cool and top with Cool Whip and crushed Heath candy bar.

title: fettucine alfredo
directions: Combine water, salt and oil in a medium saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Gradually add noodles, maintaining a boil.
Reduce heat to slow boil.
Cook, uncovered, 8 to 10 minutes, stirring once, until tender.
Drain in a strainer or colander.
Return noodles to saucepan, or put in a warm chafing dish or electric skillet to finish at table.
Fold and stir until melted.
Pour in whipping cream.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Fold and stir until cream is partially absorbed and cheese is melted.
Just before serving, add pepper and nutmeg, if desired.
Makes two servings.

title: easy cinnamon rolls
directions: Mix warm water and dry yeast.
When yeast is dissolved, add yellow cake mix.
Mix well and add flour.
Place a cover over bowl and let rise until double in bulk.

title: tortellini with four cheeses, oven-dried tomatoes and sage
directions: Preheat saute pan.
Add olive oil, shallots and garlic and saute for approximately 1 to 2 minutes or until translucent. Deglaze with white wine.
Reduce by half.
Add heavy cream; reduce by half.
Place cooked tortellini in strainer.
Place in lightly salted, simmering water for approximately 1/2 minute or until pasta is heated throughout.
Strain and place into pan with cream reduction.
Add all 4 cheeses and mix
thoroughly.
Place on plate with warmed Oven-Dried Tomatoes.
Garnish with chopped sage, shaved Reggiano cheese and fresh ground black pepper.

title: old fashioned chess pie
directions: Cream sugar and margarine together.
Beat in eggs, one at a time and add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake at 325° for 45 to 60 minutes or until pie tests done.
Yields 1 (9-inch) pie.

title: yankee noodle bake
directions: Brown frankfurters and onion in margarine until onion is tender.
Combine with noodles, soup, water and mustard in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Top with crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni.
Drain and cool.
Remove seeds and chop up pepper.
Add onions and celery and mix with macaroni.
Add remaining ingredients and chill overnight.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all items above in a large mixing bowl.
Chill.
To serve, place in smaller bowls around or on serving trays for vegetable trays.
Serves 400.

title: sandcastles are forever
directions: Mix together in old pan and cook 5 to 10 minutes over medium heat, stirring constantly until very thick and holds shape.
Put on plate and cover with damp cloth until cool enough to handle. Knead well.
Store tightly covered.
Use like clay.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Simmer chicken breasts in 1 quart water, 1 cup sherry, 1 teaspoon salt, 1/4 teaspoon pepper, 2 sliced green onions and tops for 30 minutes or until tender. Cut into chunks. Cook rice mix as directed, using broth from chicken instead of water. Saute sliced mushrooms and remaining green onions and tops (sliced) in 3 tablespoons margarine. Combine chicken chunks, rice mix, water chestnuts, sauteed mushrooms and green onions with mushroom soup and sour cream. Pour into 9 x 13 glass pan (sprayed with Pam). Cover with foil and bake for 30 minutes at 350°. Uncover. Top with grated cheese and bake for an additional 10 to 15 minutes.

title: bran rolls
directions: Mix shortening, boiling water, sugar, All-Bran and salt, stirring until shortening is melted.
Let stand until mixture is lukewarm.
Add eggs and yeast.
Beat in flour, 3 cups at a time. Cover bowl and place in icebox.
Form into cloverleaf rolls and let rise 2 hours before baking.
Bake in hot oven, about 20 minutes.

title: coconut drop cookies
directions: Bake at 350° for about 8 minutes or until golden brown.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Layer ingredients in an electric skillet.
Bake at 250° for about 30 to 40 minutes.
About 15 minutes before serving, put Velveeta cheese on top.

title: meatball stroganoff
directions: Combine beef, bread crumbs, onion, egg and salt and pepper to taste.
Shape into small meatballs.
Brown in skillet; pour off fat.
Add soup, sour cream and water.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes, stirring often.
Serve over hot egg noodles.

title: apple crumb pie
directions: Peel apples and cut into 8ths and arrange in unbaked pastry shell. Sprinkle with 1/2 c. sugar mixed with cinnamon. Sift remaining

sugar with flour. Cut butter in sugar and flour mix until it looks crumbly. Sprinkle over apples. Bake 450 degrees for 10 minutes, reduce heat to 350 degrees and bake for 30 minutes or until apples are tender.

title: linguini salad
directions: Boil noodles and drain.
Cut up the tomatoes and cucumbers and add vegetables and juice to a bowl.
Add onions.
Add 1/2 jar of Salad Supreme and 1/2 jar of salad dressing and mix well.
Add noodles.
then add 1/2 jar of Salad Supreme and 1/2 jar of salad dressing. Mix well.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and let it set overnight.

title: rice krispies cookies
directions: Cream butter, margarine and sugar.
Add nuts and flour.
Fold in Rice Krispies.
Roll into small balls.
Flatten with a fork. Bake 15 to 20 minutes in a 325° oven.

title: hasselback potatoes
directions: Slice the potatoes 1/8-inch intervals, 3/4 through (like a fan).
Place each potato on foil and drizzle with butter. Sprinkle with salt, onion salt and paprika.
Seal foil.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Combine cheese and bread crumbs.
Sprinkle and bake 15 minutes more with foil open.

title: tuna oven sandwiches
directions: Combine tuna, onions, celery, Mozzarella cheese, parsley flakes, salt, pepper and mayonnaise in bowl.
Mix well.
Separate hamburger buns.
Spread cut sides with margarine.
Spread with tuna mixture; place on a baking sheet.
Broil until golden.

title: oreo delight
directions: Crush 3/4 of the Oreo cookies and cover bottom of 9 x 13 pan. Melt butter to pour over cookies. Mix 2/3 of Cool Whip with the cream cheese. Layer over cookies. Mix pudding according to directions and pour over cream cheese mixture. Put remaining Cool Whip on top of pudding. Crush remaining cookies and put on top.

title: surprise pumpkin bread
directions: Mix well pumpkin, sugar, oil and eggs.
Add flour, soda, baking powder, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Mix well; stir in nuts and pie filling.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan or large loaf pan.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes or until done, loaf pan will take a longer baking period.

title: old-fashioned chicken dumplings
directions: Rub shortening into a part of the flour.
Use milk to make a stiff dough (3/4 cup is sufficient).
Shape into dumplings by rolling very thin and cut as desired or drop from spoon into chicken broth.
If dropped, do not make dough quite so stiff. Cook for about 12 to 15 minutes slowly.
Do not stir or remove top boiler until ready to serve.

title: popcorn nut brittle
directions: Combine sugar, water, syrup and salt in saucepan.
Stir until sugar is completely dissolved.
Cook rapidly until small amount in cup of cold water forms a hard ball (260°).
Add molasses and butter.
Cook slowly until a small amount forms a hard ball and cracks when you bite and doesn't stick to your teeth (275°; lower altitude 280°).

Pour this over a dishpan sprayed with Pam and half full of buttered popcorn with Planters nuts sprinkled on top. Mix cooked syrup with popcorn and nuts with large wooden spoon. Divide and place on 3 buttered cookie sheets.
Pound down flat and cool.
Store in airtight containers.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Lay 10 chicken breasts in the bottom of a pan.
Top each one with a piece of Swiss cheese.
In a small mixing bowl, mix the salad dressing, Parmesan cheese and oregano.
Spoon that mixture over each piece of chicken (spread over the whole piece).
Cover the chicken with spaghetti sauce.
Cover with foil.
Bake in the oven at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Makes 10 servings.

title: brownie frosting
directions: Cream
butter,	cocoa,	corn syrup and vanilla in small mixer bowl.
Add	powdered
sugar and milk.
Beat to spreading consistency.
Makes about 1 cup of frosting.

title: low-cal green beans
directions: Dissolve bouillon cube in 1/2 cup boiling water in saucepan. Add beans; heat to boiling point.
Cover, simmer for 5 minutes or until tender.
Yields 6 servings at 25 calories per serving.

title: rice dressing
directions: Pour 1/2 cup cooking oil over the first 5 ingredients; simmer until tender.

title: granola bars
directions: Peanuts,
raisins
and
sunflower seeds can be replaced with 3 cups of other
dry
ingredients like: wheat germ, coconut, chopped dates, apricots, walnuts and more oats.

title: salpicon
directions: Cook meat with spices and 3 cups of water for about 2 to 3 hours or until tender; let meat cool.
Cut up in small pieces. Cut up remaining vegetables except lettuce and peppers.
Lay lettuce on bottom of bowl.

title: cinnamon balls
directions: Open biscuits carefully.
Try not to jump when it pops open. Cut biscuits into fourths.
Heat butter in a square or round pan in the oven.
Temperature is on the biscuit can; read it before you tear it off.
Put biscuits in the pan and sprinkle with the cinnamon stuff.
Cook until done, about 10 minutes.
Serve with a big glass of cold milk.

title: lean sweet and sour cabbage borscht
directions: Heat all ingredients in a soup pot until it boils.
Reduce heat and simmer slowly, covered, for 1 hour.

title: brown sugar cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients by hand and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: cherry cheese pie
directions: In a large bowl, beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in sweetened condensed milk until smooth.
Stir in ReaLemon juice and vanilla.
Pour into prepared crust.
Chill 3 hours or until set. Top with can of cherry pie filling.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except cheese.
Put 1/2 batter in greased skillet.
Put a layer of cheese on top, then put remaining batter on top of cheese.
Bake at 450° until done.

title: lenten golubtzi
directions: Cook rice until thick.
Fry garlic, peppers, 1 onion (minced), 1 celery stalk (chopped finely) and sliced mushrooms in oil.
Add to rice and mix well; add seasoning and tomatoes, but save the liquid.
Boil cabbage until leaves can be separated without breaking.
Cut raised center vein of each leaf so it will be no thicker than most of leaf.
Place about 2 tablespoons of filling in stem end of leaf; roll once, then fold in sides of leaf and continue to roll rest of way.
Use all the larger leaves and save the too-small ones to line bottom of roaster.

Place Golubtzi in layers, then add the can of tomato soup, the liquid from the canned tomatoes and the other onion, minced, as well as the other 2 stalks of celery, chopped finely; salt and pepper to taste.
Bake for 2 hours in a covered roaster in a moderate oven, about 350°.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in a pan in oven at 400°.
Stir flour and sugar together.
Add milk and stir until well mixed.
Pour over butter. Pour peaches on top.
Bake 30 minutes at 400°.
Top with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: congealed lime salad
directions: Melt marshmallows in hot Jell-O, pulling marshmallows apart. Let cool until it thickens.
Add pineapple, nuts and whipped cream.
Place in refrigerator and let cool.

title: corn casserole
directions: Drain whole kernel corn.
(Mix in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.) Pour in baking dish.
Mix in can of cream-style corn, melted butter, sour cream, eggs and muffin mix.
Stir until all ingredients are mixed together well.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: fiesta dish
directions: Saute onion and garlic in salad oil.
Add hamburger meat. Cook until brown.
Add tomatoes, beans, chili, salt and pepper. Heat to boiling.
Cover bottom of a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan with tortillas, then sauce, etc., until mixture is used.
Cover top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sad cake
directions: Beat the eggs while butter is softening.
Mix together with remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch buttered sheet cake pan.
Bake at 350°
for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: fried chicken
directions: Mix dry ingredients in a large Ziploc bag.
Pour milk into bowl.
Cover chicken pieces in milk, then add several pieces to Ziploc bag and seal.
Shake bag to cover chicken completely. Repeat until all chicken is covered.

title: punch
directions: Mix, refrigerate and let set overnight.
Before serving, add in the ginger ale.

title: acadiana smothered okra
directions: Make sure there is enough oil to cover the bottom of a medium saucepan.
Heat oil, adding okra sliced without ends.
Add onion, tomato, vinegar, salt and pepper.
Cook about 45 minutes or until okra is no longer slimy.
Stir often to keep from sticking.

title: peach salad
directions: Heat pineapple to boiling.
Stir in Jell-O.
Let cool.
Add buttermilk.
Fold in Cool Whip and nuts.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: swedish oatmeal cookie
directions: Sift together flour, soda and salt; set aside.
Cream sugar, shortening and brown sugar.
Blend in egg and vanilla; mix well. Add flour mixture and mix.
Add oatmeal and mix well.
Drop on cookie sheet in mounds.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.
Remove from oven and place 1/2 tsp.
topping in center of each cookie; pressing lightly.
Bake for another 6-8 minutes until cookie is golden brown.
Cool 1 minute before removing from cookie sheet.

title: punch anytime
directions: Mix and pour into milk jug (1 gallon).
Finish filling with water.
Freeze.
Thaw 6 to 8 hours before serving.
Mix ginger ale with this mixture before serving.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Trim fat from pork chops.
Layer rice and mushroom soup. Sprinkle soup flakes.
Repeat.
Place pork chops on top.
Cook, uncovered, 45 minutes at 400°.

title: cherry chip cream cheese cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Cream butter and cheese until light and fluffy.
Beat in egg, vanilla and half of the cake mix (dry) until smooth.
Stir in remaining cake mix and the coconut.
tags: Betty Crocker cherry chip cake mix

title: sweet potato soup
directions: Melt butter in a medium saucepan over medium-low heat.
Stir in onion; cook 1 minute.
Stir in celery and potatoes; cook 5 minutes. Add the broth and the V-8 juice; cook, uncovered, until tender, about 25 minutes.
Cool.
Place the soup in batches in the container of a blender or food processor.
Blend until smooth. Pour the soup into a medium saucepan; stir in cream, bourbon, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Heat over low heat until warmed through.
Do not boil.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Serve hot, chill or serve cold.
Serves 4.

title: tomato pepper relish
directions: Chop tomatoes, sweet bell peppers and the onion in a small bowl.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over the vegetables. Place in refrigerator and chill.
Serve with roast beef and lamb.

title: chicken potato casserole
directions: Add butter, flour, salt and pepper to diluted soup and potatoes into greased casserole dish.
Spread undiluted soup on top.
Cook at 350° for 45 minutes, covered.
Sprinkle crushed on top and continue baking, uncovered, for 30 minutes longer.

title: stuffed pork roast
directions: Mix seasoning from onions to black pepper.
Wash roast and cut several 2-inch slits at an angle as deep as possible without going all the way through the meat.
Stuff as much seasoning as possible into each slit.
Pour remaining seasoning over roast.
Place in roasting pan.
Add 1 cup water.
Cover and bake 1 hour at 375°. Add 1/2 can soup and gravy mix.
Stir every 5 minutes until well blended.
Bake another 30 minutes to 1 hour until done.

title: hot vinaigrette vegetable
directions: In 2-quart saucepan, bring 1 quart water to a boil.
Add broccoli and cauliflower and cook, stirring once for 30 seconds to 1 minute.
Drain vegetables and transfer to serving platter.
Add onions, tomatoes and bell peppers and set aside.

title: casserole treat
directions: Use any amount of ground chuck and cream potatoes.
Brown ground beef in frypan.
Spread meat in a casserole.
Spread creamed potatoes over top.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Brown in oven.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Simmer tomato, green pepper, onion, mushrooms and zucchini until tender. In a casserole dish layer stuffing and vegetables. Top with cheese. Bake in preheated 350 oven for 1/2 hour.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix butter and sugar.
Add flour and eggs.
Beat well.
Stir in buttermilk, vanilla and nutmeg.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix sugar, milk and water.
Cook to soft-ball stage.
Remove from heat and stir in peanut butter, butter and vanilla.
Beat until shiny.
Pour onto buttered plate or pan.
Cool.
Cut into squares.

title: chiles rellenos casserole
directions: Brown ground beef
and
onions in skillet; drain excess fat. Season with
teaspoon salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper. Place half of chiles
in
x
6-inch
dish.
Sprinkle
with cheese. Spread
meat
layer; arrange remaining chiles on top. Combine milk,
flour,
eggs
and
Tabasco sauce and beat well. Pour mixture over
meat and chiles.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or
until
knife
inserted
in center comes out clean. Cool 5 minutes.
Cut into squares.
Yields 5 to 6 servings.

title: butterscotch topping
directions: Heat first 3 ingredients to full boil, stirring constantly. Cook 5 minutes.
Cool.
Then slowly stir in evaporated milk.
Serve cooked over ice cream.

title: best-ever banana muffins
directions: Mash bananas.
Add sugar and slightly beaten egg.
Add melted butter.
Add dry ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes until done.

title: orange salad
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Mix well.
Sprinkle dry jello over this and mix well.
Spoon mixture into a 13 x 9-inch dish. Mix nuts and coconut and sprinkle on top.
Cover and chill.

title: broccoli chicken casserole
directions: Layer broccoli in a 7 x 11 inch baking dish. Top with chicken. In a separate bowl, combine soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice, and curry powder. Spread the soup mixture evenly over the chicken layer. Finish by sprinkling cheese on top and adding a light coating of bread crumbs. Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour. If desired, place under the broiler until lightly browned. Makes 6 servings.

title: toffee squares
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan. Combine oatmeal, brown sugar, margarine, corn syrup, vanilla and salt.
Mix well.
Firmly press mixture into prepared pan.
Bake about 18 minutes or until brown and bubbly.
Remove from oven and let stand 10 minutes, then sprinkle with chocolate chips.
Spread over bars.
Nuts may be sprinkled over top of chocolate.
Cool completely and cut into squares.
Store tightly covered in cool, dry place.
Makes 6 dozen bars.

title: curry-yogurt dip
directions: Combine and use as a dip for vegetables.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion until tender. Drain and mash.
Combine all ingredients except dressing.
Put in buttered casserole. Sprinkle dressing on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: m&m cookies
directions: Blend Crisco and sugar.
Beat in vanilla, water and egg.
Sift remaining dry ingredients together; add to the sugar and egg mixture.
Mix well.
Stir in M&M's.
Drop from teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes, or until golden brown.
If you want more color in cookies, place more M&M's on cookies before baking.

title: california potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes with skins on until done.
Set aside to cool. Peel potatoes, then grate.
Chop scallions and add to potatoes. Sprinkle with parsley.
In saucepan, combine chicken soup, sour cream, Cheddar cheese and stick of margarine or butter.
Heat until butter or margarine melts.
Pour over potatoes.
Mix and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: imperial salad(recipe from old virginia)
directions: Drain juice from pineapple and add enough water to make a pint with the vinegar.
Heat and dissolve gelatin.
When cooked, add the other things and let set.
Serve on lettuce with Fruit Salad Dressing.

title: fruit cake
directions: Mix baking powder and pinch of salt with flour.
Place fruits and nuts in large bowl, sprinkle flour and sugar over fruits and coat each piece well.
Beat eggs and pour over mixture.
Mix well and pour in greased and lined tube pan.
Bake 2 1/2 hours at 275°.

title: sausage-potato soup(serves 6 to 8)
directions: Brown sausage, stirring to crumble.
Drain and set aside. Combine potatoes, onions, water, salt and celery seed in large Dutch oven; cover and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer about 20 to 25 minutes, or until potatoes are tender.
Slightly mash potatoes.
Add sausage, parsley and milk; heat to serving temperature.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Cut cabbage into pieces and cook.
Drain.
Mix undiluted soup, cheese and pimento.
Add cabbage.
Pour into buttered 2-quart dish.
Combine stuffing mix and melted margarine.
Sprinkle on top of cabbage mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: lasagne
directions: Mix browned and drained hamburger with spaghetti sauce. Spread 1 cup meat mixture on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer noodles, cheeses and meat sauce, saving approximately 1 cup of meat sauce to spread over top layer of noodles to keep noodles from drying out when cooking.
Pour 1 cup water on ends; cover tightly with foil.
Refrigerate for 8 hours or overnight so noodles will soften.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Remove foil; bake an additional 15 minutes.
Let stand 15 to 20 minutes before serving.

title: scrambled eggs
directions: In a 9-inch microwave-safe pie plate, crumble meat and add onion.
Cover with waxed paper.
Cook on High for 4 minutes, stirring once.
Drain.

title: helen's bean salad
directions: Combine sugar, oil, vinegar and salt.
Heat on high for 3 to 5 minutes until mixture boils and sugar dissolves.

title: potato
directions: Boil potato. Drain and put in baking dish. Put butter over potato. Sprinkle dried Italian dressing. Put potato in oven for a few minutes.

title: spanish rice
directions: In grease, cook onions, pepper, comino, oregano, salt and rice.
Cook until begins to brown. Add tomatoes and water.
Cook slowly about 40 minutes.
When served, add a small amount of hot sauce to each serving.
(Let each do their own.)
Serve with Japanese Chicken.

title: homemade paste
directions: Mix flour with cold water; stir until creamy.
Boil slowly for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Cool.
Add few drops of oil of wintergreen to retard spoiling and give pleasant odor.
Store in covered jar and refrigerate, if possible.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add eggs, water, Crisco oil and pumpkin; mix well.
Bake in two 9 1/2-inch pans or in a loaf pan at 350° for 1 hour, or until golden brown.

title: cheddar cheese pie
directions: Mix together and pour into pie shell.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.
If frozen pie shell is used, add 1/2 cup more of ham and fill 2 shells.

title: unbaked oatmeal cookies
directions: Melt butter in a large saucepan.
Add sugar, cocoa, apple and salt.
Boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat and immediately add oats, nuts and vanilla.
Mix well.
Drop by heaping teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper.
When cool, roll in powdered sugar, if desired. Makes about 70 small cookies.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Use 1 tablespoon per cup.

title: cheesy coleslaw
directions: Combine cabbage apple and cheese in a bowl.
Pour dressing over and toss.
Refrigerate 1/2 hours for flavor to blend.

title: velveeta salsa mac 'n cheese
directions: Brown meat in large skillet; drain. Add salsa and water. Bring to boil. Stir in macaroni. Reduce heat to medium-low; cover with tight-fitting lid. Simmer 8 to 10 minutes or until macaroni is tender. Add Velveeta; stir until melted. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: something different cheese spread
directions: Crumble Bleu cheese.
Mix with remaining ingredients.
Shape into ball and chill.
Take out and warm to room temperature. Serve with crackers.

title: punch
directions: Mix all ingredients except ginger ale.
Add ginger ale just before serving.

title: campers' apple pie
directions: Place apples in bottom of casserole dish and add water.
Break bread in small pieces over apples.
Melt oleo, add egg and dry ingredients. Pour over crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: pumpkin custard(not a dessert)
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Melt 1/2 stick butter in casserole. Pour half of melted butter into mixture.
Pour all into casserole. Top with 1/4 cup sugar mixed with cinnamon.
Bake at 425° for 30 minutes.
Good as extra veggie for big dinner such as Thanksgiving or Christmas.

title: potato cakes
directions: Combine potatoes, flour, eggs, salt and pepper.
Add a touch of milk, if needed for proper consistency.
Mix and form into patties. Fry on both sides until golden brown.
Enjoy!

title: jean's scalloped corn
directions: Butter a baking dish.
Arrange layers of corn and crackers, making 2 layers of corn and thinner layers of crackers.
Dot each layer with butter.
Season with salt and pepper.
Pour half and half over mixture.
Bake at 375° to 400° for 40 to 60 minutes.

title: surprise biscuits
directions: To your favorite biscuit recipe, add 1 cup grated Swiss cheese and 2 tablespoons caraway seed.
Cut out biscuits.
Sprinkle with kosher salt and butter and bake.
Different!

title: chafing dish duck
directions: Per duck:
Clean, wash and season each duck well with salt, pepper and lots of Worcestershire sauce.
Stuff each duck with one quarter each apple, onion and celery.
Place in roasting pan with 1/4 cup red wine per duck.
Cook until duck almost falls off the bone, basting frequently with the drippings and wine in the bottom of the pan.
Remove duck and cool.
Pull meat from carcass and shred.
Keep drippings from the pan for seasoning.
Add shredded duck to drippings.
Serve in chafing dish with party rolls or Melba rounds.
Great for a party!

title: wine cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease and flour 12 cup bundt pan. Mix all ingredients in a large bowl. Beat for a full 5 minutes (important). Bake at 350° for 50 minutes. Let cool for 15 minutes and then top with powdered sugar.

title: corn chowder
directions: Saute onion and green pepper in oleo.
Add ham and brown slightly.
Add all other ingredients except wine.
Simmer for 30 to 50 minutes.
Add wine and simmer another 10 minutes and serve.

title: chocolate toffee grahams
directions: preheat oven to 350 degrees. Arrange graham crackers in a single layer in a jelly roll pan (15 x 10 x 1 in.) Set aside.

title: spinach pie without crust
directions: Heat olive oil.
Saute onion.
Combine spinach and onion.
Let cool.
Add diced pork chops, grated Parmesan, Ricotta, eggs, salt and pepper to spinach mixture.
Grease 8 x 13-inch Pyrex dish and dust with bread crumbs.
Pour mixture into dish.
Bake at 425° for 40 minutes.
Reheat at 375°, covered, for 40 minutes.
Cut into bite size squares.
Hmmmm!

title: scalloped carrots
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Brown onion in margarine in skillet. Add flour, celery salt, salt and dry mustard.
Stir in milk and cook until thickened.
Add cheese and stir to melt.
Add cooked carrots and pour into buttered casserole.
Top with bread crumbs and bake at 300° for 45 minutes.

title: 4 bean salad or 3 bean
directions: Drain beans.
Add green pepper and onion.
Mix additional ingredients into it.
Refrigerate, stirring once in awhile. Leave overnight or at least 4 hours so beans have a chance to pickle.

title: shrimp stuffed peppers
directions: Cut slice from stem ends of peppers; remove seeds and wash. Parboil 5 minutes.
Chop end slice of peppers and cook with onion in butter until tender.
Add mushrooms and cook until tender.
Add tomato, salt, parsley and shrimp.
Heat thoroughly.
Fill peppers with mixture, sprinkle with bread crumbs and dot with butter. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: moist cake
directions: Bake cake in 9 x 13-inch pan according to directions.
I prefer Duncan Hines Lemon Supreme.
While hot, poke holes through cake and pour Eagle Brand over hot cake.
Cool.
Ice with Cool Whip. Sprinkle with flaked coconut.
Store in refrigerator, airtight.

title: raw vegetable dip
directions: Mix ingredients thoroughly and serve with assorted raw vegetables.

title: salad dressing
directions: Very tasty for potato salad.

title: huckleberry nut bread
directions: Sift together first 3 ingredients.
In separate bowl, beat together syrup, eggs and margarine.
Fold in berries and nuts. Mix the dry ingredients.

title: carolina apple cake
directions: Mix oil, sugar and eggs together.
Sift flour, soda and salt together.
Add to egg mixture and mix thoroughly.
Add vanilla, apples and nuts.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan and bake in a 350° oven for about 1 hour.
Remove cake and let cool.
Top with the following glaze.

title: applesauce squares
directions: Add all ingredients and mix well.
Use greased and floured baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or test when you think it is done.
Cut in squares.
Sprinkle powdered sugar when still warm.

title: african-american cornbread
directions: Mix together well.
Bake at 425° in a greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Grease loaf pans.
Pour into loaf pans or bread pans.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: lemon fruit cake
directions: Reserve 1/4 cup flour to coat fruit.
Cream butter and sugar. Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Add eggs and flour mixture to bowl; add floured fruit.
Bake in well-greased tube pan lined with wax paper.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: dill dip
directions: Combine cheese, mayonnaise and milk; mix until well blended. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Chill.
Serve with veggie dippers (carrots, celery, peppers, broccoli or cauliflower).
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef and onion. Drain. Add tomato sauce, water and seasonings.
In oblong pan, layer sauce, noodles and cheeses. Repeat layers, ending with sauce.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour.

title: lo-cal ice milk
directions: Whirl all ingredients in a blender until no chunks are left. Pour into sealable bowl and freeze.
Any fruit that can be frozen can be used.

title: beef marinade
directions: Put all ingredients in blender.
Blend until smooth.
Marinate steak at least 1 hour or overnight.

title: chocolate chip cheese cake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Combine crumbs, sugar and margarine; press firmly on bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan.
In large mixer bowl, beat cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in Eagle Brand until smooth.
Add eggs and vanilla; mix well.
In small bowl, toss 1/2 cup chips with flour to coat; stir into cheese mixture. Pour into prepared pan.
Sprinkle remaining 1/2 cup chips evenly over top.
Bake 55 minutes or until center springs back when lightly touched.
Turn oven off; allow cheesecake to cool in oven with door slightly open.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine first three ingredients in a bowl; refrigerate 30 minutes.
Shape mixture into ball and roll in chopped pecans, coating thoroughly.
Serve with crackers.
Yield: 2 1/2 cups.

title: dilled chicken
directions: Place chicken in 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Mix soup, sour cream, mayonnaise and seasonings.
Pour over chicken, covering well.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Cover with foil the last 30 minutes if it begins to brown too much.

title: homemade spaghetti
directions: Cook spaghetti until done.
Cook ground beef until brown. Drain spaghetti. Drain ground beef.
Mix tomato paste, spaghetti mix, onions and green peppers and let simmer for 5 minutes.
Pour over spaghetti.
Makes 6 servings.

title: ham 'n cheese strata
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Combine cheese, ham and mustard. Spread half ham mixture on 5 slices of toast.
Top with remaining slices of toast.

Quarter sandwiches and arrange in 3 rows in a buttered 2-quart rectangular pan, standing crust side down. Combine milk and eggs, pour over tops and sides of sandwiches. Bake 40 to 45 minutes or until knife inserted near center comes out clean.
Serves 6.

title: oyster dressing
directions: Pull crumbs from crusts of 3 or 4 day old bread.
Disregard crusts.
Add salt, seasonings and pepper; toss.
Melt margarine, add celery and onion.
Saute until just softened, then stir in oysters.
Pour over bread crumbs with chicken stock.
Mix lightly with fork or hands.
Put in 8 x 11 x 2-inch baking dish and cook, uncovered, in 350° oven for one hour.
Yields 6 servings.

title: maui linguica(cheese and sausage broil)
directions: Blend cheese, linguica and egg in mixing bowl.
Place a tablespoon of mixture on bread rounds (that have been toasted on one side).
Place under broiler until bubbly and hot, approximately 4 to 5 minutes.
Serve hot. Makes about 3 dozen 2 1/2-inch appetizers.

title: pumpkin bread #2
directions: Cream shortening and sugar in bowl.
Beat in eggs and pumpkin. Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with 2/3 cup water, mixing well after each addition.
Stir in vanilla and pecans. Pour into two greased loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool in pans for 10 minutes before removing.
Yields 20 servings.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients. Form balls and put into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Pour sweet and sour sauce on top and bake at 375° for 1 hour, then lower to 325° for 1/2 hour.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Boil carrots for 7 minutes, stirring to prevent sticking. Drain and put in buttered casserole dish.
Combine cheese, butter and milk.
Heat until cheese melts and mixture is hot.
Stir frequently to prevent sticking!
Pour mixture over carrots.
Mix 1/2 stick butter with Ritz crackers, then sprinkle layer on top of cheese mixture.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes, until bubbly.

title: hot pepper rings
directions: Pour hot water over rings and let set for 4 or 5 minutes. Bring to a boil the oil, sugar, vinegar, ketchup and salt.
Drain rings and add to boiled mixture.
Bring to a boil again and place in jars and seal at once.

title: george washington pie
directions: Bake pie crusts as directed and cool.
Drain cherries and cut into pieces.
Mix together all ingredients.
Pour into pie shells and refrigerate.
Makes 2 pies.

title: baked cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Combine margarine, crumbs and sugar. Pat firmly on bottom of buttered 9-inch spring-form pan.
In large mixer bowl, beat cheese until fluffy.
Beat in Eagle Brand, eggs and salt until smooth.
Stir in ReaLemon.
Pour into prepared pan. Bake 50 to 55 minutes or until cake springs back when lightly touched.
Cool to room temperature.
Chill.
Spread sour cream on cheesecake.
Garnish as desired (suggestions:
strawberries or blueberries toppings or peaches).

title: cashew chicken for two
directions: Cut chicken in 1 x 1 1/2-inch pieces.
Dredge in flour; let stand 15 minutes.
Combine eggs, milk, salt and pepper.
Add chicken and let stand 10 minutes.
Dredge chicken in flour and deep fry in oil at 375° for 3 to 5 minutes until golden brown. Serve chicken over rice.
Spoon on Bouillon Sauce and top with cashews, onions and soy sauce to taste.

title: do-nut balls
directions: Mix together sugar, milk and eggs.
Melt Crisco and add to sugar mixture.
Then add flour.
Mix until smooth and drop from teaspoon in deep oil.
Roll in powdered sugar.

title: hot chocolate recipe
directions: Mix together and store in tight container.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Sift flour, sugar and soda in a bowl.
Put cocoa and butter, shortening and water into a saucepan.
Heat and stir to mix. Continue to stir and bring to a full boil; boil for 1 minute.
Mix with dry ingredients.
Add buttermilk, eggs and vanilla.
Mix well. Pour into 11 x 16 x 1-inch greased and floured jelly roll pan. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Pour icing over cake while still warm.

title: potato salad
directions: Mix dressing, mustard, celery seed, salt and pepper in large bowl.
Add remaining ingredients; mix lightly.
Refrigerate.

title: cheese cake
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 cup hot water.
Put in refrigerator and let
stand
until like egg white.
Cream cheese with sugar and add lemon juice.
Add jello to cream cheese mixture.
Whip chilled evaporated
milk
and then add to mixture.
Yield:
2 (9-inch) pies.

title: spinach kimchee
directions: Wash and drain spinach.
Blanch spinach in boiling water about 60 seconds.
Rinse immediately in cold water, drain and squeeze. Add all ingredients after placing in glass bowl.
Mix by hand. Place in glass container.
Eat fresh with white rice or refrigerate!

title: north country stew
directions: In a large skillet, cook bacon, sausage and onion until bacon is crisp.
Drain.
In Dutch oven or large saucepan, combine all ingredients.
Cover and simmer 30 to 60 minutes.

title: spinach garlic soup
directions: In a 5-quart saucepan, bring spinach, 3 1/2 cups broth and carrot to a boil.
Reduce heat; simmer for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove from the heat; cool to lukewarm.
Meanwhile, in a skillet coated with nonstick cooking spray, saut onion and garlic until onion is soft, about 5 minutes.
Combine flour and remaining broth until smooth.
Add to skillet; cook and stir over low heat for 3 to 5 minutes.
Add to spinach mixture.
Puree in small batches in a blender or food processor until finely chopped. Place in a large saucepan.
Add evaporated milk, milk and pepper; heat through but do not boil.
Yields 6 servings.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream until light and fluffy oleo and sugar.
Add applesauce, raisins and pecans.
Sift together and add flour, nutmeg, cinnamon and soda.
Pour into lightly greased 9 x 13-inch cake pan and bake 45 minutes to 1 hour, depending on your oven.
This cake stays very moist.
If you have nonraisin lovers, it will work without the raisins.

title: glorified rice salad
directions: Cook rice until done.
Drain pineapple using juice.
Add cornstarch and cook until thickened (use 1/2 cup warm water). Cool and then add mayonnaise, sugar and salt.
Mix with rice and pineapple.
Whip cream with vanilla and fold into rice mixture. Chill and serve with cherry on top!

title: black walnut divinity
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients in saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture comes to a boil.
Reduce heat; cook without stirring until syrup forms a ball in cold water (holds shape but is still plastic).
Beat egg whites until stiff peaks form.
Beating constantly on high speed of electric mixer, slowly pour hot syrup over egg whites.
Continue beating until small amount holds soft peak when dropped from spoon.
Mix in vanilla and nuts.
Drop by teaspoons onto waxed paper.

title: monkey cake
directions: Cut each biscuit into quarters.
Shake in bag of cinnamon and sugar.
After shaking, layer in Bundt pan:
one layer biscuits, nuts and repeat.

title: carrot cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Beat eggs and oil together and add sifted dry ingredients; fold in carrots.
Grease and flour 2 or 3 cake pans and bake from 25 minutes to 35 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
You may also use a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan and bake for 35 minutes.

title: enchilada casserole chicken
directions: Lightly grease or use Pam on casserole dish.
Layer corn/flour tortilla, enchilada sauce, cheese, onions and chicken and sauce. Layer until dish is filled.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Garnish with shredded lettuce, diced tomatoes and sour cream.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: apple-cinnamon rolls
directions: Heat butter, jelly and icing from can of rolls in 8 or 9-inch round pan on top of stove until bubbly.
Sprinkle in coconut. Separate dough into 8 rolls and arrange over hot topping.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Invert onto serving plate.

title: cashew chicken
directions: Use boned chicken and cut in small pieces.
Mix broth, soy sauce and oyster sauce over medium heat.
When mixture boils, add 2 tablespoons cornstarch.
Stir until thick. Add 1/2 package cashews.
Mix flour, baking powder, water, 1/4 cup cornstarch, salt and oil until smooth. Soak chicken in this batter, then deep fry.
Add remaining cashews.

title: cheddar cheese rolls
directions: Mix hamburger, sauce, bread crumbs, egg
and salt well. Pat on wax paper to 14 x 8-inches.
Mix
remaining ingredients and spread over meat to within 1-inch of edges.
Roll up jelly roll fashion. Chill several hours.
Slice
into
servings. Bake in shallow pan at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Dip chicken pieces in butter.
Shake remaining ingredients in paper bag; add chicken and shake until coated. Butter 9 x 13-inch baking dish; add chicken pieces.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: elegant pork chops
directions: Crush the garlic and rub on both sides of pork chops.
Season with pepper.
Dip chops in flour.
Beat egg whites with the water. Place chops in this mixture, then roll in the bread crumbs. Refrigerate 1/2 hour.
Brown chops in margarine and oil.
Remove chops to a square casserole dish. To remaining margarine in pan, lightly brown onion.
Add the wine, beef broth and bay leaf. Simmer for 2 minutes, then pour over pork chops. Cover and bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.
Remove bay leaf and serve.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Blend in butter, flour, vanilla, salt, sugar and syrup.
Sprinkle nuts over bottom of pie shell. Gently pour ingredients over nuts and bake in hot oven at 425° for 10 minutes. Reduce heat to 325° and bake about 40 minutes.

title: sofrito(basic seasoning)
directions: In a small frying pan, heat oil slowly.
Add and brown rapidly diced ham.
Reduce heat; add and saute rest of ingredients for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Cool and store in Mason jar in refrigerator.
Use as needed to season soups, stews, chili, beans or Spanish rice.
Experiment and enjoy!

title: super fudge brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Grease an 8 x 8-inch baking pan. Combine unsweetened baking chocolate and butter in a medium saucepan; melt over medium-low heat, stirring constantly, until pieces are almost melted.
Remove from heat and stir until smooth. In a large bowl using an electric mixer on medium speed, beat eggs until light yellow in color, about 5 minutes.
Add sugar and blend on low until thoroughly combined.
Add vanilla and melted chocolate to the egg and sugar mixture;
blend on low speed until smooth.
Add the flour and mix thoroughly.
Pour batter into greased pan.
Smooth surface with a spatula and sprinkle uniformly with chocolate chips.
Bake on the center rack of oven for 45 to 55 minutes.
The batter should be set and a toothpick inserted in center should come out clean; do not overbake.
Cool to room temperature.
Cover and refrigerate for at least 1 hour.
Cut and serve chilled.

title: my strawberry cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed; add box of pudding, 1/4 cup oil and 1/4 cup water. Pour into a pan. Bake as directed. Cool. Place cream cheese in bowl (softened); add 1/4 cup sugar. Beat well. Add Cool Whip; beat well (until creamy). Place jello and boiling water in a bowl. Stir until jello is dissolved. Add quart of strawberries. Place in refrigerator. Allow to chill and thicken. Place cream cheese mixture on cake; spread evenly. Spoon strawberry mixture on top. Store in refrigerator.

title: fast and easy fruit cobbler
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 12-inch pan. Mix all ingredients together except fruit. Spread mixture loosely over bottom of pan. Spoon fruit over mixture. DO NOT STIR. Bake at 400° until golden brown, about 30 minutes.

title: adirondack beans
directions: Fry hamburger, onion and bacon together in bottom of Dutch oven. When meat is brown, drain off excess grease.
Add all remaining ingredients. Cover and place hot coals under and on top of the oven.
Bake for 1 to 1 1/2 hours, stirring occasionally.

title: tortilla and black bean casserole
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in skillet.
Bring to boil; reduce heat.
Simmer, uncovered, for 10 minutes.
Stir in beans.
Spread 1/3 of bean mixture in a 2-quart square baking dish.
Top with 1/2 tortillas overlapping as necessary and half cheese.
Add another 1/3 of bean mix, then remaining tortillas and bean mix.

title: fruity chicken salad
directions: Cut everything into bite size pieces. Mix in salad dressing. Chill and serve.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except chips.
Crumble chips on top.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: baked corn in sour cream
directions: Fry bacon; drain and crumble.
Set aside.
Saute onion in margarine.
Blend in flour and salt.
Gradually add sour cream, stirring until mixture is smooth.
Heat just to boiling.
Add corn; heat thoroughly.
Fold in half of bacon.
Spoon into greased 2-quart casserole.
Top with parsley and remaining bacon.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: play dough for children
directions: Mix together the flour, salt and cream of tartar.
Add oil, water and coloring.
Cook, stirring, for 1 to 3 minutes, or until thick.
Knead almost immediately.
Keep in airtight container in refrigerator.
This makes a nice, soft play dough and will last up to a year.

title: ham and cheese pinwheels
directions: Combine all ingredients except ham.
Spread mixture on ham slices.
Roll each slice lengthwise and fasten with toothpick. Chill.
Cut ham into thin slices.

title: hot or cold chocolate mix
directions: Mix well and store in airtight container.

title: hot spiced mulled wine
directions: Pour all above into large pot.
Heat and stir; do not boil.

title: celery salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling pineapple juice.
Cool.
Mix in remaining ingredients.
Refrigerate several hours.

title: joan's seafood supreme
directions: Coat onions and shrimp in flour.
In large frying pan, saute onions and shrimp in hot margarine, until lightly browned.
Add cooked rice to ingredients; crumble crabmeat and add to pan. Liberally sprinkle soy sauce over ingredients, stirring constantly with fork.
Cover; cook over low flame for 15 minutes or until flavors meld together.

title: easy fruit salad
directions: Drain juice from peaches and oranges.
Reserve 1 1/4 cups. Mix the 1 1/4 cups juice with the pudding.
Mix in a large bowl. Stir until smooth.
Add sliced bananas.
Stir remaining drained fruit and refrigerate until serving time.

title: lime salad
directions: Place jello in boiling water.
Stir until well mixed.
Add marshmallows and stir until slightly melted.
Add pineapple, Miracle Whip, pecans and cottage cheese.
Place in refrigerator and stir often until set.

title: strawberry torte
directions: Beat egg whites until almost stiff.
Slowly beat in 1/2 cup of sugar and add vanilla.
Mix together cracker crumbs, chopped pecans and 1/2 cup of sugar.
Fold in stiff egg whites gently.
Put in a 10-inch greased pie tin and bake at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes. Take from oven and cool.

title: cornbread
directions: Mix cornmeal, flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix together milk and egg and oil and sugar.
Add to the cornmeal mixture. Stir only enough to mix.
Fill greased baking pan half full.
Bake at 425° about 25 minutes or until lightly brown.
Can also be baked in a greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Cook until thickens, then pour into pie shell.
Cover with meringue and cook at 300° until browned slightly.
Makes one 9-inch pie.

title: greenbrier dessert
directions: Put water, Jell-O and marshmallows in a saucepan and heat until dissolved.
Let cool; mix in fruit, cottage cheese and Dream Whip.
Chill.

title: barbecue spareribs
directions: Brown spareribs.
Combine all ingredients and pour over ribs and simmer.
Very good done in crock-pot.
Broil ribs; place in crock-pot (ribs/sauce) and cook on low several hours.
Serve with rice.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Place in casserole dish and add baked Tater Tots, cream of mushroom soup and salt and pepper. Stir until well blended.
Place a few Tater Tots on top and add grated cheese. Place in oven until cheese is melted.

title: thin spaghetti with spinach and bacon
directions: Bring a large pot of water to a boil for the pasta.
In a large skillet, cook the bacon over medium to low heat until browned and crisp.
Drain on paper towels, crumble and reserve. Pour off all but one tablespoon of the bacon fat and add olive oil to the skillet.
Add the garlic and the spinach, tossing to make sure the leaves are coated with oil.
Add tomatoes and wine and simmer over medium heat for about 5 minutes, or until leaves are wilted.

title: heavenly banana pudding
directions: In mixing bowl, blend the pudding, milk, Eagle Brand milk and cool whip.
Layer starting with the wafers, then pudding mixture, then sliced bananas.
Will make approximately three layers.

title: sawdust salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add cold water, lemon juice, crushed pineapple and bananas.
Pour into 13 x 9 x 2 baking dish and cover with a layer of miniature marshmallows.
Put in refrigerator to set, but add topping before salad congeals.

title: frozen passion
directions: In ice cream freezer container, combine ingredients; mix well. Freeze according to manufacturer's instructions.
Store leftovers in freezer.

title: coach taylor's favorite chicken casserole
directions: Strip chicken into bite size pieces.
Place pieces of cooked chicken in oblong cake pan.
Place broccoli on top of chicken. Mix cream of chicken soup and mayonnaise together.
Pour over chicken and broccoli.
Sprinkle Cheddar cheese on top of mixture. Mix dressing according to package directions using broth from cooked chicken instead of water.
Add sage and pecans to dressing. Place dressing on top of cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: joshua's favorite stuffed cabbage rolls
directions: Separate cabbage leaves and cook just to tender.
Mix together in large bowl raw hamburger, onion, peppers and celery.
Add egg, oatmeal, some garlic powder, salt and pepper and mix well.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Whip to soften.
Wash shrimp in cold water.
Mix well and refrigerate 4 to 6 hours.

title: new england fish chowder
directions: Put salt pork, potatoes and onions into the two cups of boiling water and cook until potatoes are soft, not mushy.
Add fish which has been boned.
(You can steam your fish, skin and bone it after it is steamed, then add to your potatoes.
I like to add fillets of fish and cook them with the potatoes the last 4 or 5 minutes.)
When the fish has lost its opaque look, you know it is cooked.
Add your milk and seasonings.
Heat until milk is scalding hot, not boiling.
Remove from heat and let stand for a while to season.
Reheat to eating temperature.
Be sure milk does not boil.

title: herbed chicken and vegetables with wine
directions: Combine flour, paprika, Italian seasoning, salt and pepper. Coat chicken pieces with flour mixture.
Heat oil in large skillet or Dutch oven until hot.
Cook chicken until brown on both sides, about 15 minutes.
Add wine, lemon juice and garlic.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and cook 40 minutes.
Add carrots; cover and cook for 5 minutes.
Stir in green beans and mushrooms; cook, uncovered, stirring occasionally until green beans are hot, about 5 minutes.
Stir in cherry tomatoes.
Heat just until hot. Yields 6 servings.

title: four herb barbecue sauce(for chicken, turkey, leg of lamb)
directions: Combine all ingredients. Shake or stir and pour into a glass jar with screw-top. Keep covered in refrigerator until needed. Use to baste chicken, turkey or lamb while roasting.

title: ice cream roll
directions: Beat eggs, salt and vanilla.
Add other ingredients.
Pour into wax papered jelly roll pan.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes. Pour onto powdered sugar coated pillow case (yes a real linen pillow case) and roll up.
Cool completely.
Fill with 1/2 gallon softened vanilla ice cream (or another kind if you prefer).
Roll up.
Freeze.
Slice and serve.
(I sometimes slice individual pieces, wrap and freeze.)

title: chimichangas
directions: Brown meat with onion and garlic; drain.
Stir in picante sauce, cumin, oregano and salt.
Simmer 5 minutes or until most of liquid has evaporated.

title: glorified brownies
directions: Mix in order given.
Spread in pan and bake 20 minutes at 400°.
When done, cut marshmallows into very small pieces and spread over top of brownies while still hot.
Cover with powdered sugar and nuts.
It is just as good without the marshmallows and powdered sugar.

title: crab dip
directions: Soften cheese at 350° for 25 minutes.
Blend.

title: gregg's cookies
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add remaining ingredients.
Form into balls.
Flatten slightly on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: fudge filling
directions: Boil ingredients, except vanilla, exactly 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and add vanilla.
Place in ice water and beat with electric mixer for five minutes.

title: harvard beets
directions: Mix vinegar, salt, sugar and cornstarch into beet juice. Bring to boil, stirring constantly.
Add beets and butter.
Cook 10 minutes.

title: chicken mushroom
directions: Cook chicken until done.
Can be fried or baked the way you prefer.
Pour mushroom mixture over chicken and bake 10 to 15 minutes at 350°.

title: potatoes au gratin
directions: Melt butter; blend in flour and salt.
Stir until smooth. Turn to low heat and slowly add milk, stirring constantly.
Cook and stir until thick and smooth.
Remove from heat.
Add cheese and stir until cheese melts.
Arrange potatoes in 1 1/2-quart buttered casserole dish.
Pour cheese sauce over potatoes; top with crumbs.
Dot with additional butter.
Bake in 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Serves 4.

title: hawaiian skillet beans
directions: Cook bacon in skillet until crisp; drain on paper towel. Crumble coarsely.
Pour off all but 2 tablespoons drippings. Saute pineapple until slightly browned; remove.
Combine beans, brown sugar and crumbled bacon in skillet.
Heat through.
Top with pineapple slices; heat until bubbly.
Makes 5 servings.

title: flour frosting(not so sweet)
directions: Boil milk and flour until thick.
Cool and add butter, shortening, sugar and vanilla.
Beat until smooth.

title: grandma annie cameron's sunday-after-church beef roast
directions: Rinse roast and put in large baking dish or covered roaster with about 1/2 cup water.
Add onions, carrots and celery.
Salt and pepper roast.
Cover baking pan with foil or roaster with lid. The secret of a very tender roast is to cook it slow at 275° until tender and roast falls apart.
(This is very similar to roast beef in Amish restaurants.)
When cooked, you can make gravy from drippings over meat, if desired.

title: cornbread
directions: Sift together the first 5 ingredients; add the milk, egg and oil.
Beat together for 2 minutes.
Place 2 teaspoons of oil in an 8-inch cake pan. Pour in batter.
The oil will rise around it, greasing pan evenly.
Bake at 425° for 25 minutes.
Use a larger pan if you wish a crisper and thinner cornbread.
Shorten baking time.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients; add egg, milk and shortening.
Mix well until smooth.
Pour into 8-inch greased pan or muffin pan.
Bake in hot oven (425°) for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: crock-pot stew
directions: Put all ingredients in crock-pot.
Cook on low for about 8 or 9 hours.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: play dough
directions: Mix the dry ingredients together in a pan.
Add the oil and water a bit at a time to blend.
Add food coloring of your choice until you like the color.
Mix well.
Place the mixture over medium heat, stirring constantly.
The mixture will thicken to a "doughy" consistency.
Remove from heat.
Cool.
Knead (good therapy!).
Store in an airtight container.

title: mincemeat cookies
directions: Sift together flour, salt and soda.
Cream shortening.
Add sugar gradually, cream together until light and fluffy.
Add eggs.
Beat until fluffy.
Add flour and mix well.
Add mincemeat, broken into small pieces.
Drop by teaspoons 2-inches apart on greased baking sheet.
Bake in moderately hot oven (375°) for about 10 to 12 minutes.

title: fudge pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Melt chocolate and butter.
Mix sugar and flour.
Add eggs to sugar and flour.
Add chocolate mixture.
Bake in unbaked pie shell at 350° for 35 minutes.
It is good to serve with ice cream.

title: easy coconut cake
directions: Bake cake as directed.
Punch holes in cake top while still hot.
Spread cream of coconut while cake is hot.
Sprinkle very lightly with grated coconut.
Spread undrained pineapple now.
Let cool.
Cover with whipped topping and more shredded coconut.
Keep refrigerated.

title: morning crispies
directions: In a large mixing bowl, dissolve yeast in water; let stand for 5 minutes.
Add milk, 1/2 cup sugar, oil, salt, eggs, extract and 2 cups flour; beat well.
Add enough remaining flour to make a soft dough.
Turn onto a floured board; knead until smooth and elastic, about 6 to 8 minutes.
Place in a greased bowl, turning once to grease top.
Cover and let rise in a warm place until doubled, about 1 hour.
Punch the dough down.

title: sugar-free chocolate fudge
directions: In a small mixing bowl, beat cream cheese, chocolate, sweetener and vanilla until smooth.
Stir in pecans.
Pour into an 8-inch square baking pan, lined with foil.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Cut into squares.
Serve chilled.

title: toffee
directions: Boil together 10 minutes until it starts to brown. Add 1 teaspoon vanilla. Spread on cookie sheet. Spread chocolate chips on top. When melted, spread chocolate over first mixture. Sprinkle with ground pecans. Break when cold.

title: dump salad(dessert)
directions: Mix together condensed milk and pie filling.
Add pineapple. Fold in Cool Whip.
Cover and chill.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Cook and drain ground chuck.
Sprinkle meat with chili powder. Add onion, tomato sauce, water and salt and pepper to taste.
Mix well, then add corn and pinto beans.
Stir to mix and add 3/4 cup grated Cheddar cheese.
Put mixture in a casserole dish.
Top with mashed potatoes.
Spoon out in 9 different piles.
Add grated cheese.
Cook approximately 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: skillet steak and corn
directions: In a skillet over medium heat, brown steak, onion and thyme in oil.
Add broth; simmer for 10 minutes.
Stir in tomatoes; cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Add the corn and heat through. Serve over rice.

title: biscuit nugget chicken bake
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In medium saucepan, combine first 7 ingredients.
Heat until hot and bubbly.
Pour hot chicken mixture into ungreased baking dish.
Separate biscuit dough into 10 biscuits.
Cut each into 4 pieces.
In medium size plastic bag, combine 1/2 teaspoon paprika, Parmesan cheese, onion and parsley. Shake biscuit pieces 3 or 4 at a time in cheese-herb mixture until well coated.
Arrange over chicken mixture.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes approximately 6 servings.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Combine zucchini, onions and salt.
Let set overnight.
Drain and rinse, then drain again.
Add remaining ingredients and cook, uncovered, for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Put in jars and seal.

title: wing dings(24 wings)
directions: Melt butter.
Add taco sauce and vinegar.
Dip each wing in mixture and arrange in a shallow baking pan.
Take 1 package salad dressing and sprinkle on top; then sprinkle paprika.
Bake 350° for 25 to 30 minutes until golden brown.
Mix second package of dressing with sour cream.
(Dig wing in dressing.)

title: mom's delight
directions: Cut beef into bite size pieces.
Marinate in Worcestershire sauce for at least 30 minutes.
Place marinated beef into a covered casserole dish.
Add tomato wedges with their juice.
Add onion quarters and bell pepper.
Add Worcestershire sauce.
Marinate. Cover and bake at 350° until aroma fills kitchen (approximately 1 hour).
Bake an additional 30 minutes.
Serve over white rice.

title: cheese grits casserole
directions: Bring water to a boil; add grits.
Cook 15 minutes.
Add all other ingredients.
Place in a greased casserole dish.
Sprinkle with additional cheese and red pepper.
Bake 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.
Real good with fried fish.

title: easy chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli slightly; drain.
Arrange in greased 12 x 7 x 2-inch baking dish.
Put broccoli on bottom and chicken on top. Combine soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and milk.
Stir until smooth and pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Top with crumbs combined with butter.
Bake at 350° for about 35 minutes.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: rick and ron's 20 minute chocolate cake
directions: Sift first 2 ingredients into a bowl.
In pot, bring to a boil next 2 ingredients.
Add chocolate and pour dry ingredients into pot.
Mix and add last 5 ingredients.
Pour on cookie sheet and bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Put ingredients in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer until all is used. Top with dressing.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Separate stems from caps.
Mix stems and all ingredients except caps.
Wash caps well.
Fill caps with stuffing.
Layer bottom of dish with oil when ready to bake.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: chicken and asparagus casserole
directions: Boil chicken breasts in seasoned water until tender.
Cool, debone and cut into bite-size pieces.
Set aside.
Saute onion in butter and add remaining ingredients, except asparagus.
Simmer sauce until the cheese melts.
Place a layer of chicken in a large casserole dish, a layer of asparagus and a layer of sauce.
Repeat layers, ending with sauce.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.
Do not add liquid, even if it looks dry.
Serves 12.
It also freezes well.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix together and bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: dinner rolls
directions: Mix together water, yeast and sugar; set aside.
Mix together buttermilk, melted margarine and eggs.
Add to yeast mixture. Sift soda, salt and flour together into mixture.
Knead and place in large greased covered bowl.
Let rise until double in size. Punch down and let rise second time.
Into greased muffin tin, squeeze off 3 balls per roll for cloverleaf rolls.
Let rise, covered, with dish towel.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: sugar-free apple pie
directions: Bring apple juice to a boil (stove or microwave).
Combine cornstarch, spices and oleo.
Add juice slowly to mixture, blending.
Pour over apples.
Stir to coat.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Place top crust over apples.
Bake at 425° for about 30 minutes.
Reduce temperature to 375°.
Bake 30 more minutes.

title: pickles - pickles
directions: In each quart jar, put grape leaf, garlic, pepper and dill. One or two green green grapes are good, too.
Heat 3 quarts of water and when it comes to a boil, add salt and vinegar.
Bring to a boil.
Then pour over your prepared jars of pickles.
This will cover about 8 quarts.

title: oatmeal bread
directions: Mix together boiling water, coffee, oatmeal, molasses, shortening and salt.
Add the yeast cake dissolved in warm water. Add eggs and flour.
Let rise 2 hours.
Punch down.
Form 2 loaves of bread.
Put in greased loaf pans.
Let rise again.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Reduce oven temperature to 350° and bake for 35 minutes.

title: sweet and easy carrots
directions: Cut carrots into strips about 2 to 3 inches long; also cut lengthwise into halves or quarters (if large).
Boil in saucepan until tender.
Drain off excess water.
Mix together juice, brown sugar and flour.
Pour into saucepan and stir well.
Add margarine.
Stir occasionally until carrots are well coated. Serves 4.

title: crab chowder
directions: Step one is to save all the bones and skin from whatever chicken dishes you make.
Put them into one of the large gallon freezer bags and store in your freezer.
Add to the bag until it is full.
You will need at least one gallon bag full to make your stock.
The size of your stockpot and your freezer size dictate the amount of stock you make at any given time.

title: pastry
directions: Cut in flour, salt and sugar with pastry blender until crumbly.
Then work in the other ingredients until the right texture to work with.

title: parsley potatoes
directions: In saucepan, cook potatoes in water to cover until tender; drain.
Combine butter and parsley; pour over potatoes and toss to coat.
Season with salt and pepper.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: instant breakfast cookies
directions: Stir together the flour and instant breakfast.
Blend shortening and peanut butter.
Add sugar; beat until light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs.
Add dry ingredients; mix well.
Drop heaping teaspoonfuls onto greased baking sheet; flatten.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 12 to 15 minutes, until lightly browned. Cool on wire racks.

title: hearty nacho dip
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Melt cheese and add other ingredients. Stir well.
Serve with tortilla chips.
May serve as a meal with salad.
This is a party favorite and travels well in a crock-pot to keep warm.
I brown and drain meat, then pour all in crock-pot until cheese is melted and mixed well.

title: golden broccoli
directions: Cook broccoli in salted water as directed on package or until tender.
Drain.
Place broccoli in a greased 9 x 12 x 2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with lemon juice and pepper and cover with the soup.
Sprinkle cheese on top and place under broiler for 10 minutes or until cheese is melted and bubbly hot.
Serves 8.

title: aunt hope's apricot bars
directions: Grease pan very well.
Mix cake mix, margarine and nuts.
Set aside one cup of this mixture.
Press remainder into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread 1 cup of preserves over top.
Mix cheese, sugar, egg, vanilla, flour, salt and 1/3 cup preserves.
Spread on top.
Add coconut to reserved mix and sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes, until solid.
Refrigerate.

title: barbs beefy burgers
directions: Brown beef; drain fat.
Add all vegetables.
Saute several minutes.
Add soup and 1/2 can of water.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Put on hamburger buns and top with cheese.

title: chicken divan
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cook broccoli.
Layer the chicken, broccoli and cheese.
Pour over all a mixture of the soup and Pet milk.
Bake 25 minutes, then put onion rings on top. Bake about 5 minutes more.

title: bisquick cookies
directions: Mix well.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Let cool a short time before putting on rack.

title: ham and rice stir-fry
directions: Cook rice according to directions; drain and set aside.
Saute onion and celery in oil until tender-crisp.
Add mushrooms, peas and ham.
Cook 3 to 4 minutes.
Push mixture aside in pan and scramble eggs.
Add rice and soy sauce.
Toss lightly with ham mixture until completely heated.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: fruited chicken
directions: Dip chicken parts in flour mixture.
Saute in garlic and oil. When browned, add remaining ingredients.
Simmer until done.
Keep stirring.

title: cowboy soup
directions: In large stock pot brown the meat and onions. Add remaining ingreds. Cover and simmer for 1 hr.

title: let's have some more fruit dip
directions: Mix equal parts of soft cream cheese and marshmallow topping. Tint mixture pink with red food coloring.
Good with strawberries, watermelon, cantaloupe, grapes, etc.

title: apple lasagna(serves 12 to 15)
directions: Combine Cheddar
cheese, Ricotta cheese, egg, sugar and almond extract in a medium bowl.
Blend well.
Spread 1 can of apple pie filling over
bottom
of
a greased 13 x 9-inch pan. Layer 1/2 of the
noodles
over	filling,
then spread cheese mixture over noodles, then remaining can of apple pie filling.

title: nachos
directions: Cook meat, onion and garlic until meat is brown; drain.
Stir in beans.
Arrange half of the chips on each of two 12-inch ovenproof platters.
Layer half of the meat-bean mixture, olives, chili peppers and cheese on each platter.

title: five cup salad
directions: Combine above items and chill well.
Serve on lettuce, or in drained peach halves.

title: italian sausage sandwich
directions: Bake sausage in a 325° oven for 40 minutes; drain.
Slice onions and green peppers; saute in melted oleo.
The last 5 minutes, add mushrooms and bouillon cube mixture.
Slice buns in half.
Spread with butter and brown under broiler.
Spread with mustard.
Put sausage mixture on each bun.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown meat, seasoned with salt, pepper and onion flakes. Drain.
In a bowl, combine lettuce and tomato.
Add beans, cheese and crushed Doritos.
Add meat last!

title: chinese ting - a - ling
directions: Melt chips, stir in noodles and nuts.
Drop by spoonfuls on wax paper.
Cool.
Store in airtight containers.

title: chinese chicken noodle soup
directions: Heat chicken, salt and enough water to cover chicken to boiling in Dutch oven.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer about 40 minutes.
Cool chicken and broth quickly.
Remove chicken from broth and refrigerate broth.
Remove skin and bones from chicken and cut chicken into bite-size pieces.
Skim fat from broth. Place chicken, broth and remaining ingredients, except vermicelli, in Dutch oven.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, until carrots are crisp-tender (about 20 minutes). Stir in vermicelli and simmer until tender (about 5 minutes).

title: orange salad
directions: Use pineapple juice to dissolve Jell-O.
Place cottage cheese in bowl.
Add Jell-O, oranges, pineapple and Cool Whip.
Mix and chill.

title: creamy onion dip
directions: Thoroughly combine sour cream, salad dressing, soup mix and parsley.
Cover.
Chill until serving time.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Cook spaghetti.
Stir margarine into hot spaghetti; stir in eggs.
Make a crust of spaghetti in a buttered baking dish.
Spread cottage cheese over spaghetti.
In skillet, cook beef until brown; drain off fat.
Stir in undrained tomatoes, tomato paste, sugar, oregano and garlic salt; heat through.
Turn meat mixture into spaghetti crust.
Bake uncovered in a 350° oven for 20 minutes. Sprinkle the Mozzarella cheese on top.
Bake 5 minutes longer or until cheese melts.

title: broccoli supreme
directions: Saute onions in oleo.
Add other ingredients.
Sprinkle almonds on top.
Bake at 250° for 40 minutes.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and place in a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Top with toasted slivered almonds.
Bake at 350° until hot throughout.

title: cheese noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles.
Layer noodles and all ingredients except Parmesan cheese.
Alternate, leaving Parmesan to sprinkle on top. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Beat eggs, pumpkin, water, oil and vanilla.
Beat well.
Add sugar and beat.
Sift dry ingredients and add to pumpkin mixture, beating until well blended.
Grease and flour 4 bread pans, 9 x 5 x 3-inch.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Leave in pan about 10 minutes before turning out.
Batter will be thin.
Use ladle.
This bread freezes extremely well if packaged airtight.

title: potato soup
directions: Bake potatoes and let cool.
Scoop out potatoes.
Melt butter in heavy saucepan.	Add flour.
Stir until smooth.	Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Gradually add milk.
Cook until thick and bubbly.
Put into crock-pot.
Add potato pulp, salt, pepper, 2 pounds onions, 1/2 cup bacon and 1/2 cup cheese.
Cool in crock-pot.	Stir in sour cream.
May add more milk if too thick.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Combine flour, soda, salt, cinnamon and sugar; add remaining ingredients.
Mix all ingredients until just moistened well.
Pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
