Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 1 hour.
After removing from oven, let cool in pans on rack for 10 minutes.
Remove from pans; cool on wire rack.
Freezes well.

title: chicken, artichoke and wild rice salad
directions: Boil or grill chicken and cut into chunks.
Prepare rice, using 1/2 cup less water per box.
Cool.

title: turkey casserole
directions: Place spaghetti in bottom of baking pan.
Spread shredded turkey on top of spaghetti.
Add soup mixture on top of turkey together with water, pimento and parsley.
Add shredded cheese last.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: okra patties
directions: Combine all ingredients and add enough water to make a dough just stiff enough to shape into patties. Fry in deep fat until golden brown.

title: sausage-hamburger sandwich
directions: Fry sausage and hamburger together; drain good, then cut up cheese into chunks and let it melt into meat combination.
Stir it in good.
Put on Texas toast on sheet pan.
Put into 350° oven and just let it brown (toast) slightly.
Watch closely.

title: quick raisin bread pudding
directions: Toast raisin bread.
Spread lightly with butter or margarine. Cut toasted bread in 1/2-inch cubes.
Divide in 6 (6-ounce) custard cups.
Combine eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Stir in evaporated milk and 1 cup boiling water.
Pour mixture over toast. Place custard cups in pan of hot water and bake until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Remove cups and cool. Refrigerate.
Makes 6 servings.

title: icebox slaw
directions: Shred cabbage; chop green pepper and onions.
Mix.
Put sugar, vinegar, salt, celery seed and dry mustard in a sauce pan. Bring to a boil.
Pour over the cabbage mixture.
DO NOT STIR! Refrigerate for at least 12 hours before serving.

title: dishpan cookies
directions: Cream first five ingredients.
Sift soda and salt with flour, then mix.
Add oats, corn flakes and chocolate chips.
Drop on cookie sheet with spoon.
Bake at 350° for 8 or 10 minutes.
Will not look brown.

title: quick drop biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Combine flour and cream and stir until well mixed.
Drop biscuits by the teaspoon (for bite-size biscuits) or tablespoon (for larger biscuits) onto lightly greased baking sheets. Bake about 8 to 10 minutes.

title: barbecued shrimp
directions: Use a large flat baking pan covered with foil (seems to work best).
Put shrimp in pan.
Mix all other ingredients, except the butter, and put over shrimp.
Cut the butter in squares and lay over the top of shrimp.
Bake, covered, at 375° until done (approximately 40 minutes; stir every 10 minutes).

title: chocolate topping in microwave
directions: I use 1/2 cup semi-sweet and 1/2 cup milk chocolate (personal preference).

title: crustless bacon and egg quiche
directions: Fry or microwave bacon until crisp; crumble and set aside.
In blender, combine milk, biscuit mix, eggs, butter and pepper. Blend for 15 seconds.
Pour into greased 9-inch pie pan.
Sprinkle bacon and cheese on top of egg mixture; gently press below surface with a fork.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Let stand for 10 minutes before serving.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: sauerkraut and wieners
directions: Cut wieners in slices.
Mix sauerkraut, wieners and caraway seed.
Saute onion and bacon.
Mix well with sauerkraut and wieners and cook well.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Mix together all ingredients by hand.
Stir in 1/2 cup cut up nuts and 1 cup raisins.
Mixture will be thick.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes in a greased and floured tube pan.
Let cool before taking out of pan.

title: egg la stroda
directions: This recipe must be made the night before.
In a 3-quart, buttered, oblong casserole, place the bread which has been buttered and each slice cut into 9 pieces. Sprinkle grated cheese over bread.
Sprinkle cooked and crumbled sausage over cheese.
In a bowl, mix remaining ingredients.
Pour over sausage.
Sprinkle paprika on top.
Cover with foil and refrigerate overnight.
Cook, uncovered, at 350° until browned and puffy.
Slice into pieces and serve.
Can be frozen.
Great for company.

title: green pea casserole
directions: Mix lightly, the peas, pimento and eggs.
Top with cheese and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: soft italian cookies
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco.
Add beaten eggs and lemon juice. Cream together.
Sift baking powder into flour.
Add flour and milk alternately to creamed mixture.
Put flour on wax paper. Roll into strips and cut into pieces, about 2 1/2 inches.
Bake at 350° until done, 8 to 10 minutes.
Cookies should be soft when done.

title: noodles and crab
directions: Cook noodles in salted water
until tender; drain.
Put butter and cheese	in
top
of
double
boiler
and
heat over boiling water
until melted.
Stir in cream, pimiento and crab meat.
Mix crab sauce	with
noodles
and salt to taste.
Turn into 3-quart greased
casserole. Bake in a moderately hot oven (375°) for 25 minutes or until bubbly. Serves 6.

title: mountain fried steak
directions: Round steak's the best.
Pound the daylights out of a slice for some folks, and it won't be hard on teeth.

title: heavenly hot fudge
directions: Melt chocolate and margarine in top of double boiler.
Add sugar, a little at a time, blending thoroughly after each addition.
Add salt and evaporated milk in same manner.
Use while warm or store in refrigerator and reheat when ready to use.

title: asparagus salad
directions: Heat soup to boiling and add the water and jello.
Add soup mixture to cream cheese and then add other ingredients.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown onion and meat. Drain. Add remaining ingredients. Layer it with Doritos and cheese in casserole dish. Bake until cheese melts.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush Oreos into fine crumbs.
(Can use a food processor.) Put half crumbs in a 9 x 13-inch pan or large clay flower pot that has been buttered well.
Combine Cool Whip, cream cheese, sugar and butter in a large bowl until creamed.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Combine Karo syrup and sugar; bring to a rolling boil (don't cook too long).
Take syrup mixture and stir in peanut butter until smooth.
Pour over cereal and coconut.
Drop by a spoon onto waxed paper.

title: cowboy dinner
directions: Cook rice until tender.
Drain.
Meanwhile, cook onions in fat until tender.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer for 15 minutes; remove bay leaf and cloves.
Add rice.
Arrange 1/3 of mixture in greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Cover with 3 cut up franks.
Repeat layers until all ingredients are used.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Uncover and bake another 15 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: canned apple pie filling
directions: Cook sauce ingredients in saucepan until bubbly.
Add lemon juice.
Fill quart jars with apples and pour sauce over apple to cover.
Seal and process 20 minutes in boiling water bath.

title: foolproof dark chocolate fudge
directions: In heavy saucepan over low heat, melt chips with sweetened condensed milk and salt.
Remove from heat; stir in walnuts and vanilla.
Spread evenly into wax paper-lined 8 or 9-inch square pan.
Chill for 2 hours or until firm.
Turn fudge onto cutting board; peel off paper and cut into squares.
Store loosely covered at room temperature.
Makes about 2 pounds.

title: oreo cake
directions: Crush Oreo cookies and melt 1/2 stick of margarine.
Mix and put in a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Freeze 30 minutes or until frozen. Soften the ice cream.
Spread on the Oreo crust.
Freeze until firm.
Mix the chocolate, margarine, evaporated milk and sugar. Boil for 4 minutes.
Remove from stove and stir in vanilla.
Cool. Spread on top of the ice cream.
Sprinkle nuts on top of cooked mixture.
Freeze.
Set it out for awhile before serving.

title: almond cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add egg yolks and flavoring; beat thoroughly.
Add flour, salt and almonds.
Mix until blended.
Form into a roll about 2 inches in diameter. Wrap in wax paper and chill for several hours.
Slice and bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: barbecued beef
directions: Brown meat until crumbly, but not hard.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer about 30 minutes.
Serve on buns.

title: zesty italian wontons
directions: Cook sausage and onion over medium heat until sausage is brown, stirring to break meat into small pieces.
Drain well and cool completely.
Stir in cheeses and parsley.

title: egg salad cheese spread
directions: Combine first five ingredients in mixing bowl.
Season with salt and pepper.
Yields 3 cups.

title: porcupine meat balls
directions: Combine meat, rice, onion, 1/4 cup water, salt, and pepper. Shape into 15 one inch balls.

title: taco salad dip
directions: Mix beef, beans, tomato sauce, taco seasoning, onion, bell pepper and pepper sauce.
Cover tightly and microwave 3 minutes. Spread in microwavable pie plate.
Cover and microwave 5 minutes. Top with sour cream, cheese and green onions.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: deer jerky
directions: Mix all the ingredients.
Place meat in sauce and let it marinate for 24 hours.
After 24 hours, take it out and dry with paper towels.
Place in a dehydrator or in oven on low for 6 to 8 hours.

title: eggplant patties
directions: Pare and cube eggplant and cook in water 5 minutes.
Drain and mash; add to the other ingredients.
Mix well and shape into 8 patties.
Fry in hot oil until golden brown on each side.

title: cranberry jello
directions: Chop cranberries (a few at a time) in blender.
Chop apples (a few at a time) in blender.
In mixing bowl, mix cherry Jell-O, sugar, orange juice and nuts all together.
Chill.
Serves 8.

title: festive fruit punch
directions: Combine all ingredients into a punch bowl.

title: unbaked cookies
directions: Mix oil, sugar, raisins and nuts.
To this mixture add 1/2 flour mixture.
The hot applesauce mixture stirring add rest of flour mixture.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Use 9 x 12 loaf pan, greased and floured.
To ice: glaze with butter frosting. Sprinkle with cinnamon and swirl with knife.

title: fruit topped cake
directions: Bake cake and let cool completely.

title: squash croquettes
directions: Combine first five ingredients, mixing well.
Stir in flour. Drop by tablespoonfuls in hot oil.
Cook until brown, turning once; drain.

title: hot dog relish
directions: Grind all vegetables through food chopper.
Mix well.
Put into a crock or plastic container (not metal).
Sprinkle 1/2 cup salt over this.
Cover and let stand overnight.
Drain and rinse. The best way to rinse without losing part of it is to put it into a cloth sack.
You can run water through and squeeze until it is rinsed good.
Put into a large pan.
Add all other ingredients and cook to a boil.
Boil for 3 minutes.
Pour into jars and seal.

title: sheraton halibut
directions: Combine all ingredients and place over halibut in a shallow baking dish. Crush Wheat Thins crackers over the top. Bake at 425° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: easy cobbler
directions: Pour pie filling in 9 x 13 pan. Sprinkle dry cake mix over pie filling. Melt butter and drizzle over cake mix. Bake at 350° until bubbly. Serve with ice cream.

title: `over-night' layered salad
directions: Layer above ingredients, in order listed.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar; add 1 egg at a time, beating well after each addition.
Dissolve soda in hot water and add to buttermilk.
Add buttermilk and flour with salt alternately.
Add vanilla; beat well.
Pour in floured tube pan with wax paper liner on bottom.
Bake 1 hour and 35 minutes at 300°.

title: breakfast casserole(serves 6 to 8)
directions: Mix together.
Put into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Refrigerate for 12 hours.
Bake for 50 minutes at 350°.

title: elephant stew
directions: Clean, smooth skin, bone and dice 1 medium elephant.
If more stew is required, add one rabbit.

title: midwestern chowder
directions: Boil vegetables separately, simmer 10 minutes (boil until vegetables are cooked but not mushy).
Shred cheese.
Make a cream sauce with butter, flour and milk; stir in cheese until melted. Add cream-style corn and vegetables including broth.
Heat but do not boil.
Add hot dogs.
Garnish with parsley.

title: brunch cheese puffs
directions: Bake patty shells according to package directions. Discard unbaked dough from center. Save caps.

title: lasagne
directions: Boil noodles 15 minutes in salted water.
Beat eggs and Ricotta cheese.
Cover bottom of greased glass pan with spaghetti sauce, next layer noodles, more sauce, Ricotta mixture, then Mozzarella cheese and crumbled Italian sausage.
Repeat layer of noodles, sauce, cheeses and sausage; top with noodles and sauce and sprinkle grated cheese over.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes.

title: potato and pork chop bake
directions: Slice potatoes and put in a well-greased large Pyrex or stainless steel pan.
Cover potatoes with pork chops.
Mix tomato soup with the water into a bowl.
Add the spices and pour all of this liquid over the potatoes and meat and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: ham chowder
directions: Combine corn, tomatoes, broth, celery, salt and hot pepper sauce.
Heat to boiling. Reduce heat.
Melt butter and stir in flour and milk.
Cook and stir until mixture thickens and comes to a boil. Stir in tomato mixture. At this point, you may not want to use all of the liquid.
Add cheese, green pepper and ham. Cook over low heat until cheese melts and mixture is heated through.

title: cowboy biscuits
directions: Mix together in one bowl, then add to this same bowl 1/2 to 1 cup more flour and knead.
Pinch off and place in greased iron skillet, close together.
Let rise about 30 minutes to 1 hour. Bake at 400° until golden brown.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all in a jar; shake.
Refrigerate.
Especially good on chicken or rabbit.

title: cavalier's brown sugar cookies
directions: Cream lard and sugar.
Dissolve soda in boiling water; pour over sugar mixture.
Stir and cool to room temperature.
Add vanilla.
Add flour until dough seems ready for rolling.
Chill dough.
Roll very thin; shape as desired.
Place on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for about 10 minutes.

title: ham and cheese strata
directions: Cut 12 rounds from bread and set aside.
Fix scraps of bread on bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Place cheese slices on top of bread.
Add layer of broccoli, then ham.
Arrange rounds of bread on top.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over bread. Cover.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 1 hour.

title: carnation green garden salad
directions: Chill until firm.
This amount fits well in my 3 1/2 cup copper ring mold.

title: cottage cheese kolaczki
directions: Cut margarine into flour as for pie dough.
Add cottage cheese and mix well.
Knead until fairly smooth.
Cover and refrigerate 2 hours.
Roll out 1/8-inch thick on well floured board.
Cut into 2 or 3-inch squares.
Put a small teaspoonful of filling in center of each.
Pinch together opposite corners.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: old fashion tea cakes
directions: Cream sugar, oleo, milk, egg and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients and mix.
Knead until easy to handle.
Roll out thin. Cut and bake on cookie sheet at 425° until done.

title: chicken breasts casserole
directions: Brown chicken which has been lightly salted and peppered in butter in a large skillet.
When brown, remove and set aside.
Add remaining ingredients
to skillet and cook 5 minutes, while stirring.
Place chicken in a baking dish and pour sauce over it. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: t~e~g's perfect rice
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Take long grain rice and rinse 5 times until the water is clear. Drain water and set rice aside.

Using a large skillet (preferably an iron skillet), heat butter until melted, and then reducing heat to medium. Place prepared rice into skillet with butter. Add onion. Cook rice and onions on medium heat for 2 minutes. Add chicken stock. Add salt. Add pepper. Cover and place skillet in 400° oven for exactly 18 minutes. Remove and serve.

title: harvard beets
directions: In a small saucepan, combine sugar, cornstarch and salt; slowly pour in vinegar; add margarine and minced onion.
Over medium heat, cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Reduce heat to low and add beets.
Cook until heated, stirring occasionally.

title: molasses fruit cookies
directions: Cream sauce, shortening and eggs.
Add balance of ingredients; mix well.
Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet or roll and cut. Store in refrigerator and bake as desired.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: barbecued beans
directions: Brown and season beef, onion and green pepper.
Add brown sugar and catsup.
Add beans.
Bake in a large Pyrex bowl for 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.

title: banana ice cream
directions: Combine 1/2 cup sugar, gelatin and 1/2 teaspoon salt in saucepan.
Stir in light cream over low heat until gelatin and sugar are dissolved.
Chill until partially set.
Blend in bananas, yolks, lemon juice and vanilla.
Whip cream.
Fold into gelatin.
Beat egg whites to soft peaks, gradually add remaining sugar, beating to stiff peaks.
Fold into banana mixture.
Pour into large freezer tray.
Freeze firm.
Makes 2 quarts.

title: foil chicken
directions: Place prepared mushrooms in bottom of foil bag.
Season chicken with spices and place on top of mushrooms.
Top with butter/margarine, garlic and white wine (or water).
Seal bag very tightly, making sure it will not leak.
Place on baking sheet. Bake at 350° for 40-45 minutes (depending on your oven and on thickness of chicken). Spoon liquid in bag over chicken.

title: impossible coconut pie
directions: Grease and flour pan.
Combine ingredients; pour into pan. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Pie makes own crust.

title: ice cream cookie
directions: Put a scoop of ice cream on each of four cookies.
Top with remaining cookies; gently press together.
Roll edge in chocolate chips.
Wrap in plastic wrap and freeze.
Serves 4.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: In a small pot, put sugar, cocoa, margarine and milk.
Bring to a boil.
Let boil for 2 1/2 minutes.
Remove from heat; add vanilla and peanut butter.
Stir in oatmeal.
Drop on wax paper. Makes 15 to 20 cookies.

title: watermelon syrup
directions: Cut inside into cubes.
Boil seeds and all for about 20 minutes.
Strain.
Boil liquid until consistency of syrup.

title: best in the world cake and icing
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift dry ingredients and add remaining ingredients. Mix well. Bake in a well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan for 40 to 45 minutes. Cool for 20 minutes before icing.

title: no-cook divinity
directions: Combine frosting mix (dry), corn syrup, vanilla and boiling water in small mixer bowl.
Beat on high speed until stiff peaks form (about 5 minutes).
Transfer to larger bowl and gradually blend in confectioners sugar on low speed.
Stir in nuts.
Drop by spoonful onto wax paper.
When outside of candy feels firm, turn over, allow to dry at least 12 hours.
Store in airtight container.

title: christmas fruit cookies
directions: Stir together flour, soda and salt.
Cream shortening and sugar together.
Add eggs and mix thoroughly.
Add flour mixture to creamed mixture alternately with milk.
Stir in nuts and fruit. Drop by teaspoonfuls into greased baking sheets.
Bake in a 400° gas oven for 10 to 12 minutes or until done.
Yields 4 dozen cookies.

title: sausage balls #1
directions: Knead all ingredients together.
Form into balls and bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: lima bean casserole
directions: Cook lima beans in 2-quart saucepan.
Sear the bacon and cook green pepper (sliced) and onions until soft.
In greased casserole, place a layer of beans sprinkled with onions, small pieces of bacon and sparingly with salt and pepper.
Repeat until all is used.
Over this pour the milk and bake in preheated casserole over medium heat for 1/2 hour.

title: meat marinade
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Marinate meat 4 to 18 hours.
May be used as basting sauce or for gravies.

title: tasty apricot chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Season the chicken with salt, pepper and garlic salt.
Set aside.

title: mock bake steak
directions: Combine well.
Pat onto cookie sheet to desired thickness. Score into pieces the size you want.
Set overnight in refrigerator or freezer.
When ready to fix, roll in flour. Brown in skillet.
Place in baking pan.
Pour mushroom soup over meat.
Bake in 350° oven 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: play dough
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large pot. Cook and stir until play dough leaves the sides of the pot. Knead as soon as it is cool enough to handle. Store in a tightly sealed container. The play dough will last for several months.
Keep a supply of old cookie cutters, an old rolling pin, etc. handy to used with the play dough.

title: potato refrigerator rolls
directions: Place into greased loaf pan (1 large or 2 small).
Bake at 375° (55 - 60 minutes for large and 30 - 35 minutes for small).

title: norma's hot sauce
directions: Drain tomatoes and Ro-Tel.
Put in blender.
Cut peppers in small pieces and add.
Put in cumin, onion powder and garlic salt and mix on low setting for about 3 seconds.
Mix only until blended together, not to a liquid consistency.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Keeps in refrigerator 1 week.

title: buttermilk brownies
directions: Boil first 3 ingredients together; add powdered sugar, vanilla and nuts, if desired.

title: shrimp mozambique
directions: In a large, heavy skillet combine oil, butter, garlic, parsley, chili peppers and Assafroa over high heat until butter melts and garlic sizzles.
Add shrimp and stir briskly until nearly done.
Add juice and wine; toss a few more times and remove from heat.
Drizzle pan sauces over 3 to 4 shrimp in a shallow dish and serve with fresh Portuguese bread for dipping and a crisp, new white wine.
(This recipe also works very well substituting fresh, whole, scrubbed littlenecks for the shrimp.)

title: orange julius
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients in blender.
Add half of cubes at a time.
Mix and put into containers.
Can be used immediately or frozen in individual cups for later on.
Just zap 20 to
30 seconds in microwave, if frozen.

title: chocolate bread pudding(with custard sauce)
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Butter an 8-inch square baking pan or 8 X 3 souffle dish or cake pan and dust with 1 tablespoon of the sugar.
In a medium saucepan, bring cream to a simmer.
Place chocolate in a food processor and chop finely, 15 to 20 seconds. With the machine on pour in the hot cream.
As soon as mixture is smooth, add 1/3 cup of sugar and egg yolks, one at a time.
Add butter and vanilla.
Process just until smooth.

title: spanish rice and beef
directions: Place ground beef in a 3-quart glass casserole.
Cook using microwave 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add remaining ingredients and stir well.
Cook with microwave 21 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Recipe yields 6.

title: millionaire salad
directions: Mix Jell-O and hot water, stirring until dissolved.
Cool and add Cool Whip.
Add pie mix and crushed pineapple.
Let stand in refrigerator.

title: green enchiladas
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet, stirring until crumbly.
Season and set aside to cool.
Combine the next 6 ingredients in double boiler, heating until Velveeta melts.
Mix Longhorn cheese and onion with ground beef.
Soften tortillas, one at a time, in hot oil in skillet.
Spoon 1 or 2 tablespoons of ground beef mixture on each tortilla and roll up.
Place in an 8 x 10-inch baking dish.
Top with cheese sauce.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: zuppa de pesee with angel hair pasta(italian fish soup)
directions: Cooking Time:
1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: ruth luck's sloppy joes
directions: Brown ground beef and onions.
Add all other ingredients. Simmer 15 minutes.
Serve on buns.

title: baked hash browns
directions: Bake for 50 to 60 minutes at 350°.
Before done, sprinkle paprika on the last 10 minutes.

title: quick sweet and sour chicken
directions: Cut 4 bones chicken
breasts
into 1 inch pieces.
Marinate with soy sauce, oil and wine for 1 hour.
Make a batter of pancake mixture, egg and
milk.
Add
chicken to coat, and deep fry. Drain.

title: hot buttered rum
directions: Cook in crock-pot for 2 hours on high.
Serve warm.
Keeps good in refrigerator.
Can be warmed in cup or more at a time.

title: yummie chicken
directions: Shake chicken in flour.
Beat 1 egg.
Dip each piece in egg . Combine crumbs, salt, cheese and flakes.
Coat each piece.

title: sensational double layer pumpkin pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, 1 tablespoon milk and sugar with a wire whisk.
Stir in Cool Whip; spread on crust.
Chill.

title: hobo dinner
directions: You will need 1 (12 x 15-inch) piece of aluminum foil.

title: no knead refrigerator rolls
directions: Mix boiling water, 1/2 cup sugar, shortening and salt.
Cool to lukewarm.
Soften yeast in 1/4 cup lukewarm water and add 1 teaspoon sugar.
Add this to the first mixture.
Add eggs and flour.
Mix thoroughly, but do not knead.
Cover and put in refrigerator for overnight.

title: cherry crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Mix flour, margarine and nuts by hand. Put in buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cook 40 to 45 minutes until brown.
Beat cream cheese until creamy.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla and powdered sugar.
Blend in Cool Whip.
Blend with mixer for 3 minutes.
Spread over cool cake.
Top with cherry pie filling. Chill.

title: german goulash
directions: Combine all
ingredients, juice also.
Bring to a boil; turn down
heat	and
simmer
until potatoes are done.
Remove from heat.
Serve with your favorite salad and bread.

title: elegant steak and rice
directions: Cut steak into thin strips.
In a large skillet, brown meat in oil using high heat.
Add onions.
Saute until tender-crisp. Blend soup, sherry, liquid from mushrooms and garlic salt.
Pour over steak.
Add mushrooms.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 1 hour or until steak is tender.
(Or, transfer to casserole. Cover and bake at 350°.) Serve over rice.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chicken with peaches and sherry sauce(serves 2)
directions: In medium skillet, brown chicken in 2 teaspoons butter.
In medium saucepan, saute onion in butter for 2 minutes.
Add peaches to onion mixture and stir.
Add sugar, Worcestershire sauce and sherry to peaches and onions; stir.

title: colcannon
directions: Cook potatoes and rutabagas in lightly salted water until tender, about 25 minutes. In meantime, blanch cabbage in boiling water for 4 minutes; drain. When potatoes and rutabagas are done, drain and return to pan. Shake over low heat until they are dry. Mash potatoes and rutabagas in 4 tablespoons butter and 1/3 cup half and half. Add more half and half if necessary to make a thick smooth puree. Season with salt and pepper. Melt 2 tablespoons of the remaining butter in a large ovenproof skillet over medium heat. Add cabbage and cook, stirring constantly, for 2 minutes. Stir in mashed potatoes and scallions. Dot top with remaining butter and bake in preheated oven at 350° for 15 minutes.
Serve immediately.

title: old cucumber pickles
directions: Peel and core cucumbers.
Soak 24 hours in a gallon of water and lime.
Wash and soak 24 hours in 2 gallons of water and alum. Wash and soak 6 hours in two gallons of water mixed with ginger. Drain and soak 3 to 4 hours in remaining ingredients.
Boil 1 hour; bottle and seal in this last solution.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix well; put in 9 x 13-inch dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
May freeze leftovers.

title: noodle dumplings for soup
directions: Beat eggs; add flour.
Stir in Cream of Wheat.
Let set for 20 to 30 minutes.
Drop by small pieces into boiling broth or stock. (Dough is easy to stir when Cream of Wheat is first stirred into eggs, but becomes much stiffer as dough sets.)

title: cold oven pound cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add flour alternately with milk.
Pour into a greased and floured tube pan. Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: tuna salad
directions: Bring peas to boil; drain.
Chill.
Mix ingredients.
Add noodles just before serving.
Toss well.
Serve with Curry Dressing.

title: lime jello congealed salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill thoroughly.

title: sausage balls
directions: Combine
all
together and roll in balls.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: potato latkes
directions: Shred onion on large holes of grater.
Shred potatoes on small holes.
Drain potatoes and onion, pressing out liquids.
Stir together potatoes, onion, egg, flour, salt and pepper.
Heat 1-inch of cooking oil on medium setting in a 10-inch skillet. Drop mixture by 1 tablespoon at a time.
Cook 2 to 4 minutes, until golden brown, turning once.
Drain on paper towels.

title: mushroom beef patties
directions: Mix together first 6 ingredients.
Shape into patties.
Can be any size you want.
Quickly brown lightly on both sides using high heat.
Place patties into a baking dish and pour can of mushrooms over top.
Mix mushroom soup and milk together.
Pour over meat. Cover and bake in oven for 25 to 30 minutes on 350°.
Take out and let cool for about 5 minutes.

title: brown sugar drops
directions: Mix well shortening, sugar and eggs; stir in buttermilk. Combine with sifted dry ingredients.
Chill dough.
Drop spoonfuls on greased baking sheet about 2 inches apart.
Bake in hot oven (400°) 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: golf ball stew
directions: Combine all ingredients in crock-pot.
Cook on low 4 to 8 hours.

title: pumpkin pie squares
directions: In bowl, mix flour, 1 cup sugar and oats.
Cut in margarine until blended.
Press 3 cups of mixture into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake in a 350° oven for 12 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: watergate salad
directions: Put pineapple in a large bowl.
Add cherries, marshmallows and pecans.
Sprinkle pudding over mixture and fold in Cool Whip. Chill.

title: low-fat oven fried chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Dip chicken in egg whites.
Roll dipped chicken in crushed corn flakes.
Place on baking sheet pre-sprayed with Pam.
Salt and pepper to taste and bake 30 to 35 minutes. You may want to put some seasonings like paprika in with the corn flakes.
Contains 1 gram of fat.

title: lucky charm bars
directions: Grease 9 x 9 inch pan. Place margarine and marshmallows in large, microwaveable bowl; microwave on high for 1 to 3 minutes uncovered. Stir after each each minute until mixture is melted and smooth. Add cereal and mix until well coated. Press into greased pan. Let set until firm. Cut into bars.

title: zesty meat balls
directions: Combine meat, chopped onion, oatmeal, pepper, 1/2 cup ketchup and salt; mix well.
Shape into medium size meat balls.
Place in large baking dish.
Combine 1/2 cup ketchup, vinegar, brown sugar and Worcestershire sauce.
Bring to a boil.
Pour over meat balls and bake in a 300° oven until brown and well done, about 35 to 40 minutes.

title: frozen cucumbers
directions: Cover the sliced vegetables with water and the salt. Refrigerate for 24 hours; drain.
Pour over mixture of sugar, vinegar and celery seed.
Let stand in refrigerator for 48 hours. Stir and freeze.
Serve in slushy to thawed state.
Keeps well.

title: whiskey pie
directions: In a saucepan, mix sugar, Karo, soda and salt. Bring to a boil. Remove from heat and cool. Stir in the butter, beaten eggs, flour, orange peel and whiskey. Pour into unbaked pie crust. Bake at 325° for 50 minutes or until firm in the center.

title: lemon-garlic olives
directions: Drain olives, reserving brine.
Rinse olives and drain well. Layer olives, oregano sprigs, garlic, lemon wedges and peppercorns in jar.
Add lemon juice to jar.
Add enough reserved brine to fill jar.
Place lid on jar and shake well.
Let olives marinate at least 1 week in refrigerator before serving.

title: cucumbers in sour cream
directions: Refrigerate until served.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: easy strawberry cream cheese pie
directions: Drain strawberries, reserving 1/4 cup liquid.
Beat cream cheese, liquid, strawberries, sugar and vanilla until smooth.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Spoon into crust.
Refrigerate several hours or freeze for faster set up.
Garnish with a strawberry fan.
Serves 8 to 10 people.

title: coconut pie
directions: Cream eggs and sugar together.
Melt margarine.
Mix with eggs and sugar.
Add milk, vanilla and 3/4 of coconut.
Pour in unbaked 9-inch pie shell.
Sprinkle with remaining coconut.
Cook at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: icebox cookies
directions: Cream sugar, butter and egg together. Add remaining ingredients.
Mix together well.
Make ball and wrap in wax paper. Chill.

title: hot cocoa for a crowd
directions: Stir all but milk together and boil gently over heat for 2 minutes.
Add milk.
Stir and heat, but don't boil.
Beat with rotary beater and garnish with whipped cream, marshmallow cream or marshmallows.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients until pudding mix is thoroughly absorbed. Add marshmallows and nuts. Mix well. Add additional nuts on top to decorate. Refrigerate until chilled.

title: creamed broccoli
directions: Mix Cream Sauce with the cooked broccoli.
Put the stuffing (cook like package says) on the top and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: sugared walnuts
directions: Cook sugar, honey and water to soft ball stage.
Add walnuts and vanilla.
Stir until coated, creamy and thick.
Pour onto waxed paper and break into individual pieces.

title: the great pumpkin cookie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine flour, oats, soda, cinnamon and salt; set aside.
Cream butter; gradually add sugars, beating until light and fluffy.
Add egg and vanilla; mix well.
Alternate additions of dry ingredients and pumpkin, mixing well.
Stir in morsels.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Place pineapple in casserole dish. Sprinkle sugar and flour over pineapple. Add Cheddar cheese. Toss crackers in margarine and spread over cheese. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook chicken in water.
Reserve broth!
Cut chicken into bite-size pieces.
Melt margarine and saute onion and green pepper until soft.
Add chicken, chili powder, tomatoes, salt and pepper. Meanwhile, cook spaghetti in broth (add water, if needed). Drain.
Mix spaghetti into sauce and simmer for 15 minutes.
Layer spaghetti and cheese in an 8 x 11-inch baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes or so.

title: layered lettuce salad
directions: In a small bowl, stir together first three ingredients for dressing.
Set aside.
Layer remaining ingredients in a large bowl.
Pour on dressing.
Refrigerate.
Toss just before serving. Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: crab dip
directions: Mix ingredients.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan and bake uncovered at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: people puppy chow
directions: Melt the first 3 ingredients together on low heat in large saucepan.
Remove from heat and fold in Chex cereal.
When well mixed, pour mixture into a brown paper bag with 1 of the cups of powdered sugar on the bottom and 1 on the top of the mixture.
Fold top of bag securely; shake well.
Pour mixture into bowl; store in an airtight container or in the freezer.
Serves an entire party.

title: teriyaki glaze
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: crab alfredo
directions: In skillet saute onion in butter until tender. Add mushrooms cook and stir 3 minutes, or until tender. Add crab. Reduce heat cook for 10 minutes or until heated through. Serve over fettucine.

title: cream cheese eggs
directions: Beat cream cheese and cream until smooth.
Gradually beat in sugar, then blend in chocolate.
Stir in vanilla, rum, salt and 1 cup nuts.
Press into lightly greased 8-inch square pan and cover top with remaining nuts.
Mark in 64 pieces (about 1-inch squares) and chill for several hours or overnight.
Makes 1 pound.

title: pleasant hill corn pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease a shallow 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Combine butter, flour, sugar and salt in a bowl; mix until smooth.
Stir in eggs.
Stir in corn and milk.
Pour into prepared dish.
Place in a larger baking pan and pour boiling water into a larger pan halfway up sides.
Bake 30 minutes; stir.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes more, or until a knife inserted in center of pudding comes out clean.
Cool 10 minutes before serving.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In bag, place spices, cheese, parsley and crumbs.
Coat chicken by shaking a few pieces at a time.
Oil a shallow roasting pan; pour in water and arrange chicken pieces. Sprinkle chicken with oil and melted margarine and bake, uncovered, for 45 minutes.
Pour wine over chicken.
Lower oven heat to 325°.
Cover pan with foil; bake 15 minutes longer. Remove foil, raise oven heat to 350° and bake 10 minutes longer.

title: fresh peach pie
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients in a saucepan.
Boil until thick and clear, then add the 4 tablespoons of peach gelatin.
Let cool. Meanwhile, mix together the 1/2 cup sugar and cream cheese.
Cream together until smooth and spread in bottom of cooled pie crust. Combine the cooled gelatin mixture and the sliced peaches.
Place on top of the cream cheese mixture in pie crust.
Cover with Cool Whip and refrigerate for a few hours before serving.

title: milkless, eggless, butterless cake
directions: Boil together for 5 minutes the first 4 ingredients.
When cool, add remaining ingredients.
Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: donna's pot cajun shrimp boil
directions: In large pot, bring sausage and potatoes to boil.
While boiling, add enough Old Bay to cover top of water.
Boil for 10 minutes and add corn.
Add hot sauce to taste and boil 5 minutes. Add shrimp and bring to a boil.
When it begans to boil, remove from heat and let stand 5 minutes.
Drain and pour all ingredients onto large platter.
Sprinkle with Old Bay, if desired and serve with garlic bread.

title: zucchini muffins(from the parsonage kitchen)
directions: Gently mix together eggs, oil and brown sugar.
Combine flour, salt and baking soda.
Stir gently together the egg mixture, flour mixture, zucchini, vanilla and nuts.
Spoon into well-greased muffin pans (or cupcake liners).
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Remove from pans to cool.
Yield:
24 muffins.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Beat sugar and cream cheese until creamy. Add pineapple. Fold in whipped topping. Pour in either a baked pie shell or a graham cracker crust. Chill.

title: babysitter slop
directions: In a large saucepan, prepare macaroni and cheese as directions indicate.
While pasta is boiling, cut up hot dogs and boil along with pasta.
Drain water and put ingredients back into saucepan. Add cheese(s).
Stir well.
Serve hot.
Makes about 5 to 6 (1 cup) servings.
Yum Yum!

title: cheese grits
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In large pot, bring water to a rolling boil before adding grits. Reduce heat to low and stir while they thicken. When mixture is thick, stir in the eggs followed by margarine, cheese, seasoning salt and hot sauce. Stir until cheese has melted. Pour mixture in 9 x 13 baking dish. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Cut grits into squares and serve.

title: bread bowl(bread machine)
directions: After dough or manual cycle is completed in bread machine, and before the baking cycle begins, remove the dough from the machine. Turn dough out onto a lightly floured surface and carefully form into a ball without punching down.
Place onto a greased cookie sheet and let rise about 1 hour until double in size.
Brush with beaten egg and bake at 375° for 25 to 35 minutes until golden brown.
Let cool.
Hollow out cooled bread like a pumpkin, reserving "lid" to put back on.
Fill with your favorite meat, soup or whatever.
Replace the top.
Serve and enjoy.

title: broccoli classic
directions: Cook spaghetti in rapidly boiling salted water for 6 minutes. Add fresh broccoli and continue to cook 5 more minutes. Drain. Place spaghetti and broccoli on platter. Toss with oil and butter. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: cousin linda's oreo cookie cake
directions: Grind Oreos; set aside 1/4 cup in a bowl. Mix the rest of the ground Oreos with the melted butter. Pat out into a 9 x 13 baking dish.

title: marinated chicken wings
directions: Marinate overnight.
Baste wings and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Marinate on each side; keep basting.

title: hot fudge sundae cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In greased square pan, 9 x 9 x 2-inches, stir together flour, sugar, 2 tablespoons cocoa, 2 teaspoons baking powder and salt.
Mix in milk, oil and vanilla with a fork until smooth.
Stir in nuts; spread evenly in a pan.
Sprinkle with brown sugar and 1/4 cup cocoa.
Pour hot water over the batter.
Bake 40 minutes.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Spoon into dessert dishes or cut into squares.
Top with ice cream and spoon sauce over each serving.
Makes 9 servings.

title: company corn pudding
directions: Combine ingredients and pour into 2-quart greased casserole. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix ingredients together and drop by spoonfuls into hot grease.
Deep fry until golden brown, turning when brown on one side.
Drain on paper towel.

title: cheesy chicken
directions: Pound boned and skinned chicken breasts with mallet until flattened.
Slather the pounded breasts with sour cream on both sides, then sprinkle on side with garlic salt.
Coat them with crushed Cheez-Its.
Roll up in jelly roll fashion and place, seam side down, in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Drizzle with melted margarine.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: crisp onion-roasted potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
In shallow baking dish, thoroughly blend all ingredients except potatoes.
Add potatoes and turn to coat.
Bake, stirring occasionally, 60 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Garnish with chopped parsley.

title: hot dog chili for a crowd
directions: Use a 20-qt pot or larger.
Dissolve ground meat with about 2 qt. water to separate and brown.
Add tomato sauce and bring to a boil.

title: orange muffins
directions: Combine all ingredients in order given, mixing just until incorporated. Do not beat. Bake in well-greased muffin pans in 400° oven for 20 minutes. Makes 12 muffins.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Beat softened butter, sugar and egg in a large bowl at high speed for 3 minutes.
Blend in vanilla.
Stir in flour to make a stiff dough.
Wrap in wax paper and chill 3 hours or until firm. Roll dough one quarter at a time to 1/4-inch thickness on a lightly floured surface.
Cut cookies out with desired shapes and place 1-inch apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Decorate as you wish.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.
Remove to wire rack to cool.

title: seeded parmesan pull-aparts
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Melt oleo in an 8 or 9-inch round cake pan.
Sprinkle onions and seeds over oleo.
Cut biscuits into fourths.
Put cheese into a paper sack and add a handful of biscuit pieces at a time, shaking well to cover.
Arrange in pan. Sprinkle with rest of cheese in bag, if any.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 18 minutes or until golden.
Invert on serving plate.

title: honeybun cake
directions: Mix the cake mix, oil, sour cream and eggs.
Pour half the batter in a greased and floured loaf pan.
Mix the brown sugar, cinnamon and chopped pecans and sprinkle on top of the batter. Pour the rest of the batter on top. Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes. Remove from the oven.
Mix the powdered sugar, milk and vanilla.
Pour this over the cake while the cake is still hot.

title: pot roast
directions: Flour both sides of roast.
Cook in large pot with a little grease.
Turn roast when gets brown on both sides.
Leave in pan. Cover with water and put in cut up onion.
Turn down; cook slow about 2 hours or until tender.
Take roast out.
Put in package onion soup mix and 2 tablespoons cornstarch that's been dissolved in water.
It will thicken, gravy.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix oil, sugar and eggs.
Sift flour and dry ingredients together, then add to oil mixture.
Add carrots and nuts.
Bake 1 hour at 350° in 2 pans, size 9-inch or 1 tube pan.

title: ratatouille
directions: In 1/4 cup oil, saute onion and garlic until soft.
Add remaining oil, eggplant and zucchini and cook about 5 minutes, stirring frequently.
Add tomatoes, peppers, salt, thyme, pepper and basil.
Cover and simmer over low heat, about 20 minutes, then uncover and cook until the juices are reduced.
Serve either hot or cold.
Serves 6.

title: hot brownies with brandy-ice cream sauce
directions: After baking brownies, time this so it can be served while they are still warm.
Whisk the brandy into softened vanilla ice cream.
Scoop warm brownies into dessert dishes and top with cold sauce.

title: corn casserole dish
directions: Melt butter and stir in flour and sugar.
Add beaten eggs and corn mixture.
Mix all together.
Salt and pepper.
Put in 13 x 9-inch baking dish or round pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
You can remove from oven after 45 minutes and add grated Colby and Cheddar cheese on top.
Return to oven and cook until cheese is melted.
May double recipe for large group.
Makes a 9 x 13-inch dish.

title: spaghetti
directions: Lightly brown
meat
in skillet.
Add to other ingredients in a
large
saucepan.
Cook
over
medium heat to a slow boil.
Stir occasionally.
Reduce heat and simmer for 2 hours on lowest heat. Stir occasionally until done.

title: turtle pie
directions: Bake pie shells and cool completely.
In pan, melt margarine. Mix in coconut and nuts.
Stir until coconut is toasty brown. Remove from heat and set aside.
In mixing bowl, mix cream cheese and sweetened condensed milk.
Add Cool Whip.
Spoon layer of Cool Whip mixture in each pie shell; sprinkle layer of coconut over Cool Whip mix.
Put caramel topping on next.
Repeat.
Each pie should have 2 layers mixture.
Chill.
Can be frozen.

title: ginger beer
directions: *Juices of other fruits; e.g., 2 or 3 limes or lemons, diluted with enough water to make 8 cups may be substituted for pineapple.

title: taco pie
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Add taco seasoning.
Crush corn chips and spread in large round pie dish.
Top with ground beef mixture.
Spread sour cream over this, then add refried beans. Top with the chopped onion, tomato and lettuce.
Then cover with shredded cheese.
Keep refrigerated.

title: chicken bake
directions: Shred chicken.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Mix mushroom soup mix and sour cream.
Pour over chicken.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Cream together shortening, sugar and eggs.
Sift in flour, cream of tarter, salt and soda.
Blend well. Roll the dough into balls the size of small walnuts.
Roll balls in mixture of 3 Tbsp. sugar and 2 tsp. cinnamon.
Bake 8-10 minutes at 375 degrees on ungreased cookie sheet.

title: dumplings
directions: Mix slightly beaten egg and just enough milk to make a stiff dough.
Divide into 3 parts and roll out 1/4-inch on a floured surface.
Cut into squares; put in single layer on floured cookie sheet and freeze.
When frozen, put in plastic bags with flour.

title: easy ice cream pie
directions: Line a Pyrex dish with ice cream sandwiches and cover with Cool Whip.
Return to freezer until ready to serve. Cut into squares and put chocolate syrup on top.

title: bourbon balls
directions: Mix together.
Form by teaspoonful into balls.
Roll in powdered sugar.
Store in tight container in cool place.

title: microwaved hot turkey salad
directions: In a 2-quart casserole, combine turkey, water chestnuts, pimientos, almonds, mushrooms, lemon juice and mayonnaise.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Top with cheese and onions.
Microwave, covered, on High for 8 to 10 minutes, giving dish a 1/4 turn after 4 minutes.
Serve hot.
Serves 6.

title: creamed potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Saute onions, green pepper and celery in butter until soft.
Stir in flour.
Add cream slowly, stirring constantly, and simmer until mix thickens.
Stir in salt and pepper.

title: preacher's cookies
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients and let it come to a boil.
Boil 1 minute.
Pour over the remaining ingredients that have been thoroughly mixed.
Mix well and drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper to cool.
Makes about 30 cookies.

title: adams county apple cake
directions: In mixing bowl, combine flour, baking powder, 2 cups sugar, oil, eggs, orange juice, salt and vanilla. Beat until thoroughly combined. In another bowl, toss apples with cinnamon and remaining sugar. Spread 1/3 of the batter in a greased 10-inch tube pan. Cover with half of the apples. Repeat the layers.
Spoon remaining batter over the top. Bake in a 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours.
Cool in pan 20 minutes.

title: sweet and sour carrots
directions: Layer first 3 ingredients in casserole.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Pour over layered carrots.
Bake at 350° until tender, approximately 1 hour.
Carrots may be partially precooked to cut down on baking time.
Very good!

title: cervera repa(pickled red beets)
directions: Wash fresh beets; cut tops off 3/4-inch from beets, but do not cut root, this would cause the color to bleed out.
Boil until tender; drain and cool with cold water.
Slip the skins off; cube or slice (like the little round ones).
Combine equal parts of water, sugar and vinegar.
Bring to boil; stir until sugar is dissolved.
Add beets and bring back to boil and boil until as tender as you prefer.
Pack in sterilized jars; bring liquid back to boil and pour over beets in jars.
If any liquid left, save for another batch.

title: easy banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding with milk.
Beat 2 minutes; add Eagle Brand milk. Mix well.
Add Cool Whip and mix well.
Layer ingredients in bowl, starting with the crackers, then pudding, then bananas.

title: smoked salmon party ball
directions: Drain and debone salmon.
Mix with cream cheese, liquid wood smoke seasoning, onions and lemon juice.
Form by hand into 1 large ball or 2 small balls.
Roll ball(s) in 1 cup chopped nuts and set in refrigerator to mold.
Serve with crackers as cocktail appetizer.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan well.
Layer bottom with whole graham crackers.
Mix pudding, 3 cups milk and vanilla; let stand 5 minutes.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour half of mixture on graham crackers.
Top with more whole graham crackers.
Pour rest of pudding mixture.
Add last layer of graham crackers.
Top with ready to spread frosting.
Let set in refrigerator for 8 hours before serving.

title: old fashion raisin pie
directions: Mix all ingredients except pie shell.
Cook until raisins are soft.
Put in pie shell and bake at 350° until brown.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Pour pecan chips into pie crust and cook according to directions on package.
Cream Cool Whip and cream cheese together. Add powdered sugar and mix well.
Pour into cooled pie crust. Wash and slice strawberries.

title: peanut butter smoothie
directions: In a blender, add milk, sugar, peanut butter and vanilla. Blend on high speed.
Add ice until the smoothie gets thick.
Make sure all ice is chopped up.

title: chop suey casserole
directions: Brown meat in oil.
Add chopped vegetables to meat.
Cook for 10 minutes.
Add uncooked rice, soup, water, soy sauce and bean sprouts.
Place in casserole dish and bake for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: easy quick beans
directions: Place beans into saucepan.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir over medium heat until hot.
Add salt and pepper.

title: italian style meat loaf
directions: Mix all together at 350° for 1 hour.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut crescent rolls into halves.
Take each half and roll it about three times.
Pour melted Crisco into a bowl.
Mix the sugars and cinnamon together in another bowl.
Dip each roll into the Crisco, then into sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Place in a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Let cool for 5 minutes. Cut like a pie and serve hot.

title: feather the rice
directions: Place 1 cup uncooked rice in shallow baking pan.
Toast in preheated oven at 400°, stirring occasionally, until golden brown.

title: freezer slaw
directions: Add salt to cabbage and
let stand 1 hour.
Squeeze out juice. Add carrot
and
pepper.

title: florentine artichoke dip
directions: Drain spinach; press between layers of paper towels to remove excess moisture.
Combine spinach, artichoke hearts, and the next five ingredients, stirring well.
Spoon into a lightly greased 11 x 17 inch baking dish.
Combine breadcrumbs and butter. Sprinkle over spinach mixture.
Bake uncovered at 375 ° for 25 minutes. Serve with assorted crackers, bagel chips or bread sticks.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: This is a tasty variation of that old standby meatballs.
To save time, you can mix the meatballs ahead of time and refrigerate until ready to prepare.

title: spaghetti goo
directions: Brown hamburger and onion. Drain.
Mix in spaghetti sauce. Let simmer while noodles are cooking.
Mix sauce and noodles together.
In a deep casserole dish, layer noodles mix and cheese. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: rancherio pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Stir together sugar, pineapple, eggs, flour and coconut in a bowl. Melt butter and add to other ingredients. Pour filling into pie shell. Bake 1 hour or until filling is set and brown.

title: chocolate pudding
directions: Mix sugar, flour and cocoa; add eggs.
Mix well.
Add milk; mix well.
Cook until thick; add vanilla.

title: green briar's irish trifle
directions: Put a layer of sponge cake on the bottom of a pan and soak thoroughly with strawberry liqueur.
Add a layer of pudding and a layer of the strawberries.
Then add another layer of sponge cake, liqueur, pudding and strawberries.
Top with sponge cake (not soaked in liqueur) and fresh whipped cream.

title: babe ruth balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together in large bowl.
Shape into small balls.
Place on wax paper and dip in chocolate candy coating.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Cream the shortening, sugar and eggs; add molasses and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients.
Take small balls of the dough, roll in hand and flatten slightly.
If the cookies do not crack; add more flour.
Bake on greased cookie sheet at 350°
for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: shortbread cookies
directions: Cream sugar and butter and mix in flour.
Press into cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: crunchy green beans
directions: In frying pan, bring 1-inch of water to a boil.
Add green beans, cover and reduce heat.
Cook 8 minutes.
Drain and put into ice water 5 minutes.
Drain.
Saute onion and garlic in oil until tender, stirring constantly.
Put beans back into pan and cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Add 2 tablespoons water, sugar and salt.
Cook 2 minutes and serve.

title: classic lasagna
directions: Mix ricotta, mozzarella, 1/2 c parmesan and eggs. Brown beef, drain. Stir in spaghetti sauce. In each of two 11 x 7 x 1-inch pans, layer 1 c sauce mixture, 2 noodles and 1 1/4 c cheese mixture. Repeat layers, top with remaining noodles, sauce mixture and parmesan. Bake at 400 degrees for 30 minutes. Let stand for for a few minutes before serving.

title: company pie
directions: Combine margarine, sugar and eggs.
Beat well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Turn into pie shell.
Bake about 40 minutes in moderate oven.
Makes 1 pie.

title: smoked pork chops casserole
directions: Boil potatoes until just tender (about 10 minutes).
Grease 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Combine potatoes, apples and onion and spoon into pan.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Sear pork chops over high heat. Place chops over potatoes and cover lightly with foil.
Bake 30 minutes.
Uncover the dish and bake an additional 30 minutes.
One and 1/2 hours total time.

title: raisin bars(sugar-free)
directions: In a saucepan over medium heat, cook raisins, water, margarine, cinnamon and nutmeg until margarine is melted.
Continue cooking for 3 minutes.
Add all remaining ingredients and spread into an 8-inch square baking dish that has been sprayed with nonstick cooking spray.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until lightly browned.
Yield:
16 servings.
Exchange:
1 serving equals 1 starch and 1/2 fat.

title: artichoke parmesan dip
directions: Drain artichokes very well and chop.
Add Parmesan cheese and mayo and mix well.
Place in ovenproof serving dish and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serve hot with crackers or Melba toast. Serves 6 to 8.

title: sawdust pie
directions: Bake pie shell at 350° for 5 or 6 minutes.
Mix all ingredients together until well blended. Pour into shell and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until filling is set.

title: bacon and egg triangles
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Separate crescent rolls into 4 large rectangles.
Place 2 rectangles in ungreased 8 or 9-inch square pan.
Press over bottom and 1/2-inch up sides of pan to form crust, sealing perforations.
Place cheese slices over dough. Sprinkle with bacon and onions.

title: champagne punch
directions: Mix together sugar, sauterne, lemon juice and pineapple. Keep in refrigerator.

title: apple and green tomato pie
directions: In a large bowl, combine ingredients in given order, except the last 2.
Pour mixture into 9-inch baked pie shell.
Sprinkle top with nutmeg; dot with butter.
Bake in a 400° oven for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Steam broccoli and place in baking dish.
Blend soup, cheese, milk, mayonnaise and egg.
Pour over broccoli.
Combine bread crumbs with butter.
Sprinkle over mixture.
Bake at 350° until it bubbles.

title: baked custard
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Add sugar, salt and vanilla.
Gradually add scalded milk.
Strain into custard cups or casserole dish; sprinkle nutmeg.
Bake in moderate oven (375°) about 30 minutes.

title: purple hull pea jelly
directions: After shelling peas, wash about 3 gallons of the hulls in 2 to 3 different waters.
Place in large kettle and cover with water. Bring to a boil and boil for about 20 minutes.
Strain liquid from hulls.
In a large pan, measure liquid.
Add Sure-Jell. Stir until dissolved.
Add sugar.
Bring this to a full rolling boil and boil about 15 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Let stand about 5 minutes.
Skim and pour in hot jars and seal.

title: happiness cake
directions: Beat thoroughly.
Add tears of joy, sorrow and sympathy. Flavor with love and kindly sympathy.
Fold in 4 cups of prayer, faith and enthusiasm.
Spread all into your daily life.
Blend well with human kindness.
Serve with a smile at all times, and it will satisfy the hunger of many people less fortunate than ourselves.

title: strawberry streusel coffee cake
directions: Preheat oven to 400° (375° for glass dish).

title: pork chop dinner
directions: Put Reynolds Wrap in pan.
Lay pork chops on Reynolds Wrap. Add other vegetables.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Cover with Reynolds Wrap.
Cook slowly until done.
You may need to add more water.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix jello and hot water.
Let partially set.
Add pineapple and cranberry sauce.
Let partially set again.
Swirl in sour cream, just until marbled and chill until firm.

title: swedish pound cake
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Add eggs, flour and vanilla. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: apple cinnamon jelly
directions: Boil your fruit jars for 10 minutes.
Let cool upside down on a dish towel.
Combine juice and pectin in large saucepan; bring to a full, rolling boil.
Add sugar and candies, stirring constantly; bring to a boil.
Boil for 3 minutes; remove from heat.
Let boiling subside; skim foam from top.
Pour into sterilized jars; seal.
Makes 8 1/2 pints.

title: barbecue tri-tip
directions: Mix the salt, garlic and 3 types of pepper in a bag or small dish.
Fire up the barbecue and place the tri-tip, fat side down, on the grill when the coals are white-hot.
Sprinkle the meat with some of the seasoning and poke with a sharp fork a few times to allow the seasoning to seep into the meat.
Place the lid on the grill and wait 10 to 15 minutes before turning the meat over. Repeat the sprinkling/poking process.
Wait 40 to 45 minutes for the beef to be ready.
Cut away the fat and slice into 1/4-inch thick slices.

title: goulash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in casserole.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: salmon party log
directions: Drain and flake salmon.
Remove the skin and bones.
Combine all ingredients, except nuts and parsley.
Roll in waxed paper and chill well.

title: cookie cake
directions: Slice roll thin.
Place in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix with mixer eggs, cheese and sugar.
Pour over sliced cookies.
Slice second roll and place on top.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: sun maid raisin peanut butter bars
directions: Combine peanut butter and butter; stir over medium-low heat; stir in sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Combine flour and baking powder; stir into mixture.
Stir in raisins. Spread butter in greased and floured 9 x 13 inch pan.
Bake at 350 degrees for 25 minutes or until pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool on wire rack. Place chocolate in small bowl.
Microwave on 3 to 4 minutes until melted, stirring every minute.
Drizzle over top.
Cool.

title: turkey stroganoff
directions: Brown turkey in small amount of vegetable oil; drain.
Add and cook chopped onion.
Sprinkle garlic salt.
Add mushrooms and cook until tender.
Remove from heat and add sour cream.
Serve over noodles or rice.
This with a green salad and garlic bread makes a great low-fat meal.

title: applesauce raisin bread
directions: Mix applesauce, oil and sugar.
Stir in flour, baking soda, salt and spices and slightly beaten egg and raisins.
Mix, then pour into greased and floured 8 x 4-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes or until done.

title: soft pretzels
directions: Cover dough; let rise in warm, draft-free place until doubled. Divide in 12 pieces.
With lightly floured hands, roll each piece into a 16-inch rope.
Form in pretzel shape.
In a large skillet, bring 2 inches of water to a boil.
Slip pretzels, a few at a time, into gently boiling water.
Cook until pretzels rise to the surface, about 45 seconds.
Remove with slotted spoon; drain on paper towels.
Brush lightly with egg-white mixture.
Sprinkle with salt and/or caraway seed.
Do not let pretzels rise.
Bake immediately in preheated 400° oven for 15 to 20 minutes until browned.

title: yum yum salad
directions: Mix gelatin and water. Add pineapple juice, crushed pineapple and cream cheese with fork. When mixture begins to set, add whipped cream.

title: anastasis chicken pie for 400
directions: Cook the chickens in the steamer.
Place on sheet trays to cool.
Remove the meat from the bone.
Throw away the skin and bones and keep the meat.
Remove the liquid from the steamer keeping the last 5 gallons to make a thick white sauce which the chicken will be put into before it goes into the pie crust.

title: crock-pot chili
directions: Brown beef in hot oil in skillet; discard excess fat. Put all ingredients into slow cooker. Stir once. Cover and cook on low for 8 to 10 hours. Discard bay leaf. Serve hot.

title: salsa
directions: Chop onion, jalapeno pepper and garlic buds in food chopper or chop by hand very fine.
Diced tomatoes may have to be diced into smaller pieces.
Place all ingredients into an airtight container such as a Rubbermaid or Tupperware bowl with snap lid.
Great served with restaurant-style tortilla chips or your favorite Mexican dish.

title: chocolate snowball crinkles
directions: Roll level tablespoons of dough into balls.
Roll balls in powdered sugar to coat; place 2 inches apart onto ungreased baking sheets.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 12 to 14 minutes.
Cool for 1 minute; remove to wire racks to cool completely.
Sprinkle with additional powdered sugar, if desired.
Makes about 24 cookies.

title: shrimp saute
directions: In heavy skillet, melt butter; add all other ingredients except shrimp.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to low and cook 5 minutes, stirring often.
Remove from burner and let sit for 10 to 30 minutes.
Add shrimp and return to boil.
Lower heat and stir mixture until shrimp are done (about 6 to 8 minutes).
Serve sauce over shrimp or use for dipping with French bread.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Spray pan with Pam.
Arrange chicken breasts with 1 slice cheese on each, then mushrooms.
Mix chicken soup with wine or water and pour over top.
Spread 2 cups (more if desired) herb stuffing over top, then pour over melted margarine.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes, then uncover and bake another 15 minutes.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Make your favorite pie crust.
Butter or use Pam on inverted muffin tins.
Cover tins with pie crust and flute.
Prick well. Bake in hot oven at 450° until brown.
Cool.
Remove from tins and fill with any type of filling.

title: heinz ketchup
directions: Cook tomatoes and onions and put through strainer.
Cook juice and add rest of ingredients except Clear Jell.
After cooking for about an hour, finish by thickening with a mixture of Clear Jell and water to desired thickness.
Pour in jars and seal.

title: peach cream pie
directions: May use frozen pie shell.
Put in glass pan and flute edges higher.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Spread crescent rolls on large pizza pan and pinch together. Bake according to directions.
Let cool.
Spread mixture of cream cheese, mayonnaise, sour cream and dry Hidden Valley dressing. Next, sprinkle with shredded cheese.
Put vegetables in circles, starting at outer edge of pizza crust.
Refrigerate.
May be made ahead.

title: banana bread
directions: Blend together butter and sugar.
Blend in bananas.
Add eggs, mixing after each.
In a separate bowl, mix together flour, soda and salt.
Blend into banana mixture.
Bake in greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Put all ingredients (except soda) in a pot; cook slowly until hard crack candy stage. (270° to 310°) Remove from heat and add soda. Stir well and pour into greased pan. When cooled, break in pieces.

title: barbecued chicken
directions: Skin and wash chicken; pat dry and squeeze lemon over.
Mix other ingredients and pour over chicken.
Cook in preheated 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours; turn chicken after 45 minutes.

title: chinese pork and vegetables
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving 3 tablespoons juice.
Mix reserved juice with 1/2 cup water, soy sauce, cornstarch, vinegar and pepper flakes; set aside.
Cut pork loin in strips and brown in hot oil.
Add garlic and ginger; cook 1 minute.
Add onion and carrots; cook 1 minute.
Add sauce, pineapple, bell pepper and snow peas.
Cook until sauce boils and thickens.
Serves 4.

title: linguine with broccoli, cauliflower and mushrooms
directions: Combine Ricotta and 1/3 cup Romano; set aside.
Add salt, cauliflower and broccoli to boiling water.
Cover; return to boil. Uncover and cook about 5 minutes.
Remove vegetables and reserve liquid for linguine.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Beat in egg, pumpkin and vanilla.
Mix and sift flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt, nutmeg and cinnamon.
Add to creamed mixture; mix well.
Add chocolate pieces and mix thoroughly.
Drop dough by teaspoons onto well-greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until light brown.
Remove while still warm; cool on rack.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: easiest italian beef
directions: Put meat in crock-pot on low heat.
Pour in jar of peppers, including juice, and package of onion soup mix.
Cook for 8 or more hours.
Shred meat, taking out fat or gristle.
Serve on hoagie buns.
Use au jus to dip sandwich in.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Combine all ingredients, except chocolate chips. Beat 2 minutes. Fold in chocolate chips.
Pour into greased Bundt pan. Bake at 325° for about 1 hour. Cool 10 minutes, then remove from pan.

title: cherry pineapple salad
directions: Mix cherries, pineapple and milk.
Fold in Cool Whip and nuts.
Chill.

title: no-bake peanut butter oat bars(sugar-free)
directions: In skillet over low heat, toast oats until browned, stirring. In a large bowl with mixer at medium, beat peanut butter and margarine until smooth, occasionally scraping bowl with rubber spatula.
Gradually beat in milk, vanilla and sweetener until mixed.
Stir in raisins and oats.
Spread mixture evenly into a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Refrigerate until firm, at least 2 hours.
Cut into 24 bars.
Store, covered, in refrigerator.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Boil dry macaroni and drain.
Melt butter in saucepan; add pepper and flour.
When dissolved add milk; stir.
When thickened add cheese soup.
When well melted and mixed pour over macaroni.

title: chili
directions: In
Dutch
oven brown ground beef (or beef and turkey). Add green
pepper
and	onion and cook until onion is tender. Add tomatoes,
salt and chili powder.
Reduce heat and simmer for approximately
hour; stir occasionally.	Stir in beans and liquid;
heat through completely.
Let sit about 1/2 hour and serve.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: the best and easiest dill pickles
directions: When pickles are gone, boil eggs and put in brine for Pickled Eggs.

title: oatmeal bars
directions: In a large bowl, combine shortening, brown sugar, sugar, eggs, water, vanilla and rum flavoring.
Stir until fluffy.
Add flour, salt and soda, mixing well.
Stir in oats and chips.
Bake on well-greased pans at 350° for about 20 minutes.
Use one 9 x 13-inch pan and one 8 x 8-inch pan.

title: pan fried zucchini
directions: Saute garlic in oil until golden brown.
Add onions and sliced zucchini; stir.
Add salt and Accent.
Cook on high heat for 5 minutes, while continuing to stir.
Add tomatoes; gently toss the vegetables for 1 minute.
Remove from heat immediately.

title: cranberry wine sauce
directions: In a saucepan, combine all ingredients.
Simmer, uncovered, for 5 minutes.
Serve warm with sliced turkey.

title: crawfish etouffee
directions: Melt butter or oleo in a skillet. Add flour and stir until blended. Add onions, bell pepper and garlic pods. Cook for 10 minutes. Cover and cook for another 15 to 20 minutes on low heat, stirring occasionally. Add salt, pepper and cayenne to taste, green onions and parsley and simmer a while, covered, until seasonings blend. Serve over rice.

title: pickled eggs and beets
directions: Heat water, vinegar, sugar and salt to boiling.
Pour over beets and juice in a large container. Add peeled hard-boiled eggs. Let set in refrigerator for 3 days.

title: chili vinegar
directions: Steep four red chili peppers in the vinegar.
Cool and put in jar; let "age" for about 20 days.
Shake daily.
Strain off the peppers and store in a jar in the refrigerator.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Remove stems from mushrooms. Put mushroom heads aside. Chop stems and stir all other ingredients together, then spoon into tops off mushroom heads. Place on baking sheet. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: grandma lizzie's mile-high apple pie
directions: Pare apples; core apples.
Slices should be cut very thin.
Use a large salad bowl; add sugar and cinnamon.
Put bottom pie shell in pie plate (stoneware works best); mound up apples.
Dot with butter.
Stretch top pie shell to cover and seal edges.
Cut an "A" in top to let steam out.
Put tinfoil under pie -- VERY JUICY. Bake at 425° for 50 to 60 minutes.
(If outer edge starts to get too brown, cover with tinfoil.)

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix cream cheese, chopped onions and 2/3 of ham, pepper, Accent and Worcestershire sauce.
Mold into ball and chill. Before serving, roll in rest of ham.

title: garlic croutons
directions: Saute garlic in olive oil in a large nonstick skillet until tender.
Add water mixing well.
Add bread crumbs, tossing to coat; remove and discard garlic.
Spread bread cubes evenly on a baking sheet and bake at 325° for 25 minutes or until golden brown.

title: she-crab soup
directions: In
double
boiler,
combine milk, mace and lemon peel. Let simmer 7 minutes.
Add crabmeat, butter and half and half, stirring
carefully.
Heat
over boiling water for 15 minutes. Season
to
taste.
Remove
lemon peel and add cracker crumbs. Stir in sherry and serve.
Serves 6.

title: asparagus soup
directions: In a pot melt butter.
Add oregano, thyme, garlic and asparagus.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Add flour, salt and pepper and mix thoroughly.
Cool 2 minutes, then add broth.
Stir and simmer until thick.
Add wine and milk and allow to come to boil.
Remove from heat.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grate cranberries, apple and orange.
Add nuts and sugar to taste.
Prepare Jell-O.
Stir in fruits and nuts.
Chill until firm.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Blend first 3 ingredients together.
Put in 2-quart baking dish.
Bake 8 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Mix Dream Whip, cream cheese and 1/2 cup sugar together.
Spread on pretzel base.

title: poppy seed pudding cake
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large mixer bowl.
Blend well, then beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Pour into a greased and floured 10-inch Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until cake springs back when lightly touched.
Cool in pan for 15 minutes.
Remove from pan and finish cooling on rack.

title: stuffing for baked fish
directions: Put all ingredients in a bowl and mix well. Use it to stuff the cavity of fish or spread it between fillets of fish.

title: potato soup
directions: In a large pot, brown onion and butter.
Add potatoes, ham, carrot, salt, pepper, and dill weed.
Cook on low heat until potatoes are creamy, about 45 minutes.
Stir in milk and parsley, continue to cook.
When mixture is heated through, stir in instant potatoes.
You can add more or less instant potatoes depending on what constancy you like your soup.

title: marie barker's awesome turkey
directions: Shake flour in a Brown-in-Bag.
Mix other ingredients.
Put turkey breast in bag and pour sauce over.
Close bag, cut slits in top of bag and bake 5 hours in 300° oven.
Serve with plenty of the sauce.

title: chicken or turkey tetrazzini
directions: Saute mushrooms in margarine until tender.
Add flour, stir until smooth.
Add milk and seasonings.
Cook until thickened, stir constantly.
Remove from heat.
Blend 1/2 of sauce with chicken and remaining half with spaghetti.
Bank spaghetti round edges of shallow greased baking dish.

title: easy chicken chili
directions: In a 3-quart saucepan coated with cooking spray, saute onion over medium heat until tender. Add remaining ingredients; bring to a boil. Reduce heat, cover and simmer for 10-15 minutes or until heated through. Serves 6.

title: fruit cake
directions: Sift flour into 4-quart mixing bowl; add baking powder, salt and cinnamon.
Mix fruit and nuts into flour mixture until well coated.
Set aside.
Cream butter; gradually add 2 1/4 cups sugar and beat until creamed.
Add eggs (beat well after each).
Add extracts; mix well.
Pour into 10-inch tube pan, lined with heavy-duty foil.
Fill pan 2/3 full.
Bake at 275° for 2 hours and 45 minutes to 3 hours.
Half hour before cake is done, brush top with honey.
Return to oven to finish baking.
Cool completely. Wrap tightly with foil and store in cool place for several weeks.

title: fluffy biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Mix shortening into dry ingredients.
Add yeast and buttermilk, cut like biscuits and fold over.
Dip each one in melted butter.
Place in a bread pan.
Bake at 470° for 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: spicy oven fries
directions: Cut each potato lengthwise into 8 wedges.
Combine olive oil and Creole seasoning in a zip-top plastic bag.
Add wedges.
Seal bag and shake to coat.
Arrange wedges, skin side down, in a single layer on a baking sheet coated with vegetable cooking spray.
Bake at 450° for 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Drain well and put in casserole dish.

title: rhubarb preserves
directions: Boil rhubarb and sugar 10 minutes; add jello and stir well. Can and seal or freeze.

title: elaine's cake mix cookies
directions: Cut margarine into cake mix until it resembles pie dough (crumbly).
Add beaten eggs and water.
If mixture is too thick, add another tablespoon of water.
Drop on greased cookie sheet and flatten with the bottom of a glass that has been dipped in water and then sugar.
Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Place cocoa and milk over low heat and stir until chocolate is melted and mixture is smooth.
Stir in sugar, corn syrup and salt.
Cook until a soft ball is formed when portion is dropped in cold water.
Remove from heat and add butter.
Cool without stirring until lukewarm and add vanilla.
Beat until thick and glossy, stir in pecans and spread in a buttered dish.

title: bacon fried chicken
directions: Combine milk, egg and chicken in a large bowl.
Chill 1 hour. Mix flour, salt and pepper in a medium bowl.
Coat chicken with flour mixture.
Shake off excess.
Cover the bottom of a large frying pan with bacon.
Place chicken on top of bacon.
Cook, uncovered, over medium-low heat for 50 minutes until chicken is tender.
Drain on paper towels.
Sprinkle with any loose bacon.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix cheeses together.
Heat soups, broth and chiles together. Layer in greased casserole dish:
1/2 soup, 1/2 tortillas, 1/2 chicken and 1/2 cheeses.
Repeat.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Let set 5 to 10 minutes before serving.
Top with sour cream. Serve with a tossed salad.

title: crabmeat appetizers
directions: Mix all ingredients until very smooth (butter and cheese should be softened).
Spread on English muffins; cut into quarters.
Bake at 375° for 7 to 10 minutes.

title: beef 'n tater casserole
directions: Brown beef; drain.
Combine beef, green beans, soup, water, salt, garlic and pepper.
Pour into a casserole.
Combine mashed potatoes and 1/2 can onion.
Spoon potato mixture in a mounded ring around top outer edge of casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 25 minutes.
Top potatoes with cheese and remaining onions and bake 5 minutes longer.
Serves 6.

title: armadillo eggs
directions: Remove stems and slit peppers lengthwise, rinse in cold water to remove seeds.
Lay out to dry on paper towels.
Stuff with cheese.
Pat sausage into thin patties and wrap around cheese stuffed peppers.
Put on cookie sheet (seam side down).
Bake at 450° until sausage is cooked (about 20 minutes).
Drain and set aside to cool.
Roll out each biscuit (may need two).
Place a sausage pepper in each one and roll up making sure completely covered.
Bake at 450° turning frequently until browned.
Cool. Serve with sour cream and guacamole.

title: minestrone soup
directions: Combine onion, broth and garlic.
Cook until onion is translucent.
Add remaining ingredients, except beans and macaroni.
Cook about 10 minutes until carrots are tender.
Then add beans and macaroni.
Heat.
Can top with Parmesan cheese.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Melt butter.
Cook garlic, green pepper, parsley and mushrooms until soft.
Add flour.
Stir until smooth.
Stir in broth.
Add cream.
Cook until bubbling.
Add wine, salt, pepper, nutmeg, pimentos, chicken and cooked spaghetti.
Turn into 12 x 7 x 2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: easy fruit cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in deep baking dish.
Pour in fruit.
(If peaches, add 1 teaspoon almond flavoring).
In a small bowl mix flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Add milk.
Stir well.
Pour batter, which will be thin, over top of fruit.
Do not stir!!
Bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes or until brown.

title: miami beach birthday cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Melt 1/3 cup chocolate chips.
Grease 2 (9-inch) layer pans.
Combine coconut, butter and walnuts.
Let cool.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Set aside.
