Mix flour, soda and salt.
Cream butter in large bowl.
Gradually add sugar and cream until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Blend in melted chocolate and vanilla.
At low speed add dry ingredients alternately with buttermilk, beginning and ending with dry ingredients.
Pour into pans.
Sprinkle tops with coconut-nut mixture.
Bake until knife inserted comes out clean, about 30 to 40 minutes.
Mix Cool Whip and cream cheese.
Fill between layers, around sides.
Mound around outer edge of top layer.
Refrigerate.

title: cheese cake pie
directions: Microwave butter in pie plate until melted.
Mix in crumbs and Equal.
Press onto bottom and around sides of pie plate. Microwave on Full power 1 1/2 to 2 minutes, or until crumbs are hot enough to set crust.
For conventional oven, bake crust at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: chess cake
directions: Mix cake mix, butter and 1 beaten egg well.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan.
Dough will be stiff.
Mix together 2 beaten eggs and cream cheese, along with confectioners sugar.
Pour over first layer and bake for 40 to 45 minutes at 325°.

title: tomato and avocado salsa
directions: Combine all ingredients except avocado in large bowl.
Mix well.
Refrigerate 3 to 4 hours or overnight.
Remove from refrigerator at least 1/2 hour before serving.
Add diced avocado just before serving.
Mix well with large wooden spoon.
Perfect accompaniment for swordfish with avocado sauce.
Serves 4.

title: quick start breakfast drink
directions: For a large blender, combine all ingredients in blender jar. Whip until smooth.
For a small blender, combine 1/2 of the ingredients.

title: smoked sausage casserole
directions: In a skillet, saute onions in the oil along with the sausage until some browning occurs.
Add the next five ingredients and simmer 20 minutes.
Mix the sausage and tomatoes with the steaming hot noodles.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese (optional).
Serves 4.

title: jiffy cake
directions: Bake cake mix according to directions in a 9 x 13-inch cake pan; let cool. Blend cream cheese and milk; add pudding and blend until thick.
Spread over cake.
Spread drained crushed pineapple over pudding mixture. Spread Cool Whip over top and sprinkle with nuts.
Best if refrigerated overnight.

title: sweet and sour dressing
directions: Put in blender and mix until smooth.

title: cherry-coke salad
directions: Heat
cherries and their juice to boiling.
Remove from heat and
add gelatin.
Add pineapple, with its juice.
Stir. Pour
in Coke and nuts.
Cool.
Pour in dish or mold.
Refrigerate.

title: hot apple cider
directions: Heat in electric percolator.
Before heating, place the following ingredients in percolator basket:

title: cranberry barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in a saucepan; bring to a boil.
Use on ribs, pork chops or pork roast.
Yields about 1 1/2 cups.

title: simple meatballs
directions: Soak the bread in milk so it is thoroughly wet.
Drain well, squeezing it gently to remove most of the milk (you want the crumbs moist but not dripping).
Combine the crumbs with the ground meat, egg, minced parsley, nutmeg, and salt and pepper to taste.
Knead the mixture well.
Then shape into as many balls about an inch in diameter.
If you like, roll them in bread crumbs (optional).
Set a large skillet to heat with oil, and add the meatballs.
Cook, stirring, over medium heat until they are browned on all sides, then pour in half cup or slightly more milk.
Partially cover and simmer the meatballs until they are done and the sauce is considerably thickened.
Serve, spooning the sauce over the meatballs, with salad, spinach, mashed potatoes or pasta.

title: white sangria
directions: Mix all ingredients, except club soda and orange slices, in a large pitcher.
Float orange slices in the pitcher or glasses.
Chill for at least 2 hours before serving.
Add club soda when serving.

title: sweet potato or yam casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in buttered casserole dish. Bake at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: freezer bread and butter pickles
directions: Mix together the cucumbers, green pepper, sweet onion and salt.
Let stand for 3 hours.
Drain well.

title: easy hamburger quiche
directions: Brown meat in skillet over medium heat.
Drain fat and set aside.
Blend next four ingredients until smooth.
Stir in meat, cheese, onion and pepper.
Turn into pastry shell.
Bake until golden brown on top and knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: peanut brittle candy
directions: Combine sugar, peanuts, syrup, water and salt; cook on high until it becomes to good boiling point.
Turn down to medium heat (3 or 4 from high) and cook for 10 to 12 minutes.
Be sure not to overcook.
Turn back on high and get real hot; pour soda in, stirring constantly.
Pour on well buttered cookie sheet.
Take a knife and pull to make thin candy.

title: fudgy pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In medium saucepan over low heat, melt chocolate with margarine. Stir in sweetened condensed milk, hot water and eggs.
Mix well. Remove from heat. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into
prepared pastry shell. Bake 40 to 45 minutes or until center is set. Cool slightly. Serve warm or chilled. Garnish as desired.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: cheese ball
directions: Let cheese reach room temperature.
Using a mixer, blend cheeses until smooth and creamy.
Add Worcestershire sauce and onion; mix well.
Chill.
Shape into balls.
Sprinkle chili powder or paprika over balls.
Serve with crackers.
Yield: 2 (2 pound) balls.

title: fiesta pasta salad
directions: In large bowl, combine pasta, onion, red pepper, corn, chilies, jalapeno and cilantro or parsley.
In small bowl, whisk together salad dressing, chili powder and cumin.
Pour over pasta mixture, tossing to coat well.
Chill at least 30 minutes to blend flavors before serving.

title: easy salmon patties
directions: Drain salmon and set aside 2 tablespoons of liquid.
Mix salmon, egg and onion until sticky.
Stir in flour.
Add baking powder to liquid.
Stir until dissolved, then add to salmon mixture.
Form patties by hand and fry in hot oil until golden (about 5 minutes).
Serve with lemon quarters.
When you're tired after a long day at work, this is a quick way out of the kitchen.

title: marshmallow whip salad
directions: Whisk together French vanilla and cheesecake puddings with 2 cups milk. Add other ingredients, mix well and refrigerate.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and garlic salt.
Place in 1-quart buttered casserole dish.
Pour melted butter on top.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: spaghetti squash casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Slice squash in half lengthwise and scoop out the seeds.
Bake it face down on buttered tray for about 30 minutes or until easily pierced by a fork.
Cool.
Scoop out insides.
While squash bakes, saut the onions and garlic with salt, pepper, mushrooms and herbs.
When onions are soft, add chopped tomatoes.
Cook until most of the liquid evaporates. Combine all ingredients.
Pour into buttered 2-quart casserole. Top with lots of grated Parmesan.
Bake, uncovered, about 40 minutes.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Chill one hour.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: klaudia's no crust cheesecake
directions: Divide eggs.
Beat eggs whites until stiff.
Combine egg yolks, sugar and lemon rind at high speed for 3 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients except egg whites.
Mix together.
Fold in egg whites.
Bake 1 hour at 325° to 350° in a spring form pan. Can be served warm or cold.

title: easy chicken continental
directions: Saute chicken, mushrooms and garlic in oil 2 to 3 minutes. Add all remaining ingredients, except rice.
Bring to a boil. Stir in rice and let stand 5 minutes, covered.

title: spanish noodles
directions: Combine hamburger meat, onion and green pepper.
Fry in a pan until meat is well done.
Cook noodles in salted water; drain and rinse.
In a baking dish, put meat mixture, noodles, corn, soup, salt and cheese.
Mix well.
Add some water so mixture will be moist.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until heated through.

title: broccoli and cauliflower casserole
directions: Steam vegetables until crisp-tender.
Melt soup and cheese together and pour over vegetables.
Mix and pour into casserole, top with onion rings.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all together and chill.
Makes 1 cup.

title: zesty rice lasagna
directions: In a large bowl, combine cooked Success rice, 1 egg and 1/3 cup Parmesan cheese.
In another bowl, combine 1 egg, Mozzarella, Ricotta, 1/3 cup Parmesan and parsley.
In a large skillet, brown beef, stirring to break into bits; drain.
Add sauce and oregano; heat.
Evenly spread half rice mixture into an 11 1/2 x 7 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch greased baking dish.
Top with half cheese mixture and meat mixture.
Repeat layers.
Sprinkle with remaining Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes, or until hot.
Serves 8.

title: taco beef skillet meal
directions: Brown beef and onion and drain fat.
Drain and cut up tomatoes, reserving juice.
Add water to juice to make 2 1/2 cups liquid.
Add tomatoes, liquid, rice and taco seasoning to beef in skillet.
Stir.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer unti liquid is absorbed (about 25 minutes).
Stir occasionally. Top with shredded cheese and lettuce before serving.

title: mom's rolled sugar cookies
directions: Mix soda and buttermilk, whip with a fork; set aside.
Cream sugar, shortening and oleo.
Then add salt, nutmeg, vanilla and eggs.
Add half of flour then half of buttermilk, other half of flour then other half of buttermilk.
Roll and cut out.
Bake at 375° until light brown, about 8 minutes.

title: leftover roast beef hash
directions: Slice potatoes into thin pieces; put into skillet with some oil.
Fry until crisp around edges.
Add the roast beef and mushrooms soup; cook until hot.
Add seasoned salt to taste.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients except the blueberries together. Add the blueberries.
Bake 20 minutes at 400°. Makes 12 muffins (if oven is too hot, turn down to 375°).

title: yummy hot corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Place in 2 1/2-quart casserole dish. Bake at 350° about 30 minutes.
(To minimize spicy taste, use Cheez Whiz without peppers.)
Prepare Rice-A-Roni according to package directions.

title: banana pudding
directions: Place a layer of graham crackers in a baking dish.
Add a layer of bananas, sliced and 1/2 mixture which has been cooked until thickened.
Then repeat with another layer of graham crackers, bananas and remaining mixture.
Beat 4 egg whites until stiff, add 3 tablespoons sugar, pour on top of pudding and set in oven to brown.

title: lentil roast
directions: Cook lentils; drain.
Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: orange mayonnaise chiffon cake
directions: Into large mixer bowl, sift flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Make well in center; add egg yolks, orange rind and juice and reduced-calorie mayonnaise.
With mixer at medium speed, beat until smooth.
In large bowl with mixer at high speed, beat egg whites and cream of tartar until very stiff peaks form.
Fold flour mixture into egg whites until well blended.
Pour into ungreased 10 x 4-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 60 to 65 minutes or until cake springs back when lightly touched.
Invert pan over funnel.
Cool completely.
Remove from pan.
Makes 16 servings, 180 calories each.

title: lemon delight cake
directions: Mix Jell-O and hot water.
Set aside to cool.
When cool, combine remaining ingredients.
Add Jell-O.
Blend well.
Bake in greased tube pan at 325° for 1 hour, 10 minutes.
Prepare 1 cup 10x sugar and 1/4 cup fresh lemon juice.
Pour over cake as soon as removed from oven.

title: beef cheese balls
directions: Mix and roll into 3 to 4 cheese balls, then roll in chopped pecans. Wrap in wax paper, then foil.
Freezes well.
Enjoy!

title: meat dip
directions: Brown hamburger and onion; drain and set aside.
In saucepan, mix soup, milk, cheese and taco seasoning.
Simmer until cheese melts.
Add hamburger and onion.
Heat and serve with tortilla chips.

title: virginia cox's peanut brittle
directions: Cook sugar, syrup, peanuts, water and salt.
In heavy pan, cook 8 to 10 minutes, until peanuts nearly stop popping and lose whiteness when opened.
Remove from heat.
Add baking soda.
Stir fast and pour immediately.
Cool and crack.

title: cousin donnie's cheese balls
directions: Bring cheese to room temperature.
Add all ingredients, mix well.
Roll into 3 balls.
The balls can be rolled in nuts or decorated with black olives and pimentos.

title: cream cheese sugar cookies
directions: In large mixing bowl, combine butter and cream cheese.

Beat with mixer. Add half of the flour, the 2/3 cup sugar, 1 egg, baking powder, vanilla and almond extract. Beat until combined. Beat or stir remaining flour; divide in half. Cover and chill for 1 to 2 hours or until firm. On lightly floured surface, roll 1 portion at a time to 1/4 inch thickness. Using cookie cutters, cut in desired shapes. If desired, decorate before baking. Bake in oven for 8 to 10 minutes at 350°. Makes 32 cookies.

title: corn vegetable medley
directions: In saucepan, heat soup and milk to boiling, stirring often. Stir in vegetables.
Return to boiling.
Cover; cook over low heat 20 minutes or until vegetables are tender, stirring often.
Stir in cheese.
Heat through.

title: mom's christmas pie
directions: Scald milk. Melt butter and blend in cornstarch, sugar and salt. Gradually add milk to melted butter mixture. Cook mixture until fairly thickened. Remove from fire; add gradually to beaten egg whites. Stir in vanilla. Pour into baked 9-inch pie shell and bake in 350° oven for 5 minutes. When cool, top with whipped cream. Garnish with chopped nuts.

title: texas barbecue sauce
directions: Mix in saucepan the 2 tablespoons brown sugar, paprika, salt, mustard, chili powder, pepper, Worcestershire sauce, vinegar, tomato juice, catsup and water.
Simmer until slightly thickened (about 15 minutes).
Add Open Pit, 1/3 cup brown sugar and honey.

title: grilled chicken
directions: Pour dressing over chicken.
Refrigerate 1 hour to marinate. Drain.
Place chicken on a greased rack of grill or on rack of broiler pan.
Grill over medium coals or broil 5 to 7 inches from heat for 6 minutes on each side or until tender.

title: low fat key lime pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325 degrees.
In a large bowl, beat egg yolks with condensed milk, using wire whisk.
Stir in lime juice and food coloring.
Pour into pie crust and bake for 40 minutes.
When cool, top with Cool Whip.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Melt butter in 13 x 9 pan. Mix other ingredients and pour into pan with butter. Bake 25- 30 minutes at 375 (or 350 for glass pan).

title: fresh lemonade
directions: With a sharp knife, very thinly slice lemons crosswise. Discard end slices and seeds.
Put lemon slices into a large bowl or sturdy pitcher.
Add the sugar.
With a wooden spoon, stir until the sugar is dissolved.
Let lemon-sugar mixture stand 10 minutes.
Add ice and 6 cups cold water.
Stir until very cold. Add lemon slices.
Serve.

title: chicken fried rice
directions: Saute 3 vegetables in part of bacon grease.
When done, pour over rice (using as much of the bacon grease as desired).
Add the chopped chicken and the bacon.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown ground beef, onion, salt and pepper in medium saucepan. Stir in rest of ingredients, except Doritos.
Heat oven to 350°. Layer bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking pan with tortilla chips.
Then spoon 1/2 meat mixture and 1/2 cheese.
Repeat. Bake 1/2 hour.

title: judy's special chicken
directions: Melt butter in baking dish.
Stir in thyme, paprika, salt and pepper.
Dredge chicken in flour, then swish each piece in butter until well coated.
Arrange them in the dish and bake at 400° until browned (30 to 45 minutes).
Reduce heat to 350°.
Add wine and mushrooms.
Cover with foil and bake about 30 more minutes. Serve with rice.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Beat egg yolks.
Mix with all dry ingredients.
Add milk and vanilla and pour in pie shell.
Bake at 350°
for 25 to 35 minutes.

title: hot cabbage slaw
directions: In covered pan, cook on medium heat 3 minutes.
Then add 2 tablespoons vinegar.
Good on fish sandwiches.

title: radish kilawin
directions: Pare radish and slice thinly crosswise. Work lightly with 1 1/2 teaspoons salt. Rinse once and drain. Boil shrimp, shell and cut lengthwise into halves. Pound the heads of the shrimp and extract the juice using the water in which the shrimp were cooked. Fry pork until brown. Remove from pan and saute garlic, onion and tomatoes. Add shrimp and 1/2 teaspoon salt and cook 3 minutes. Add cooked pork and shrimp liquid. Cook 2 minutes, stirring constantly. Add drained radishes. Cover and cook about 10 minutes. Add vinegar and pepper. Bring to a boil and remove from heat. Serve hot as appetizer.

title: baked chicken and rice casserole
directions: Spread rice evenly in buttered casserole pan.
Sprinkle 1/4 of the dry onion soup on rice.
Place chicken on rice.
Sprinkle with remaining onion soup and pepper to taste.
Blend well the mushroom soup, chicken gumbo soup and water.
Pour over chicken and rice. Dot with margarine and cover with foil.
Bake 2 hours at 325°.

title: sweet and tart salad
directions: Toss together cabbage and apple. Pour on dressing and toss to coat evenly.

title: lemon-lime salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 1/2 cups boiling water.
Add 1/2 cup cold water.
Let set in refrigerator until slightly firm.
Stir in all other ingredients and let congeal.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni according to directions.
Drain.
Arrange in shallow, buttered baking dish.
Melt butter in saucepan, blend in flour and stir in milk slowly,.
Bring to a boil (do not burn). Add salt and pepper and 1/2 cheese, diced.
Stir until melted. Scatter other half of cheese over macaroni.
Pour sauce over all. Sprinkle crumbs over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: blue cheese ball
directions: Mix all together, chill.
Roll in chopped nuts (optional).

title: homemade ice cream(cooked custard version)
directions: Separate eggs.
Put egg whites in the refrigerator.
Beat yolks until blended well.
Mix sugar and cornstarch.
Add to egg yolks.
Stir in the milk.
Cook until this comes to a boil, stirring constantly.
(It takes a long time.)
Let cool.
Add vanilla.

title: salmon sandwich spread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Spread on bread.

title: artichoke dressing
directions: Mix bread crumbs, artichoke juice, olive oil and lemon juice. Add mashed artichoke hearts, cheese and garlic. Pour into casserole dish; bake 20 minutes at 350°. Makes 2 1/2 quarts.

title: chocolate decadence(the original)
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Line an 8 x 2-inch round cake pan with parchment or waxed paper.
Melt chocolate and butter in a small bowl place in a barely simmering water bath over low heat, stirring occasionally until smooth.
Or, cook in a microwave oven on Medium (50% power) for about 2 1/2 minutes.
Stir until completely melted and smooth.
Whisk in egg yolks and flour; set aside.

title: cheese fingers
directions: Remove crust from bread.
Combine eggs with milk.
Put melted margarine into bowl and cheese in another.
Dip 1 slice bread in egg mixture and place in between 2 slices of dry bread.
Cut into 4 pieces.
Dip each piece in margarine, then in cheese, leaving bottom side clean.
Place uncheesed side down on cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Yield:
About 80.

title: cheesy coleslaw mold
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water. Add vinegar. Combine Miracle Whip, salt and pepper. Gradually add jello mixture.
Chill until partially set. Combine cabbage, carrot, cheese and celery seed. Fold into jello.
Pour into 1-quart bowl or mold. Chill until set.

title: no-bake cookies
directions: Mix together and cook 7 minutes.
Add 2 cups Rice Krispies and 1/2 cup chopped nuts.
Set aside to cool.
Make in balls and roll in fine coconut.
Makes a pretty cookie for Christmas.
Good cookies.

title: party punch
directions: Combine Kool-Aid, sugar, ginger ale and pineapple juice. Stir.
Add sherbet by spoonfuls and stir.

title: breakfast rolls
directions: Put pecans on bottom of Bundt cake pan.
Place frozen rolls over them.
Sprinkle with butterscotch pudding mix (instant will not work!!)
Melt margarine, add the sugar and cinnamon.
Pour over frozen rolls and pecans.
Cover with towel and leave on counter overnight.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes in the morning. Invert on serving dish immediately upon removing from oven.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix apples and sugar.
Let set for 1 hour.
Then add and mix together the rest of the ingredients.
Grease and flour Bundt cake pan or 2 loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes.

title: ham loaf
directions: Stir and let stand several hours.
Mix all together thoroughly.
When you put loaf in oven, pour sauce over top. Press in the sauce.
Bake 1 1/2 to 2 hours at 325°.

title: rice pudding
directions: Wash rice.
Place in a heavy pot and stir in regular milk and salt.
Cook, covered, for 45 minutes or until rice is tender.
Add 1/4 cup evaporated milk and raisins.

title: jalapeno pepper jelly
directions: In heavy pan, combine sugar and 1 cup white vinegar; cook slowly until sugar dissolves.
Blend the jalapenos, green pepper and 1/4 cup white vinegar; blend into a puree.
Add puree to first mixture; bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Cook 2 minutes. Remove from heat and skim foam or strain.
Add food coloring (green) and 1 bottle Certo.
Immediately fill hot, sterile jars. Clean tops.
Use paraffin to seal, if desired.
Refrigerate.

title: heavenly salad
directions: Mix Jell-O and boiling water; let jell partly.
Mix cream cheese, pineapple, nuts and marshmallows, then add to Jell-O. Fold in Cool Whip.
Return to refrigerator.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Quarter
cherries; mix in pecans and marshmallows.
Stir into whipped topping.
Serve in chilled sherbet glasses.

title: no-fat three bean salad
directions: Steam green beans for 5 minutes until barely tender.
Remove from steamer immediately.
Combine all beans and onion in bowl or storage container.
Prepare dressing by beating the vinegar, honey, water and apple juice with a fork until well blended.
Pour dressing over beans and mix well.
Cover and let marinate at room temperature at least 30 minutes, then chill 30 minutes.
Toss again before serving.

title: potpourri soup
directions: Brown meat in large pot.
Crumble up.
Add onion and cook until transparent.
Add water, tomatoes, barley, salt and pepper.
Simmer one hour.
Add vegetables and cook one more hour.
Serves 6.

title: good simple cobbler
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add
eggs.
Measure
baking powder; add to flour.
Alternate milk and flour.
Add berries last.
Bake about an hour in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: spicy cabbage salad
directions: Whisk vinegar, ginger, salt, pepper, garlic, red pepper and oil together in large bowl.
Add cabbage and green onions; toss well.
Only 50 calories per serving and 0 mg cholesterol.

title: steve's vegetable casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients except crackers and margarine.
Pour into casserole dish and crumble crackers over the top.
Melt margarine and cover crackers.
Bake for 20 minutes.

title: million dollar fudge
directions: Blend sugar, butter, salt and milk.
Cook on medium heat, stirring constantly.
Boil about 6 minutes.
In large bowl, add chocolate bits, semi-sweet chocolate, which has been broken into small pieces, Marshmallow Creme and chopped nuts.
Add cooked mixture to bowl containing chocolate and stir until chocolate is melted and pour into 2 (8 x 8 x 2-inch) greased pans or 1 (9 x 13-inch) pan.

title: rhubarb bread
directions: In large bowl, mix eggs, salad oil, brown sugar and vanilla. Beat until thick and foamy.
Stir in rhubarb and walnuts.
In separate bowl, combine flour (or use 1 1/2 cups each white and whole wheat flour), soda, cinnamon, salt, baking powder, nutmeg and allspice.
Mix dry ingredients into rhubarb mixture with spoon.
Spoon into 2 greased and floured loaf pans and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cream of potato soup
directions: Dice potatoes and onion.
Add water and cook until tender. Melt oleo; add flour and blend.
Then add milk and salt; cook until slightly thick.
Stir constantly.
Add potatoes and onion. Serves 6.

title: cheese krispins
directions: In mixing bowl, cream together cheese and margarine.
Add flour, pepper and salt. Work in Rice Krispies.
Drop by teaspoons on greased cookie sheet.
Flatten with thumb.
Bake about 10 minutes at 350°.
Yields 3 to 4 dozen.

title: easy fruit pie(may use any fresh fruit)
directions: Wash fruit and let dry.
Mix flour and sugar together.
Place fruit in unbaked pie crust and pour the flour-sugar mixture over fruit.
Slice the stick of oleo and place on top of pie.
This will make a top crust.
Bake at 350° until light brown.

title: chicken delight
directions: Place chicken in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix soup and sour cream. Mix cracker crumbs, poppy seed and butter or margarine.
Spread sour cream and soup over chicken, then cracker crumb mixture. Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: cheese ball
directions: Crumb beef in food processor or blender.
Divide in half. Reserve 1/2 for later.
Add onions to beef in processor.
Chop until fine.

title: hot roll mix
directions: Dissolve yeast in water to which sugar has been added.
Mix liquid with mix until well blended.
Knead on floured board. Allow to rise until double in bulk.
Make into rolls and allow to rise again until double in bulk.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: cream of mushroom soup
directions: Saute mushrooms and onion in butter until tender (5 to 8 minutes).
Stir occasionally.
Blend in flour; add milk slowly and then beef stock, stirring to blend.
Add salt and pepper and cook, stirring constantly until soup is thickened.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Mix brown sugar, shortening, molasses and egg.
Stir in flour, baking soda, cinnamon, ginger, cloves and salt.
Cover and refrigerate at least 1 hour.

title: beef enchiladas
directions: Brown hamburger meat, then drain grease. Put back in pan. Add 1 can of refried beans. Add 1 can of mild enchilada sauce. Simmer for 15 minutes.

title: pumpkin cream pie
directions: Combine ingredients and pour into pie shell.
Chill about 3 hours.
Garnish with prepared whipped topping, if desired.

title: chocolate fudge pie
directions: Melt chocolate and cool.
Mix together butter or ultra light butter by Land O Lakes, sugar, vanilla, salt and eggs.
Add cooled chocolate to mixture and pour into an 8-inch pie crust, pastry or graham cracker.
Refrigerate for at least 4 hours.

title: batter-fried franks
directions: Combine first 3
ingredients
and then stir in second 3 ingredients until smooth.
Insert
a
wooden skewer into 1 end of franks.
Fry in hot oil and sprinkle with cheese while hot. Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: alaska carrot cake
directions: Cream sugar and oil together in large mixing bowl.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Combine dry ingredients and add
alternately
with buttermilk and vanilla, mixing
until smooth.
Fold
in
remaining
ingredients.
Pour equal amounts of batter into
well-greased and floured 8 or 9-inch round cake pans.
Bake
in
preheated
350° oven for 25 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes.
Remove
from
pans
and frost with orange cream frosting when completely cool.

title: bob's deer jerky
directions: Cut meat into 1/4-inch thick strips 2-inches wide.
Cut with grain of meat.
(Partially freeze meat to make cutting easier.) Combine soy sauce and liquid smoke and seasonings together in bowl. Marinate meat in sauce about 15 minutes.
Place in food dryer and dry about 15 hours (can substitute beef for the deer meat).

title: diabetic soft honey cake
directions: Blend margarine and honey. Add well beaten egg. Stir in 1/2 cup sour milk or buttermilk, then add rest of ingredients. Mix well and beat until light. Pour into a greased square pan. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes and cool. Can also be made into cupcakes, if so desired.

title: quick rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Spoon in greased muffin tin.
Let rise 1/2 to 1 hour.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: chili
directions: Brown meat, onions, bell peppers and salt and pepper. Drain off fat. Add tomato sauces and chili powder. Cook potatoes separately and when done add to chili, simmer for 30 minutes.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients together.
Grease a cookie sheet and line with wax paper.
Pour batter in and spread.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Lay towel on counter top and sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Turn cake out onto this and roll up in towel for 10 minutes.

title: melon ball
directions: Mix all ingredients with ice in blender.

title: southern spoon bread
directions: Sift meal and salt into mixing bowl; add sugar.
Add boiling water to make consistency of mush, stirring briskly all the while. Add butter and set aside to cool.
Beat eggs until light.
Add baking powder and milk.
Combine with meal mixture and stir until smooth and creamy.
This will be a very thin batter.
Pour into greased baking dish; bake about 25 minutes in 450° oven until brown.

title: zucchini cookies
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Add sugar.
Mix.
Add oil and vanilla. Mix dry ingredients; then mix with egg mixture, a little at a time.
Fold in nuts and grated zucchini.
Cover and chill.
Drop on a cookie sheet.
Bake in a 350° oven for 12 to 14 minutes.

title: pineapple refrigerator relish
directions: Combine pineapple, cilantro, red pepper and purple onion in a glass bowl, tossing well.

title: icing
directions: Cook until mixture is slightly thick. Pour over warm cake. Top with whipped topping.

title: party meat balls
directions: Soak bread in milk, add all other ingredients.
Roll into small balls, brown in 1 tablespoon of butter.
Add two cups beef broth (use bouillon cubes or soup) which has been thickened with 1 tablespoon cornstarch.
Simmer until thickened, then pour over meatballs.
Simmer about 1 hour, leaving lid on electric frypan or regular pan.
Serve direct from pan to table.
Keep meatballs warm all during the serving time.

title: seafood bisque
directions: Saute onion and celery in butter.
Add to onion mixture two or more fresh seafoods (shrimp, crab, scallops or lobster).
Mix soup, milk and seasonings together; add to seafood.
Heat, but do not boil.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream sugar, oleo and Crisco; add egg yolks one at a time. Add soda to the flour and add alternately with buttermilk and vanilla.
Beat egg whites really stiff and fold into the mixture and then add coconut.
Pour batter into greased and floured pan. Bake 25 minutes at 350° or until done to touch.
Icing follows.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Mix together and put in cabbage leaves.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Mix together all ingredients except zucchini.
Add it last. Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken continental
directions: Grease crock-pot and line bottom and sides with chipped dried beef.
Wrap chicken in bacon slices.
Combine soup, sour cream and flour mixture.
Pour over chicken.
Cook 8 to 10 hours on low. Serve over green noodles.

title: gramie's brown stone cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Sift soda, chocolate and salt together.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk and water. Mix well.
Add vanilla. Stir, then bake in Bundt pan at 350° until done. Check by straw (broom straw) for doneness.

title: german chocolate pie
directions: Melt together chocolate and margarine.
Blend in evaporated milk.
Mix and add sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Beat and blend into chocolate mixture the eggs and vanilla.
Add coconut and pecans. Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Cool at least 4 hours.

title: "spaghetti carbonara"
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions (6 minutes).
Melt butter and add to cooked pasta.
Add beaten eggs to pasta and butter mixture.
The hot pasta cooks the eggs.
Mix in Parmesan cheese, black pepper, cream or milk and sprinkle with crumbled bacon.

title: strawberry shortcut cake
directions: Sprinkle marshmallows in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
In small bowl, combine strawberries and jello; set aside.
In large mixing bowl, combine remaining ingredients.
Pour strawberry mix over marshmallows, then pour batter evenly over berries.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until golden brown.

title: picante sauce
directions: Cook tomatoes and onions together until onions are clear in color.
Add remaining ingredients; pour into jars.
Hot water bath for approximately 20 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Cook the first 3 ingredients until boiling.
Cool sauce and pour over fruit.
Refrigerate.
Keeps for days.

title: modeling clay
directions: Mix and knead until mixture is not sticky.
Store in plastic bags.

title: cheesecake bars
directions: Cream butter and brown sugar.
Add flour and nuts to make crumb mixture.
Reserve 1 cup crumb mixture for topping.
Press remainder into 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour in greased and floured 9 x 2-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 35 minutes.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Mix sugar, cinnamon, butter and 7-Up.
Bring to a boil.
Roll out biscuits.
Put half of a handful of apples in center of biscuit and fold together.
Pinch the sides together.
Place in baking dish. Place rest of apples and mixture over dumplings. Bake at 350°
until brown.

title: frosted cranberry salad
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving syrup.
Add water to syrup to make 1 cup.
Bring to boil; dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Let cool.
Gently stir in ginger ale.
Chill until partially set. Blend in pineapple, cranberry sauce and marshmallows.
Turn into a 2-quart glass dish and chill until firm.
Prepare topping mix according to package directions.
Blend in softened cream cheese and spread over gelatin.
Roast pecans in butter at 350° for about 10 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Cool slightly, then sprinkle over topping.
Chill until serving time.
Cut and serve on lettuce leaf.
Makes 10 servings.

title: hamburger cake
directions: Melt margarine in frying pan.
Add beef, onion, celery, green pepper, poultry seasoning, salt and pepper; simmer 5 minutes, stirring frequently.
Set aside.
(Pour off excess grease.)

title: strawberry bread
directions: Combine flour, sugar, baking soda, salt and cinnamon. Mix rest of ingredients together, then add to dry mix, blending well. Pour batter into two greased and floured loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until golden brown.

title: farmer-blickenstaff family pie(also called bob andy)
directions: Beat well sugar, cloves, cinnamon, flour and butter.
Add egg yolks and beat.
Blend in egg whites and milk.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
It will be full!
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes, then reduce heat to 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Test with silver table knife like for custard.
Be careful and don't cut through the bottom of the pie.

title: very berry cheesecake
directions: For Crust:
Finely crush wafers and combine with melted margarine.
Transfer to 8-inch spring-form pan.
Press mixture onto bottom and 3/4 inch up sides.
Set aside.

title: chocolate pretzel rings
directions: Place the pretzels on greased baking sheets; place a chocolate kiss in the center of each ring.
Bake at 275 degrees for 2-3 minutes or until chocolate is softened.
Remove from the oven.
Place one M&M on each, pressing down slightly so chocolate fills the ring.
Refrigerate for 5-10 minutes or until chocolate is firm.
Store at room temperature.
Yield: about 4 dozen.

title: chocolate triple
directions: Break cake into bottom of bowl.
Spread 1/2 pudding over this, 12 ounces Cool Whip.
Then top with 3 Skor bars.
Repeat layers. Chip.
Serves 15 to 20.

title: lasagna
directions: Spoon a small amount of spaghetti sauce in a large baking dish to grease pan.
Layer noodles across pan.
Cover noodles with cottage cheese.
Spoon sauce to lightly cover cheese.
Distribute mushrooms on sauce.
Sprinkle hamburger meat on sauce.
Cover with Mozzarella cheese, then Parmesan cheese.
Continue layering process until pan is full.
A regular baking dish will hold two layers. This recipe will make two large and one small baking dishes.
This freezes and reheats great.

title: italian frittata
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in bowl and mix well.
Coat a medium nonstick skillet with cooking spray.
Saute red pepper and broccoli for 2 to 3 minutes.
Remove mixture from skillet and set aside.
Add egg mixture to skillet and cook over low heat until set.
Do not stir.
Top with cooked vegetable mixture, alfalfa sprouts and mushrooms.
Sprinkle with shredded cheese.
Cover tightly and let stand off stove for 3 to 5 minutes until cheese melts.
Serves 2.

title: easy meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients thoroughly.
Pack firmly into loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: gloria's cheesecake
directions: Cream the cheese in a bowl.
Add the sugar gradually.
Add the eggs and beat well.
Stir in lemon juice, vanilla, cornstarch and flour.
Add the butter and mix until smooth.
Blend in sour cream.

title: buttermilk pancakes
directions: Mix soda in buttermilk; set aside.
Put dry ingredients in large bowl; add buttermilk, egg and oil.
Stir until mixed good. Grease griddle.
Recipe may be doubled.
Turn pancakes as soon as puffed and full of bubbles.

title: lucy's cheese puffs
directions: Mix butter, cheese, Worcestershire and Tabasco.
Add flour. Roll into balls.
Cover with wax paper and chill in refrigerator. When ready to cook, remove from fridge and roll into marble-size balls.
Place 2 inches apart on cookie sheet.
Bake for 8 minutes in 425° oven.

title: thai chicken
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients.
Mix well.
Arrange chicken in shallow baking dish, single layer.
Spread sauce on top. Marinate for 2 hours.

title: cheese-eggplant casserole
directions: Peel eggplant; cut into 1-inch cubes.
Cook in boiling salted water for 5 minutes; drain.
Add cheese; mix gently until cheese melts.
Add butter; mix, then add rest of ingredients.
Place in a greased baking dish.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken or turkey delight
directions: Mix together meat potatoes and peas.
Cook until done.
Add soup.
Simmer until hot. Serve over toast, biscuits or chow mein noodles for a variety.

title: jason's favorite chocolate topping
directions: Combine cocoa and sugar in small saucepan.
Blend in evaporated milk.
Add margarine and salt.
Cook and stir constantly until mixture just begins to boil.
Remove from heat; add vanilla.

title: chewies
directions: Melt together butter and chocolate squares.
Add pecans.
Mix in separate bowl, flour, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Stir by hand. Combine and stir carefully all ingredients.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients. Allow to boil 3 minutes only. Add strawberries and sugar. Put mixture in 1 deep dish or 2 regular pie crusts, baked, or graham cracker crust.
Cool in ice box. Top with whipped topping before serving.
